86 ExternalArrayType GetExternalArrayType(DataViewOp op_type) {
87  switch (op_type) {
88 #define V(Name) \
89  case DataViewOp::kGet##Name: \
90  case DataViewOp::kSet##Name: \
91  return kExternal##Name##Array;
92  DATAVIEW_OP_LIST(V)
93 #undef V
94  case DataViewOp::kByteLength:
95  UNREACHABLE();
96  }
97 }
98 
99 size_t GetTypeSize(DataViewOp op_type) {
100  ExternalArrayType array_type = GetExternalArrayType(op_type);
101  switch (array_type) {
102 #define ELEMENTS_KIND_TO_ELEMENT_SIZE(Type, type, TYPE, ctype) \
103  case kExternal##Type##Array: \
104  return sizeof(ctype);
105 
106  TYPED_ARRAYS(ELEMENTS_KIND_TO_ELEMENT_SIZE)
107 #undef ELEMENTS_KIND_TO_ELEMENT_SIZE
108  }
109 }

111 bool ReverseBytesSupported(size_t size_in_bytes) {
112  switch (size_in_bytes) {
113  case 4:
114  case 16:
115  return true;
116  case 8:
117  return Is64();
118  default:
119  return false;
120  }
121 }

123 enum class BranchHintingMode {
124  kNone,
125  kModuleProvided,
126  kStress,
127 };
128 
129 class BranchHintingStresser {
130  public:
131  BranchHint GetNextHint() {
132  // To strike a balance between randomness and simplicity, we simply
133  // iterate over the bits of the random seed.
134  int bit = v8_flags.random_seed & (1 << cursor_);
135  static_assert(sizeof(v8_flags.random_seed) * kBitsPerByte == 32);
136  cursor_ = (cursor_ + 1) & 31;
137  return bit == 0 ? BranchHint::kFalse : BranchHint::kTrue;
138  }
139 
140  private:
141  int cursor_{0};
142 };
143

146 // TODO(14108): Annotate runtime functions as not having side effects
147 // where appropriate.
148 OpIndex WasmGraphBuilderBase::CallRuntime(
149  Zone* zone, Runtime::FunctionId f,
150  std::initializer_list<const OpIndex> args, V<Context> context) {
151  const Runtime::Function* fun = Runtime::FunctionForId(f);
152  OpIndex isolate_root = __ LoadRootRegister();
153  DCHECK_EQ(1, fun->result_size);
154  int builtin_slot_offset =
155  IsolateData::BuiltinSlotOffset(Builtin::kWasmCEntry);
156  OpIndex centry_stub =
157  __ Load(isolate_root, LoadOp::Kind::RawAligned(),
158  MemoryRepresentation::UintPtr(), builtin_slot_offset);
159  // CallRuntime is always called with 0 or 1 argument, so a vector of size 4
160  // always suffices.
161  SmallZoneVector<OpIndex, 4> centry_args(zone);
162  for (OpIndex arg : args) centry_args.emplace_back(arg);
163  centry_args.emplace_back(__ ExternalConstant(ExternalReference::Create(f)));
164  centry_args.emplace_back(__ Word32Constant(fun->nargs));
165  centry_args.emplace_back(context);
166  const CallDescriptor* call_descriptor =
167  compiler::Linkage::GetRuntimeCallDescriptor(
168  __ graph_zone(), f, fun->nargs, Operator::kNoProperties,
169  CallDescriptor::kNoFlags);
170  const TSCallDescriptor* ts_call_descriptor = TSCallDescriptor::Create(
171  call_descriptor, compiler::CanThrow::kYes,
172  compiler::LazyDeoptOnThrow::kNo, __ graph_zone());
173  return __ Call(centry_stub, OpIndex::Invalid(), base::VectorOf(centry_args),
174  ts_call_descriptor);
175 }

177 OpIndex WasmGraphBuilderBase::GetBuiltinPointerTarget(Builtin builtin) {
178  static_assert(std::is_same_v<Smi, BuiltinPtr>, "BuiltinPtr must be Smi");
179  return __ SmiConstant(Smi::FromInt(static_cast<int>(builtin)));
180 }

182 V<WordPtr> WasmGraphBuilderBase::GetTargetForBuiltinCall(
183  Builtin builtin, StubCallMode stub_mode) {
184  return stub_mode == StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub
185  ? __ RelocatableWasmBuiltinCallTarget(builtin)
186  : GetBuiltinPointerTarget(builtin);
187 }

189 V<BigInt> WasmGraphBuilderBase::BuildChangeInt64ToBigInt(
190  V<Word64> input, StubCallMode stub_mode) {
191  Builtin builtin = Is64() ? Builtin::kI64ToBigInt : Builtin::kI32PairToBigInt;
192  V<WordPtr> target = GetTargetForBuiltinCall(builtin, stub_mode);
193  CallInterfaceDescriptor interface_descriptor =
194  Builtins::CallInterfaceDescriptorFor(builtin);
195  const CallDescriptor* call_descriptor =
196  compiler::Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
197  __ graph_zone(), // zone
198  interface_descriptor,
199  0, // stack parameter count
200  CallDescriptor::kNoFlags, // flags
201  Operator::kNoProperties, // properties
202  stub_mode);
203  const TSCallDescriptor* ts_call_descriptor = TSCallDescriptor::Create(
204  call_descriptor, compiler::CanThrow::kNo, compiler::LazyDeoptOnThrow::kNo,
205  __ graph_zone());
206  if constexpr (Is64()) {
207  return V<BigInt>::Cast(__ Call(target, {input}, ts_call_descriptor));
208  }
209  V<Word32> low_word = __ TruncateWord64ToWord32(input);
210  V<Word32> high_word = __ TruncateWord64ToWord32(__ ShiftRightLogical(
211  input, __ Word32Constant(32), WordRepresentation::Word64()));
212  return V<BigInt>::Cast(
213  __ Call(target, {low_word, high_word}, ts_call_descriptor));
214 }
215 
216 std::pair<V<Word32>, V<HeapObject>>
217 WasmGraphBuilderBase::BuildImportedFunctionTargetAndImplicitArg(
218  ConstOrV<Word32> func_index,
219  V<WasmTrustedInstanceData> trusted_instance_data) {
220  V<WasmDispatchTable> dispatch_table = LOAD_IMMUTABLE_PROTECTED_INSTANCE_FIELD(
221  trusted_instance_data, DispatchTableForImports, WasmDispatchTable);
222  // Handle constant indexes specially to reduce graph size, even though later
223  // optimization would optimize this to the same result.
224  if (func_index.is_constant()) {
225  int offset = WasmDispatchTable::OffsetOf(func_index.constant_value());
226  V<Word32> target = __ Load(dispatch_table, LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase(),
227  MemoryRepresentation::Uint32(),
228  offset + WasmDispatchTable::kTargetBias);
229  V<ExposedTrustedObject> implicit_arg =
230  V<ExposedTrustedObject>::Cast(__ LoadProtectedPointerField(
231  dispatch_table, LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase(),
232  offset + WasmDispatchTable::kImplicitArgBias));
233  return {target, implicit_arg};
234  }
235 
236  V<WordPtr> dispatch_table_entry_offset =
237  __ WordPtrMul(__ ChangeUint32ToUintPtr(func_index.value()),
238  WasmDispatchTable::kEntrySize);
239  V<Word32> target = __ Load(
240  dispatch_table, dispatch_table_entry_offset, LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase(),
241  MemoryRepresentation::Uint32(),
242  WasmDispatchTable::kEntriesOffset + WasmDispatchTable::kTargetBias);
243  V<ExposedTrustedObject> implicit_arg = V<ExposedTrustedObject>::Cast(
244  __ LoadProtectedPointerField(dispatch_table, dispatch_table_entry_offset,
245  LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase(),
246  WasmDispatchTable::kEntriesOffset +
247  WasmDispatchTable::kImplicitArgBias,
248  0));
249  return {target, implicit_arg};
250 }
251 
252 std::pair<V<Word32>, V<ExposedTrustedObject>>
253 WasmGraphBuilderBase::BuildFunctionTargetAndImplicitArg(
254  V<WasmInternalFunction> internal_function) {
255  V<ExposedTrustedObject> implicit_arg =
256  V<ExposedTrustedObject>::Cast(__ LoadProtectedPointerField(
257  internal_function, LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase().Immutable(),
258  WasmInternalFunction::kProtectedImplicitArgOffset));
259 
260  V<Word32> target = __ Load(internal_function, LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase(),
261  MemoryRepresentation::Uint32(),
262  WasmInternalFunction::kRawCallTargetOffset);
263 
264  return {target, implicit_arg};
265 }
266 
267 RegisterRepresentation WasmGraphBuilderBase::RepresentationFor(
268  ValueTypeBase type) {
269  switch (type.kind()) {
270  case kI8:
271  case kI16:
272  case kI32:
273  return RegisterRepresentation::Word32();
274  case kI64:
275  return RegisterRepresentation::Word64();
276  case kF16:
277  case kF32:
278  return RegisterRepresentation::Float32();
279  case kF64:
280  return RegisterRepresentation::Float64();
281  case kRefNull:
282  case kRef:
283  return RegisterRepresentation::Tagged();
284  case kS128:
285  return RegisterRepresentation::Simd128();
286  case kVoid:
287  case kTop:
288  case kBottom:
289  UNREACHABLE();
290  }
291 }

293 void WasmGraphBuilderBase::BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlagHelper(
294  Zone* zone, OpIndex thread_in_wasm_flag_address, bool new_value) {
295  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
296  V<Word32> flag_value =
297  __ Load(thread_in_wasm_flag_address, LoadOp::Kind::RawAligned(),
298  MemoryRepresentation::Int32(), 0);
299 
300  IF (UNLIKELY(__ Word32Equal(flag_value, new_value))) {
301  OpIndex message_id = __ TaggedIndexConstant(static_cast<int32_t>(
302  new_value ? AbortReason::kUnexpectedThreadInWasmSet
303  : AbortReason::kUnexpectedThreadInWasmUnset));
304  CallRuntime(zone, Runtime::kAbort, {message_id}, __ NoContextConstant());
305  __ Unreachable();
306  }
307  }
308 
309  __ Store(thread_in_wasm_flag_address, __ Word32Constant(new_value),
310  LoadOp::Kind::RawAligned(), MemoryRepresentation::Int32(),
311  compiler::kNoWriteBarrier);
312 }
313 
314 void WasmGraphBuilderBase::BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlag(Zone* zone,
315  bool new_value) {
316  if (!trap_handler::IsTrapHandlerEnabled()) return;
317 
318  OpIndex isolate_root = __ LoadRootRegister();
319  OpIndex thread_in_wasm_flag_address =
320  __ Load(isolate_root, LoadOp::Kind::RawAligned().Immutable(),
321  MemoryRepresentation::UintPtr(),
322  Isolate::thread_in_wasm_flag_address_offset());
323  BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlagHelper(zone, thread_in_wasm_flag_address,
324  new_value);
325 }

328 // appropriate.
329 OpIndex WasmGraphBuilderBase::CallC(const MachineSignature* sig,
330  ExternalReference ref,
331  std::initializer_list<OpIndex> args) {
332  return WasmGraphBuilderBase::CallC(sig, __ ExternalConstant(ref), args);
333 }
334 
335 OpIndex WasmGraphBuilderBase::CallC(const MachineSignature* sig,
336  OpIndex function,
337  std::initializer_list<OpIndex> args) {
338  DCHECK_LE(sig->return_count(), 1);
339  DCHECK_EQ(sig->parameter_count(), args.size());
340  const CallDescriptor* call_descriptor =
341  compiler::Linkage::GetSimplifiedCDescriptor(__ graph_zone(), sig);
342  const TSCallDescriptor* ts_call_descriptor = TSCallDescriptor::Create(
343  call_descriptor, compiler::CanThrow::kNo, compiler::LazyDeoptOnThrow::kNo,
344  __ graph_zone());
345  return __ Call(function, OpIndex::Invalid(), base::VectorOf(args),
346  ts_call_descriptor);
347 }

349 void WasmGraphBuilderBase::BuildSetNewStackLimit(V<WordPtr> old_limit,
350  V<WordPtr> new_limit) {
351  // Set the new interrupt limit and real limit. Use a compare-and-swap for
352  // the interrupt limit to avoid overwriting a pending interrupt.
353  __ AtomicCompareExchange(
354  __ IsolateField(IsolateFieldId::kJsLimitAddress), __ UintPtrConstant(0),
355  old_limit, new_limit, RegisterRepresentation::WordPtr(),
356  MemoryRepresentation::UintPtr(), compiler::MemoryAccessKind::kNormal,
357  RegisterRepresentation::WordPtr());
358  __ Store(__ LoadRootRegister(), new_limit, StoreOp::Kind::RawAligned(),
359  MemoryRepresentation::UintPtr(), compiler::kNoWriteBarrier,
360  IsolateData::real_jslimit_offset());
361 }
362 
363 V<WordPtr> WasmGraphBuilderBase::BuildSwitchToTheCentralStack(
364  V<WordPtr> old_limit) {
365  // Set the is_on_central_stack flag.
366  OpIndex isolate_root = __ LoadRootRegister();
367  __ Store(isolate_root, __ Word32Constant(1), LoadOp::Kind::RawAligned(),
368  MemoryRepresentation::Uint8(), compiler::kNoWriteBarrier,
369  IsolateData::is_on_central_stack_flag_offset());
370 
371  // Save the old fp and the target sp in the StackMemory's stack switch info.
372  // We are not on the main stack, so the active stack must be set.
373  V<WordPtr> active_stack = __ Load(isolate_root, LoadOp::Kind::RawAligned(),
374  MemoryRepresentation::UintPtr(),
375  IsolateData::active_stack_offset());
376  __ Store(active_stack, __ FramePointer(), StoreOp::Kind::RawAligned(),
377  MemoryRepresentation::UintPtr(), compiler::kNoWriteBarrier,
378  StackMemory::stack_switch_source_fp_offset());
379  V<WordPtr> central_stack_sp = __ Load(
380  isolate_root, LoadOp::Kind::RawAligned(), MemoryRepresentation::UintPtr(),
381  Isolate::central_stack_sp_offset());
382  __ Store(active_stack, central_stack_sp, StoreOp::Kind::RawAligned(),
383  MemoryRepresentation::UintPtr(), compiler::kNoWriteBarrier,
384  StackMemory::stack_switch_target_sp_offset());
385 
386  // Switch the stack limit and the stack pointer.
387  V<WordPtr> central_stack_limit = __ Load(
388  isolate_root, LoadOp::Kind::RawAligned(), MemoryRepresentation::UintPtr(),
389  Isolate::central_stack_limit_offset());
390  BuildSetNewStackLimit(old_limit, central_stack_limit);
391  OpIndex old_sp = __ LoadStackPointer();
392  __ SetStackPointer(central_stack_sp);
393  return old_sp;
394 }
395 
396 // Returns the old (secondary stack's) sp and stack limit.
397 std::pair<V<WordPtr>, V<WordPtr>>
398 WasmGraphBuilderBase::BuildSwitchToTheCentralStackIfNeeded() {
399  V<WordPtr> isolate_root = __ LoadRootRegister();
400  V<Word32> is_on_central_stack_flag = __ Load(
401  isolate_root, LoadOp::Kind::RawAligned(), MemoryRepresentation::Uint8(),
402  IsolateData::is_on_central_stack_flag_offset());
403  ScopedVar<WordPtr> old_sp_var(this, __ IntPtrConstant(0));
404  ScopedVar<WordPtr> old_limit_var(this, __ IntPtrConstant(0));
405  IF_NOT (LIKELY(is_on_central_stack_flag)) {
406  V<WordPtr> old_limit = __ Load(isolate_root, LoadOp::Kind::RawAligned(),
407  MemoryRepresentation::UintPtr(),
408  IsolateData::real_jslimit_offset());
409  V<WordPtr> old_sp = BuildSwitchToTheCentralStack(old_limit);
410  old_sp_var = old_sp;
411  old_limit_var = old_limit;
412  }
413  return {old_sp_var, old_limit_var};
414 }
415 
416 void WasmGraphBuilderBase::BuildSwitchBackFromCentralStack(
417  V<WordPtr> old_sp, V<WordPtr> old_limit) {
418  IF_NOT (LIKELY(__ WordPtrEqual(old_sp, __ IntPtrConstant(0)))) {
419  // Reset is_on_central_stack flag.
420  V<WordPtr> isolate_root = __ LoadRootRegister();
421  __ Store(isolate_root, __ Word32Constant(0), StoreOp::Kind::RawAligned(),
422  MemoryRepresentation::Uint8(), compiler::kNoWriteBarrier,
423  IsolateData::is_on_central_stack_flag_offset());
424 
425  // Clear stack switch info.
426  // We are not on the main stack, so the active stack must be set.
427  V<WordPtr> active_stack = __ Load(isolate_root, LoadOp::Kind::RawAligned(),
428  MemoryRepresentation::UintPtr(),
429  IsolateData::active_stack_offset());
430  __ Store(active_stack, __ UintPtrConstant(0), StoreOp::Kind::RawAligned(),
431  MemoryRepresentation::UintPtr(), compiler::kNoWriteBarrier,
432  StackMemory::stack_switch_source_fp_offset());
433 
434  // Restore the old stack limit and stack pointer.
435  V<WordPtr> real_jslimit = __ Load(isolate_root, LoadOp::Kind::RawAligned(),
436  MemoryRepresentation::UintPtr(),
437  IsolateData::real_jslimit_offset());
438  BuildSetNewStackLimit(real_jslimit, old_limit);
439  __ SetStackPointer(old_sp);
440  }
441 }

443 class TurboshaftGraphBuildingInterface : public WasmGraphBuilderBase {
444  private:
445  class BlockPhis;
446  class InstanceCache;
447 
448  public:
449  enum Mode {
450  kRegular,
451  kInlinedUnhandled,
452  kInlinedWithCatch,
453  kInlinedTailCall
454  };
455  using ValidationTag = Decoder::NoValidationTag;
456  using FullDecoder =
457  WasmFullDecoder<ValidationTag, TurboshaftGraphBuildingInterface>;
458  static constexpr bool kUsesPoppedArgs = true;
459 
460  struct Value : public ValueBase<ValidationTag> {
461  OpIndex op = OpIndex::Invalid();
462  template <typename... Args>
463  explicit Value(Args&&... args) V8_NOEXCEPT
464  : ValueBase(std::forward<Args>(args)...) {}
465  };
466 
467  struct Control : public ControlBase<Value, ValidationTag> {
468  TSBlock* merge_block = nullptr;
469  // for 'if', loops, and 'try'/'try-table' respectively.
470  TSBlock* false_or_loop_or_catch_block = nullptr;
471  BitVector* assigned = nullptr; // Only for loops.
472  V<Object> exception = OpIndex::Invalid(); // Only for 'try-catch'.
473 
474  template <typename... Args>
475  explicit Control(Args&&... args) V8_NOEXCEPT
476  : ControlBase(std::forward<Args>(args)...) {}
477  };
478 
479  public:
480  // For non-inlined functions.
481  TurboshaftGraphBuildingInterface(
482  Zone* zone, CompilationEnv* env, Assembler& assembler,
483  std::unique_ptr<AssumptionsJournal>* assumptions,
484  ZoneVector<WasmInliningPosition>* inlining_positions, int func_index,
485  bool shared, const WireBytesStorage* wire_bytes)
486  : WasmGraphBuilderBase(zone, assembler),
487  mode_(kRegular),
488  block_phis_(zone),
489  env_(env),
490  owned_instance_cache_(std::make_unique<InstanceCache>(assembler)),
491  instance_cache_(*owned_instance_cache_.get()),
492  assumptions_(assumptions),
493  inlining_positions_(inlining_positions),
494  ssa_env_(zone),
495  func_index_(func_index),
496  shared_(shared),
497  wire_bytes_(wire_bytes),
498  return_phis_(nullptr),
499  is_inlined_tail_call_(false) {
500  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(env_);
501  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(env_->module);
502  }
503 
504  // For inlined functions.
505  TurboshaftGraphBuildingInterface(
506  Zone* zone, CompilationEnv* env, Assembler& assembler, Mode mode,
507  InstanceCache& instance_cache,
508  std::unique_ptr<AssumptionsJournal>* assumptions,
509  ZoneVector<WasmInliningPosition>* inlining_positions, int func_index,
510  bool shared, const WireBytesStorage* wire_bytes,
511  base::Vector<OpIndex> real_parameters, TSBlock* return_block,
512  BlockPhis* return_phis, TSBlock* catch_block, bool is_inlined_tail_call,
513  OptionalV<FrameState> parent_frame_state)
514  : WasmGraphBuilderBase(zone, assembler),
515  mode_(mode),
516  block_phis_(zone),
517  env_(env),
518  instance_cache_(instance_cache),
519  assumptions_(assumptions),
520  inlining_positions_(inlining_positions),
521  ssa_env_(zone),
522  func_index_(func_index),
523  shared_(shared),
524  wire_bytes_(wire_bytes),
525  real_parameters_(real_parameters),
526  return_block_(return_block),
527  return_phis_(return_phis),
528  return_catch_block_(catch_block),
529  is_inlined_tail_call_(is_inlined_tail_call),
530  parent_frame_state_(parent_frame_state) {
531  DCHECK_NE(mode_, kRegular);
532  DCHECK_EQ(return_block == nullptr, mode == kInlinedTailCall);
533  DCHECK_EQ(catch_block != nullptr, mode == kInlinedWithCatch);
534  }
535 
536  void StartFunction(FullDecoder* decoder) {
537  if (mode_ == kRegular) __ Bind(__ NewBlock());
538  // Set 0 as the current source position (before locals declarations).
539  __ SetCurrentOrigin(WasmPositionToOpIndex(0, inlining_id_));
540  ssa_env_.resize(decoder->num_locals());
541  uint32_t index = 0;
542  V<WasmTrustedInstanceData> trusted_instance_data;
543  if (mode_ == kRegular) {
544  static_assert(kWasmInstanceDataParameterIndex == 0);
545  trusted_instance_data = __ WasmInstanceDataParameter();
546  for (; index < decoder->sig_->parameter_count(); index++) {
547  // Parameter indices are shifted by 1 because parameter 0 is the
548  // instance.
549  ssa_env_[index] = __ Parameter(
550  index + 1, RepresentationFor(decoder->sig_->GetParam(index)));
551  }
552  instance_cache_.Initialize(trusted_instance_data, decoder->module_);
553  } else {
554  trusted_instance_data = real_parameters_[0];
555  for (; index < decoder->sig_->parameter_count(); index++) {
556  // Parameter indices are shifted by 1 because parameter 0 is the
557  // instance.
558  ssa_env_[index] = real_parameters_[index + 1];
559  }
560  if (!is_inlined_tail_call_) {
561  return_phis_->InitReturnPhis(decoder->sig_->returns());
562  }
563  }
564  while (index < decoder->num_locals()) {
565  ValueType type = decoder->local_type(index);
566  OpIndex op;
567  if (!type.is_defaultable()) {
568  DCHECK(type.is_reference());
569  op = __ RootConstant(RootIndex::kOptimizedOut);
570  } else {
571  op = DefaultValue(type);
572  }
573  while (index < decoder->num_locals() &&
574  decoder->local_type(index) == type) {
575  ssa_env_[index++] = op;
576  }
577  }
578 
579  if (v8_flags.wasm_inlining) {
580  if (mode_ == kRegular) {
581  if (v8_flags.liftoff) {
582  inlining_decisions_ = InliningTree::CreateRoot(
583  decoder->zone_, decoder->module_, func_index_);
584  } else {
585  set_no_liftoff_inlining_budget(
586  InliningTree::NoLiftoffBudget(decoder->module_, func_index_));
587  }
588  } else {
589 #if DEBUG
590  // We don't have support for inlining asm.js functions, those should
591  // never be selected in `InliningTree`.
592  DCHECK(!wasm::is_asmjs_module(decoder->module_));
593 
594  if (v8_flags.liftoff && inlining_decisions_) {
595  // DCHECK that `inlining_decisions_` is consistent.
596  DCHECK(inlining_decisions_->is_inlined());
597  DCHECK_EQ(inlining_decisions_->function_index(), func_index_);
598  base::MutexGuard mutex_guard(&decoder->module_->type_feedback.mutex);
599  if (inlining_decisions_->feedback_found()) {
600  DCHECK_NE(
601  decoder->module_->type_feedback.feedback_for_function.find(
602  func_index_),
603  decoder->module_->type_feedback.feedback_for_function.end());
604  DCHECK_EQ(inlining_decisions_->function_calls().size(),
605  decoder->module_->type_feedback.feedback_for_function
606  .find(func_index_)
607  ->second.feedback_vector.size());
608  DCHECK_EQ(inlining_decisions_->function_calls().size(),
609  decoder->module_->type_feedback.feedback_for_function
610  .find(func_index_)
611  ->second.call_targets.size());
612  }
613  }
614 #endif
615  }
616  }
617 
618  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
619  IF_NOT (LIKELY(__ HasInstanceType(trusted_instance_data,
620  WASM_TRUSTED_INSTANCE_DATA_TYPE))) {
621  OpIndex message_id = __ TaggedIndexConstant(
622  static_cast<int32_t>(AbortReason::kUnexpectedInstanceType));
623  CallRuntime(decoder->zone(), Runtime::kAbort, {message_id},
624  __ NoContextConstant());
625  __ Unreachable();
626  }
627  }
628 
629  if (mode_ == kRegular) {
630  StackCheck(WasmStackCheckOp::Kind::kFunctionEntry, decoder);
631  }
632 
633  if (v8_flags.trace_wasm) {
634  __ SetCurrentOrigin(
635  WasmPositionToOpIndex(decoder->position(), inlining_id_));
636  CallRuntime(decoder->zone(), Runtime::kWasmTraceEnter, {},
637  __ NoContextConstant());
638  }
639 
640  auto branch_hints_it = decoder->module_->branch_hints.find(func_index_);
641  if (v8_flags.stress_branch_hinting) {
642  // Stress mode takes precedence over a branch hints section.
643  branch_hinting_mode_ = BranchHintingMode::kStress;
644  } else if (branch_hints_it != decoder->module_->branch_hints.end()) {
645  branch_hints_ = &branch_hints_it->second;
646  branch_hinting_mode_ = BranchHintingMode::kModuleProvided;
647  } else {
648  branch_hinting_mode_ = BranchHintingMode::kNone;
649  }
650  }
651 
652  void StartFunctionBody(FullDecoder* decoder, Control* block) {}
653 
654  void FinishFunction(FullDecoder* decoder) {
655  if (v8_flags.liftoff && inlining_decisions_ &&
656  inlining_decisions_->feedback_found()) {
657  DCHECK_EQ(
658  feedback_slot_,
659  static_cast<int>(inlining_decisions_->function_calls().size()) - 1);
660  }
661  if (mode_ == kRegular) {
662  // Just accessing `source_positions` at the maximum `OpIndex` already
663  // pre-allocates the underlying storage such that we avoid repeatedly
664  // resizing/copying in the following loop.
665  __ output_graph().source_positions()[__ output_graph().EndIndex()];
666 
667  for (OpIndex index : __ output_graph().AllOperationIndices()) {
668  SourcePosition position = OpIndexToSourcePosition(
669  __ output_graph().operation_origins()[index]);
670  __ output_graph().source_positions()[index] = position;
671  }
672  if (v8_flags.trace_wasm_inlining) {
673  uint32_t node_count =
674  __ output_graph().NumberOfOperationsForDebugging();
675  PrintF("[function %d: emitted %d nodes]\n", func_index_, node_count);
676  }
677  }
678  }
679 
680  void OnFirstError(FullDecoder*) {}
681 
682  void NextInstruction(FullDecoder* decoder, WasmOpcode) {
683  __ SetCurrentOrigin(
684  WasmPositionToOpIndex(decoder->position(), inlining_id_));
685  }
686 
687  // ******** Control Flow ********
688  // The basic structure of control flow is {block_phis_}. It contains a mapping
689  // from blocks to phi inputs corresponding to the SSA values plus the stack
690  // merge values at the beginning of the block.
691  // - When we create a new block (to be bound in the future), we register it to
692  // {block_phis_} with {NewBlockWithPhis}.
693  // - When we encounter an jump to a block, we invoke {SetupControlFlowEdge}.
694  // - Finally, when we bind a block, we setup its phis, the SSA environment,
695  // and its merge values, with {BindBlockAndGeneratePhis}.
696  // - When we create a loop, we generate PendingLoopPhis for the SSA state and
697  // the incoming stack values. We also create a block which will act as a
698  // merge block for all loop backedges (since a loop in Turboshaft can only
699  // have one backedge). When we PopControl a loop, we enter the merge block
700  // to create its Phis for all backedges as necessary, and use those values
701  // to patch the backedge of the PendingLoopPhis of the loop.
702 
703  void Block(FullDecoder* decoder, Control* block) {
704  block->merge_block = NewBlockWithPhis(decoder, block->br_merge());
705  }
706 
707  void Loop(FullDecoder* decoder, Control* block) {
708  TSBlock* loop = __ NewLoopHeader();
709  __ Goto(loop);
710  __ Bind(loop);
711 
712  bool can_be_innermost = false; // unused
713  BitVector* assigned = WasmDecoder<ValidationTag>::AnalyzeLoopAssignment(
714  decoder, decoder->pc(), decoder->num_locals(), decoder->zone(),
715  &can_be_innermost);
716  block->assigned = assigned;
717 
718  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < decoder->num_locals(); i++) {
719  if (!assigned->Contains(i)) continue;
720  OpIndex phi = __ PendingLoopPhi(
721  ssa_env_[i], RepresentationFor(decoder->local_type(i)));
722  ssa_env_[i] = phi;
723  }
724  uint32_t arity = block->start_merge.arity;
725  Value* stack_base = arity > 0 ? decoder->stack_value(arity) : nullptr;
726  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < arity; i++) {
727  OpIndex phi = __ PendingLoopPhi(stack_base[i].op,
728  RepresentationFor(stack_base[i].type));
729  block->start_merge[i].op = phi;
730  }
731 
732  StackCheck(WasmStackCheckOp::Kind::kLoop, decoder);
733 
734  TSBlock* loop_merge = NewBlockWithPhis(decoder, &block->start_merge);
735  block->merge_block = loop_merge;
736  block->false_or_loop_or_catch_block = loop;
737  }
738 
739  void If(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& cond, Control* if_block) {
740  TSBlock* true_block = __ NewBlock();
741  TSBlock* false_block = NewBlockWithPhis(decoder, nullptr);
742  TSBlock* merge_block = NewBlockWithPhis(decoder, &if_block->end_merge);
743  if_block->false_or_loop_or_catch_block = false_block;
744  if_block->merge_block = merge_block;
745  SetupControlFlowEdge(decoder, false_block);
746  __ Branch({cond.op, GetBranchHint(decoder)}, true_block, false_block);
747  __ Bind(true_block);
748  }
749 
750  void Else(FullDecoder* decoder, Control* if_block) {
751  if (if_block->reachable()) {
752  SetupControlFlowEdge(decoder, if_block->merge_block);
753  __ Goto(if_block->merge_block);
754  }
755  BindBlockAndGeneratePhis(decoder, if_block->false_or_loop_or_catch_block,
756  nullptr);
757  }
758 
759  void BrOrRet(FullDecoder* decoder, uint32_t depth, uint32_t drop_values = 0) {
760  if (depth == decoder->control_depth() - 1) {
761  DoReturn(decoder, drop_values);
762  } else {
763  Control* target = decoder->control_at(depth);
764  SetupControlFlowEdge(decoder, target->merge_block, drop_values);
765  __ Goto(target->merge_block);
766  }
767  }
768 
769  void BrIf(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& cond, uint32_t depth) {
770  BranchHint hint = GetBranchHint(decoder);
771  if (depth == decoder->control_depth() - 1) {
772  IF ({cond.op, hint}) {
773  DoReturn(decoder, 0);
774  }
775  } else {
776  Control* target = decoder->control_at(depth);
777  SetupControlFlowEdge(decoder, target->merge_block);
778  TSBlock* non_branching = __ NewBlock();
779  __ Branch({cond.op, hint}, target->merge_block, non_branching);
780  __ Bind(non_branching);
781  }
782  }
783 
784  // An analysis to determine whether a br_table should be lowered to a switch
785  // or a series of compare and branch. This can be for small tables or larger
786  // 'sparse' ones, which include many cases but few targets. A sparse table may
787  // look like this: br_table [ 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 2, 0 ] which can be lowered to
788  // two conditional branches followed by an unconditional one. The advantages
789  // of this are reducing the space required for the table and reducing the
790  // latency.
791  template <typename ValidationTag>
792  class BrTableAnalysis {
793  public:
794  static constexpr int32_t kMaxComparesPerTarget = 2;
795  static constexpr uint32_t kMaxTargets = 3;
796  static constexpr int32_t kMaxTableCount = 20;
797  using CaseVector = base::SmallVector<uint8_t, 8>;
798  using TargetMap = absl::btree_map<uint32_t, CaseVector>;
799 
800  bool LowerToBranches(Decoder* decoder, const BranchTableImmediate& imm) {
801  BranchTableIterator<ValidationTag> iterator(decoder, imm);
802  while (iterator.has_next()) {
803  uint32_t i = iterator.cur_index();
804  uint32_t target = iterator.next();
805 
806  if (i == imm.table_count) {
807  AddDefault(target);
808  } else if (!TryAddTarget(target, i)) {
809  return false;
810  }
811  }
812  primary_indices_ = other_targets_[primary_target()];
813  other_targets_.erase(primary_target());
814  size_t total_targets = other_targets_.size() + 1;
815  if (default_target() != primary_target() &&
816  !other_targets_.count(default_target())) {
817  total_targets++;
818  }
819  return total_targets <= kMaxTargets;
820  }
821  // The most often occurring target, or the default if there is no other
822  // target with multiple cases.
823  uint32_t primary_target() const { return primary_target_.value(); }
824  // The default target, for when the br_table index is out-of-range.
825  uint32_t default_target() const { return default_target_.value(); }
826  // other_targets doesn't include the primary target, nor the default if it
827  // isn't an in-range target.
828  const TargetMap& other_targets() const { return other_targets_; }
829  // All the indices which target the primary target.
830  const CaseVector& primary_indices() const { return primary_indices_; }
831 
832  private:
833  bool TryAddTarget(uint32_t target, uint32_t index) {
834  DCHECK_LT(index, kMaxTableCount);
835  CaseVector& cases = other_targets_[target];
836  if (other_targets_.size() > kMaxTargets) {
837  return false;
838  }
839  if (cases.size() == kMaxComparesPerTarget) {
840  if (primary_target_.has_value() && target != primary_target()) {
841  return false;
842  }
843  primary_target_ = target;
844  }
845  cases.push_back(index);
846  return true;
847  }
848  void AddDefault(uint32_t target) {
849  default_target_ = target;
850  if (!primary_target_.has_value()) {
851  primary_target_ = default_target();
852  }
853  }
854 
855  std::optional<uint32_t> default_target_;
856  std::optional<uint32_t> primary_target_;
857  CaseVector primary_indices_;
858  TargetMap other_targets_;
859  };
860 
861  void BrTable(FullDecoder* decoder, const BranchTableImmediate& imm,
862  const Value& key) {
863  if (imm.table_count < BrTableAnalysis<ValidationTag>::kMaxTableCount) {
864  BrTableAnalysis<ValidationTag> table_analysis;
865  if (table_analysis.LowerToBranches(decoder, imm)) {
866  auto generate_cond =
867  [this](const Value& key,
868  const BrTableAnalysis<ValidationTag>::CaseVector& cases)
869  -> OpIndex {
870  switch (cases.size()) {
871  default:
872  static_assert(
873  BrTableAnalysis<ValidationTag>::kMaxComparesPerTarget <= 2);
874  UNREACHABLE();
875  case 1:
876  return __ Word32Equal(key.op, __ Word32Constant(cases[0]));
877  case 2: {
878  return __ Word32BitwiseOr(__ Word32Equal(key.op, cases[0]),
879  __ Word32Equal(key.op, cases[1]));
880  }
881  }
882  };
883  auto insert_cond_branch = [this, &decoder](OpIndex cond,
884  uint32_t depth) {
885  BranchHint hint = GetBranchHint(decoder);
886  if (depth == decoder->control_depth() - 1) {
887  IF ({cond, hint}) {
888  DoReturn(decoder, 0);
889  }
890  } else {
891  Control* target = decoder->control_at(depth);
892  SetupControlFlowEdge(decoder, target->merge_block);
893  TSBlock* non_branching = __ NewBlock();
894  __ Branch({cond, hint}, target->merge_block, non_branching);
895  __ Bind(non_branching);
896  }
897  };
898  // Insert conditional branches to the other targets.
899  for (auto const& [target, cases] : table_analysis.other_targets()) {
900  DCHECK_LE(cases.size(),
901  BrTableAnalysis<ValidationTag>::kMaxComparesPerTarget);
902  insert_cond_branch(generate_cond(key, cases), target);
903  }
904  // If needed, insert the range check for the primary target.
905  if (table_analysis.primary_target() !=
906  table_analysis.default_target()) {
907  OpIndex lower = __ Word32Equal(__ Int32LessThan(key.op, 0), 0);
908  OpIndex upper =
909  __ Int32LessThan(key.op, __ Word32Constant(imm.table_count));
910  OpIndex cond = __ Word32BitwiseAnd(lower, upper);
911  insert_cond_branch(cond, table_analysis.primary_target());
912  }
913  // Always fallthrough and branch to the default case.
914  BrOrRet(decoder, table_analysis.default_target());
915  return;
916  }
917  }
918  compiler::turboshaft::SwitchOp::Case* cases =
919  __ output_graph().graph_zone()
920  -> AllocateArray<compiler::turboshaft::SwitchOp::Case>(
921  imm.table_count);
922  BranchTableIterator<ValidationTag> new_block_iterator(decoder, imm);
923  SmallZoneVector<TSBlock*, 16> intermediate_blocks(decoder->zone_);
924  TSBlock* default_case = nullptr;
925  while (new_block_iterator.has_next()) {
926  TSBlock* intermediate = __ NewBlock();
927  intermediate_blocks.emplace_back(intermediate);
928  uint32_t i = new_block_iterator.cur_index();
929  if (i == imm.table_count) {
930  default_case = intermediate;
931  } else {
932  cases[i] = {static_cast<int>(i), intermediate, BranchHint::kNone};
933  }
934  new_block_iterator.next();
935  }
936  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(default_case);
937  __ Switch(key.op, base::VectorOf(cases, imm.table_count), default_case);
938 
939  int i = 0;
940  BranchTableIterator<ValidationTag> branch_iterator(decoder, imm);
941  while (branch_iterator.has_next()) {
942  TSBlock* intermediate = intermediate_blocks[i];
943  i++;
944  __ Bind(intermediate);
945  BrOrRet(decoder, branch_iterator.next());
946  }
947  }
948 
949  void FallThruTo(FullDecoder* decoder, Control* block) {
950  // TODO(14108): Why is {block->reachable()} not reliable here? Maybe it is
951  // not in other spots as well.
952  if (__ current_block() != nullptr) {
953  SetupControlFlowEdge(decoder, block->merge_block);
954  __ Goto(block->merge_block);
955  }
956  }
957 
958  void PopControl(FullDecoder* decoder, Control* block) {
959  switch (block->kind) {
960  case kControlIf:
961  if (block->reachable()) {
962  SetupControlFlowEdge(decoder, block->merge_block);
963  __ Goto(block->merge_block);
964  }
965  BindBlockAndGeneratePhis(decoder, block->false_or_loop_or_catch_block,
966  nullptr);
967  // Exceptionally for one-armed if, we cannot take the values from the
968  // stack; we have to pass the stack values at the beginning of the
969  // if-block.
970  SetupControlFlowEdge(decoder, block->merge_block, 0, OpIndex::Invalid(),
971  &block->start_merge);
972  __ Goto(block->merge_block);
973  BindBlockAndGeneratePhis(decoder, block->merge_block,
974  block->br_merge());
975  break;
976  case kControlIfElse:
977  case kControlBlock:
978  case kControlTry:
979  case kControlTryCatch:
980  case kControlTryCatchAll:
981  // {block->reachable()} is not reliable here for exceptions, because
982  // the decoder sets the reachability to the upper block's reachability
983  // before calling this interface function.
984  if (__ current_block() != nullptr) {
985  SetupControlFlowEdge(decoder, block->merge_block);
986  __ Goto(block->merge_block);
987  }
988  BindBlockAndGeneratePhis(decoder, block->merge_block,
989  block->br_merge());
990  break;
991  case kControlTryTable:
992  DCHECK_EQ(__ current_block(), nullptr);
993  BindBlockAndGeneratePhis(decoder, block->merge_block,
994  block->br_merge());
995  break;
996  case kControlLoop: {
997  TSBlock* post_loop = NewBlockWithPhis(decoder, nullptr);
998  if (block->reachable()) {
999  SetupControlFlowEdge(decoder, post_loop);
1000  __ Goto(post_loop);
1001  }
1002  if (!block->false_or_loop_or_catch_block->IsBound()) {
1003  // The loop is unreachable. In this case, no operations have been
1004  // emitted for it. Do nothing.
1005  } else if (block->merge_block->PredecessorCount() == 0) {
1006  // Turns out, the loop has no backedges, i.e. it is not quite a loop
1007  // at all. Replace it with a merge, and its PendingPhis with one-input
1008  // phis.
1009  block->false_or_loop_or_catch_block->SetKind(
1010  compiler::turboshaft::Block::Kind::kMerge);
1011  for (auto& op : __ output_graph().operations(
1012  *block->false_or_loop_or_catch_block)) {
1013  PendingLoopPhiOp* pending_phi = op.TryCast<PendingLoopPhiOp>();
1014  if (!pending_phi) break;
1015  OpIndex replaced = __ output_graph().Index(op);
1016  __ output_graph().Replace<compiler::turboshaft::PhiOp>(
1017  replaced, base::VectorOf({pending_phi -> first()}),
1018  pending_phi->rep);
1019  }
1020  } else {
1021  // We abuse the start merge of the loop, which is not used otherwise
1022  // anymore, to store backedge inputs for the pending phi stack values
1023  // of the loop.
1024  BindBlockAndGeneratePhis(decoder, block->merge_block,
1025  block->br_merge());
1026  __ Goto(block->false_or_loop_or_catch_block);
1027  auto operations = __ output_graph().operations(
1028  *block -> false_or_loop_or_catch_block);
1029  auto to = operations.begin();
1030  // The VariableReducer can introduce loop phis as well which are at
1031  // the beginning of the block. We need to skip them.
1032  while (to != operations.end() &&
1033  to->Is<compiler::turboshaft::PhiOp>()) {
1034  ++to;
1035  }
1036  for (auto it = block->assigned->begin(); it != block->assigned->end();
1037  ++it, ++to) {
1038  // The last bit represents the instance cache.
1039  if (*it == static_cast<int>(ssa_env_.size())) break;
1040  PendingLoopPhiOp& pending_phi = to->Cast<PendingLoopPhiOp>();
1041  OpIndex replaced = __ output_graph().Index(*to);
1042  __ output_graph().Replace<compiler::turboshaft::PhiOp>(
1043  replaced, base::VectorOf({pending_phi.first(), ssa_env_[*it]}),
1044  pending_phi.rep);
1045  }
1046  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < block->br_merge()->arity; ++i, ++to) {
1047  PendingLoopPhiOp& pending_phi = to->Cast<PendingLoopPhiOp>();
1048  OpIndex replaced = __ output_graph().Index(*to);
1049  __ output_graph().Replace<compiler::turboshaft::PhiOp>(
1050  replaced,
1051  base::VectorOf(
1052  {pending_phi.first(), (*block->br_merge())[i].op}),
1053  pending_phi.rep);
1054  }
1055  }
1056  BindBlockAndGeneratePhis(decoder, post_loop, nullptr);
1057  break;
1058  }
1059  }
1060  }
1061 
1062  void DoReturn(FullDecoder* decoder, uint32_t drop_values) {
1063  size_t return_count = decoder->sig_->return_count();
1064  SmallZoneVector<OpIndex, 16> return_values(return_count, decoder->zone_);
1065  Value* stack_base = return_count == 0
1066  ? nullptr
1067  : decoder->stack_value(static_cast<uint32_t>(
1068  return_count + drop_values));
1069  for (size_t i = 0; i < return_count; i++) {
1070  return_values[i] = stack_base[i].op;
1071  }
1072  if (v8_flags.trace_wasm) {
1073  V<WordPtr> info = __ IntPtrConstant(0);
1074  if (return_count == 1) {
1075  wasm::ValueType return_type = decoder->sig_->GetReturn(0);
1076  int size = return_type.value_kind_size();
1077  // TODO(14108): This won't fit everything.
1078  info = __ StackSlot(size, size);
1079  // TODO(14108): Write barrier might be needed.
1080  __ Store(
1081  info, return_values[0], StoreOp::Kind::RawAligned(),
1082  MemoryRepresentation::FromMachineType(return_type.machine_type()),
1083  compiler::kNoWriteBarrier);
1084  }
1085  CallRuntime(decoder->zone(), Runtime::kWasmTraceExit, {info},
1086  __ NoContextConstant());
1087  }
1088  if (mode_ == kRegular || mode_ == kInlinedTailCall) {
1089  __ Return(__ Word32Constant(0), base::VectorOf(return_values),
1090  v8_flags.experimental_wasm_growable_stacks);
1091  } else {
1092  // Do not add return values if we are in unreachable code.
1093  if (__ generating_unreachable_operations()) return;
1094  for (size_t i = 0; i < return_count; i++) {
1095  return_phis_->AddInputForPhi(i, return_values[i]);
1096  }
1097  __ Goto(return_block_);
1098  }
1099  }

1201 
1202  void Select(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& cond, const Value& fval,
1203  const Value& tval, Value* result) {
1204  using Implementation = compiler::turboshaft::SelectOp::Implementation;
1205  bool use_select = false;
1206  switch (tval.type.kind()) {
1207  case kI32:
1208  if (SupportedOperations::word32_select()) use_select = true;
1209  break;
1210  case kI64:
1211  if (SupportedOperations::word64_select()) use_select = true;
1212  break;
1213  case kF32:
1214  if (SupportedOperations::float32_select()) use_select = true;
1215  break;
1216  case kF64:
1217  if (SupportedOperations::float64_select()) use_select = true;
1218  break;
1219  case kRef:
1220  case kRefNull:
1221  case kS128:
1222  break;
1223  case kI8:
1224  case kI16:
1225  case kF16:
1226  case kVoid:
1227  case kTop:
1228  case kBottom:
1229  UNREACHABLE();
1230  }
1231  result->op = __ Select(
1232  cond.op, tval.op, fval.op, RepresentationFor(tval.type),
1233  BranchHint::kNone,
1234  use_select ? Implementation::kCMove : Implementation::kBranch);
1235  }
1236 
1237  OpIndex BuildChangeEndiannessStore(OpIndex node,
1238  MachineRepresentation mem_rep,
1239  wasm::ValueType wasmtype) {
1240  OpIndex result;
1241  OpIndex value = node;
1242  int value_size_in_bytes = wasmtype.value_kind_size();
1243  int value_size_in_bits = 8 * value_size_in_bytes;
1244  bool is_float = false;
1245 
1246  switch (wasmtype.kind()) {
1247  case wasm::kF64:
1248  value = __ BitcastFloat64ToWord64(node);
1249  is_float = true;
1250  [[fallthrough]];
1251  case wasm::kI64:
1252  result = __ Word64Constant(static_cast<uint64_t>(0));
1253  break;
1254  case wasm::kF32:
1255  value = __ BitcastFloat32ToWord32(node);
1256  is_float = true;
1257  [[fallthrough]];
1258  case wasm::kI32:
1259  result = __ Word32Constant(0);
1260  break;
1261  case wasm::kS128:
1262  DCHECK(ReverseBytesSupported(value_size_in_bytes));
1263  break;
1264  default:
1265  UNREACHABLE();
1266  }
1267 
1268  if (mem_rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord8) {
1269  // No need to change endianness for byte size, return original node
1270  return node;
1271  }
1272  if (wasmtype == wasm::kWasmI64 &&
1273  mem_rep < MachineRepresentation::kWord64) {
1274  // In case we store lower part of WasmI64 expression, we can truncate
1275  // upper 32bits.
1276  value_size_in_bytes = wasm::kWasmI32.value_kind_size();
1277  value_size_in_bits = 8 * value_size_in_bytes;
1278  if (mem_rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord16) {
1279  value = __ Word32ShiftLeft(value, 16);
1280  }
1281  } else if (wasmtype == wasm::kWasmI32 &&
1282  mem_rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord16) {
1283  value = __ Word32ShiftLeft(value, 16);
1284  }
1285 
1286  int i;
1287  uint32_t shift_count;
1288 
1289  if (ReverseBytesSupported(value_size_in_bytes)) {
1290  switch (value_size_in_bytes) {
1291  case 4:
1292  result = __ Word32ReverseBytes(V<Word32>::Cast(value));
1293  break;
1294  case 8:
1295  result = __ Word64ReverseBytes(V<Word64>::Cast(value));
1296  break;
1297  case 16:
1298  result = __ Simd128ReverseBytes(
1299  V<compiler::turboshaft::Simd128>::Cast(value));
1300  break;
1301  default:
1302  UNREACHABLE();
1303  }
1304  } else {
1305  for (i = 0, shift_count = value_size_in_bits - 8;
1306  i < value_size_in_bits / 2; i += 8, shift_count -= 16) {
1307  OpIndex shift_lower;
1308  OpIndex shift_higher;
1309  OpIndex lower_byte;
1310  OpIndex higher_byte;
1311 
1312  DCHECK_LT(0, shift_count);
1313  DCHECK_EQ(0, (shift_count + 8) % 16);
1314 
1315  if (value_size_in_bits > 32) {
1316  shift_lower = __ Word64ShiftLeft(value, shift_count);
1317  shift_higher = __ Word64ShiftRightLogical(value, shift_count);
1318  lower_byte = __ Word64BitwiseAnd(shift_lower,
1319  static_cast<uint64_t>(0xFF)
1320  << (value_size_in_bits - 8 - i));
1321  higher_byte = __ Word64BitwiseAnd(shift_higher,
1322  static_cast<uint64_t>(0xFF) << i);
1323  result = __ Word64BitwiseOr(result, lower_byte);
1324  result = __ Word64BitwiseOr(result, higher_byte);
1325  } else {
1326  shift_lower = __ Word32ShiftLeft(value, shift_count);
1327  shift_higher = __ Word32ShiftRightLogical(value, shift_count);
1328  lower_byte = __ Word32BitwiseAnd(shift_lower,
1329  static_cast<uint32_t>(0xFF)
1330  << (value_size_in_bits - 8 - i));
1331  higher_byte = __ Word32BitwiseAnd(shift_higher,
1332  static_cast<uint32_t>(0xFF) << i);
1333  result = __ Word32BitwiseOr(result, lower_byte);
1334  result = __ Word32BitwiseOr(result, higher_byte);
1335  }
1336  }
1337  }
1338 
1339  if (is_float) {
1340  switch (wasmtype.kind()) {
1341  case wasm::kF64:
1342  result = __ BitcastWord64ToFloat64(result);
1343  break;
1344  case wasm::kF32:
1345  result = __ BitcastWord32ToFloat32(result);
1346  break;
1347  default:
1348  UNREACHABLE();
1349  }
1350  }
1351 
1352  return result;
1353  }
1354 
1355  OpIndex BuildChangeEndiannessLoad(OpIndex node, MachineType memtype,
1356  wasm::ValueType wasmtype) {
1357  OpIndex result;
1358  OpIndex value = node;
1359  int value_size_in_bytes = ElementSizeInBytes(memtype.representation());
1360  int value_size_in_bits = 8 * value_size_in_bytes;
1361  bool is_float = false;
1362 
1363  switch (memtype.representation()) {
1364  case MachineRepresentation::kFloat64:
1365  value = __ BitcastFloat64ToWord64(node);
1366  is_float = true;
1367  [[fallthrough]];
1368  case MachineRepresentation::kWord64:
1369  result = __ Word64Constant(static_cast<uint64_t>(0));
1370  break;
1371  case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32:
1372  value = __ BitcastFloat32ToWord32(node);
1373  is_float = true;
1374  [[fallthrough]];
1375  case MachineRepresentation::kWord32:
1376  case MachineRepresentation::kWord16:
1377  result = __ Word32Constant(0);
1378  break;
1379  case MachineRepresentation::kWord8:
1380  // No need to change endianness for byte size, return original node.
1381  return node;
1382  case MachineRepresentation::kSimd128:
1383  DCHECK(ReverseBytesSupported(value_size_in_bytes));
1384  break;
1385  default:
1386  UNREACHABLE();
1387  }
1388 
1389  int i;
1390  uint32_t shift_count;
1391 
1392  if (ReverseBytesSupported(value_size_in_bytes < 4 ? 4
1393  : value_size_in_bytes)) {
1394  switch (value_size_in_bytes) {
1395  case 2:
1396  result = __ Word32ReverseBytes(__ Word32ShiftLeft(value, 16));
1397  break;
1398  case 4:
1399  result = __ Word32ReverseBytes(value);
1400  break;
1401  case 8:
1402  result = __ Word64ReverseBytes(value);
1403  break;
1404  case 16:
1405  result = __ Simd128ReverseBytes(value);
1406  break;
1407  default:
1408  UNREACHABLE();
1409  }
1410  } else {
1411  for (i = 0, shift_count = value_size_in_bits - 8;
1412  i < value_size_in_bits / 2; i += 8, shift_count -= 16) {
1413  OpIndex shift_lower;
1414  OpIndex shift_higher;
1415  OpIndex lower_byte;
1416  OpIndex higher_byte;
1417 
1418  DCHECK_LT(0, shift_count);
1419  DCHECK_EQ(0, (shift_count + 8) % 16);
1420 
1421  if (value_size_in_bits > 32) {
1422  shift_lower = __ Word64ShiftLeft(value, shift_count);
1423  shift_higher = __ Word64ShiftRightLogical(value, shift_count);
1424  lower_byte = __ Word64BitwiseAnd(shift_lower,
1425  static_cast<uint64_t>(0xFF)
1426  << (value_size_in_bits - 8 - i));
1427  higher_byte = __ Word64BitwiseAnd(shift_higher,
1428  static_cast<uint64_t>(0xFF) << i);
1429  result = __ Word64BitwiseOr(result, lower_byte);
1430  result = __ Word64BitwiseOr(result, higher_byte);
1431  } else {
1432  shift_lower = __ Word32ShiftLeft(value, shift_count);
1433  shift_higher = __ Word32ShiftRightLogical(value, shift_count);
1434  lower_byte = __ Word32BitwiseAnd(shift_lower,
1435  static_cast<uint32_t>(0xFF)
1436  << (value_size_in_bits - 8 - i));
1437  higher_byte = __ Word32BitwiseAnd(shift_higher,
1438  static_cast<uint32_t>(0xFF) << i);
1439  result = __ Word32BitwiseOr(result, lower_byte);
1440  result = __ Word32BitwiseOr(result, higher_byte);
1441  }
1442  }
1443  }
1444 
1445  if (is_float) {
1446  switch (memtype.representation()) {
1447  case MachineRepresentation::kFloat64:
1448  result = __ BitcastWord64ToFloat64(result);
1449  break;
1450  case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32:
1451  result = __ BitcastWord32ToFloat32(result);
1452  break;
1453  default:
1454  UNREACHABLE();
1455  }
1456  }
1457 
1458  // We need to sign or zero extend the value.
1459  // Values with size >= 32-bits may need to be sign/zero extended after
1460  // calling this function.
1461  if (value_size_in_bits < 32) {
1462  DCHECK(!is_float);
1463  int shift_bit_count = 32 - value_size_in_bits;
1464  result = __ Word32ShiftLeft(result, shift_bit_count);
1465  if (memtype.IsSigned()) {
1466  result =
1467  __ Word32ShiftRightArithmeticShiftOutZeros(result, shift_bit_count);
1468  } else {
1469  result = __ Word32ShiftRightLogical(result, shift_bit_count);
1470  }
1471  }
1472 
1473  return result;
1474  }
1475 
1476  void LoadMem(FullDecoder* decoder, LoadType type,
1477  const MemoryAccessImmediate& imm, const Value& index,
1478  Value* result) {
1479  bool needs_f16_to_f32_conv = false;
1480  if (type.value() == LoadType::kF32LoadF16 &&
1481  !SupportedOperations::float16()) {
1482  needs_f16_to_f32_conv = true;
1483  type = LoadType::kI32Load16U;
1484  }
1485  MemoryRepresentation repr =
1486  MemoryRepresentation::FromMachineType(type.mem_type());
1487 
1488  auto [final_index, strategy] =
1489  BoundsCheckMem(imm.memory, repr, index.op, imm.offset,
1490  compiler::EnforceBoundsCheck::kCanOmitBoundsCheck,
1491  compiler::AlignmentCheck::kNo);
1492 
1493  V<WordPtr> mem_start = MemStart(imm.memory->index);
1494 
1495  LoadOp::Kind load_kind = GetMemoryAccessKind(repr, strategy);
1496 
1497  const bool offset_in_int_range =
1498  imm.offset <= std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max();
1499  OpIndex base =
1500  offset_in_int_range ? mem_start : __ WordPtrAdd(mem_start, imm.offset);
1501  int32_t offset = offset_in_int_range ? static_cast<int32_t>(imm.offset) : 0;
1502  OpIndex load = __ Load(base, final_index, load_kind, repr, offset);
1503 
1504 #if V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN
1505  load = BuildChangeEndiannessLoad(load, type.mem_type(), type.value_type());
1506 #endif
1507 
1508  if (type.value_type() == kWasmI64 && repr.SizeInBytes() < 8) {
1509  load = repr.IsSigned() ? __ ChangeInt32ToInt64(load)
1510  : __ ChangeUint32ToUint64(load);
1511  }
1512 
1513  if (needs_f16_to_f32_conv) {
1514  load = CallCStackSlotToStackSlot(
1515  load, ExternalReference::wasm_float16_to_float32(),
1516  MemoryRepresentation::Uint16(), MemoryRepresentation::Float32());
1517  }
1518 
1519  if (v8_flags.trace_wasm_memory) {
1520  // TODO(14259): Implement memory tracing for multiple memories.
1521  CHECK_EQ(0, imm.memory->index);
1522  TraceMemoryOperation(decoder, false, repr, final_index, imm.offset);
1523  }
1524 
1525  result->op = load;
1526  }
1527 
1528  void LoadTransform(FullDecoder* decoder, LoadType type,
1529  LoadTransformationKind transform,
1530  const MemoryAccessImmediate& imm, const Value& index,
1531  Value* result) {
1532  MemoryRepresentation repr =
1533  transform == LoadTransformationKind::kExtend
1534  ? MemoryRepresentation::Int64()
1535  : MemoryRepresentation::FromMachineType(type.mem_type());
1536 
1537  auto [final_index, strategy] =
1538  BoundsCheckMem(imm.memory, repr, index.op, imm.offset,
1539  compiler::EnforceBoundsCheck::kCanOmitBoundsCheck,
1540  compiler::AlignmentCheck::kNo);
1541 
1542  compiler::turboshaft::Simd128LoadTransformOp::LoadKind load_kind =
1543  GetMemoryAccessKind(repr, strategy);
1544 
1545  using TransformKind =
1546  compiler::turboshaft::Simd128LoadTransformOp::TransformKind;
1547 
1548  TransformKind transform_kind;
1549 
1550  if (transform == LoadTransformationKind::kExtend) {
1551  if (type.mem_type() == MachineType::Int8()) {
1552  transform_kind = TransformKind::k8x8S;
1553  } else if (type.mem_type() == MachineType::Uint8()) {
1554  transform_kind = TransformKind::k8x8U;
1555  } else if (type.mem_type() == MachineType::Int16()) {
1556  transform_kind = TransformKind::k16x4S;
1557  } else if (type.mem_type() == MachineType::Uint16()) {
1558  transform_kind = TransformKind::k16x4U;
1559  } else if (type.mem_type() == MachineType::Int32()) {
1560  transform_kind = TransformKind::k32x2S;
1561  } else if (type.mem_type() == MachineType::Uint32()) {
1562  transform_kind = TransformKind::k32x2U;
1563  } else {
1564  UNREACHABLE();
1565  }
1566  } else if (transform == LoadTransformationKind::kSplat) {
1567  if (type.mem_type() == MachineType::Int8()) {
1568  transform_kind = TransformKind::k8Splat;
1569  } else if (type.mem_type() == MachineType::Int16()) {
1570  transform_kind = TransformKind::k16Splat;
1571  } else if (type.mem_type() == MachineType::Int32()) {
1572  transform_kind = TransformKind::k32Splat;
1573  } else if (type.mem_type() == MachineType::Int64()) {
1574  transform_kind = TransformKind::k64Splat;
1575  } else {
1576  UNREACHABLE();
1577  }
1578  } else {
1579  if (type.mem_type() == MachineType::Int32()) {
1580  transform_kind = TransformKind::k32Zero;
1581  } else if (type.mem_type() == MachineType::Int64()) {
1582  transform_kind = TransformKind::k64Zero;
1583  } else {
1584  UNREACHABLE();
1585  }
1586  }
1587 
1588  V<compiler::turboshaft::Simd128> load = __ Simd128LoadTransform(
1589  __ WordPtrAdd(MemStart(imm.mem_index), imm.offset), final_index,
1590  load_kind, transform_kind, 0);
1591 
1592  if (v8_flags.trace_wasm_memory) {
1593  TraceMemoryOperation(decoder, false, repr, final_index, imm.offset);
1594  }
1595 
1596  result->op = load;
1597  }
1598 
1599  void LoadLane(FullDecoder* decoder, LoadType type, const Value& value,
1600  const Value& index, const MemoryAccessImmediate& imm,
1601  const uint8_t laneidx, Value* result) {
1602  using compiler::turboshaft::Simd128LaneMemoryOp;
1603 
1604  MemoryRepresentation repr =
1605  MemoryRepresentation::FromMachineType(type.mem_type());
1606 
1607  auto [final_index, strategy] =
1608  BoundsCheckMem(imm.memory, repr, index.op, imm.offset,
1609  compiler::EnforceBoundsCheck::kCanOmitBoundsCheck,
1610  compiler::AlignmentCheck::kNo);
1611  Simd128LaneMemoryOp::Kind kind = GetMemoryAccessKind(repr, strategy);
1612 
1613  Simd128LaneMemoryOp::LaneKind lane_kind;
1614 
1615  switch (repr) {
1616  case MemoryRepresentation::Int8():
1617  lane_kind = Simd128LaneMemoryOp::LaneKind::k8;
1618  break;
1619  case MemoryRepresentation::Int16():
1620  lane_kind = Simd128LaneMemoryOp::LaneKind::k16;
1621  break;
1622  case MemoryRepresentation::Int32():
1623  lane_kind = Simd128LaneMemoryOp::LaneKind::k32;
1624  break;
1625  case MemoryRepresentation::Int64():
1626  lane_kind = Simd128LaneMemoryOp::LaneKind::k64;
1627  break;
1628  default:
1629  UNREACHABLE();
1630  }
1631 
1632  // TODO(14108): If `offset` is in int range, use it as static offset, or
1633  // consider using a larger type as offset.
1634  OpIndex load = __ Simd128LaneMemory(
1635  __ WordPtrAdd(MemStart(imm.mem_index), imm.offset), final_index,
1636  value.op, Simd128LaneMemoryOp::Mode::kLoad, kind, lane_kind, laneidx,
1637  0);
1638 
1639  if (v8_flags.trace_wasm_memory) {
1640  TraceMemoryOperation(decoder, false, repr, final_index, imm.offset);
1641  }
1642 
1643  result->op = load;
1644  }
1645 
1646  void StoreMem(FullDecoder* decoder, StoreType type,
1647  const MemoryAccessImmediate& imm, const Value& index,
1648  const Value& value) {
1649  bool needs_f32_to_f16_conv = false;
1650  if (type.value() == StoreType::kF32StoreF16 &&
1651  !SupportedOperations::float16()) {
1652  needs_f32_to_f16_conv = true;
1653  type = StoreType::kI32Store16;
1654  }
1655  MemoryRepresentation repr =
1656  MemoryRepresentation::FromMachineRepresentation(type.mem_rep());
1657 
1658  compiler::EnforceBoundsCheck enforce_bounds_check =
1659  (wasm::kPartialOOBWritesAreNoops || type.size() == 1)
1660  ? compiler::EnforceBoundsCheck::kCanOmitBoundsCheck
1661  : compiler::EnforceBoundsCheck::kNeedsBoundsCheck;
1662 
1663  auto [final_index, strategy] =
1664  BoundsCheckMem(imm.memory, repr, index.op, imm.offset,
1665  enforce_bounds_check, compiler::AlignmentCheck::kNo);
1666 
1667  V<WordPtr> mem_start = MemStart(imm.memory->index);
1668 
1669  StoreOp::Kind store_kind = GetMemoryAccessKind(repr, strategy);
1670 
1671  OpIndex store_value = value.op;
1672  if (value.type == kWasmI64 && repr.SizeInBytes() <= 4) {
1673  store_value = __ TruncateWord64ToWord32(store_value);
1674  }
1675  if (needs_f32_to_f16_conv) {
1676  store_value = CallCStackSlotToStackSlot(
1677  store_value, ExternalReference::wasm_float32_to_float16(),
1678  MemoryRepresentation::Float32(), MemoryRepresentation::Int16());
1679  }
1680 
1681 #if defined(V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN)
1682  store_value = BuildChangeEndiannessStore(store_value, type.mem_rep(),
1683  type.value_type());
1684 #endif
1685  const bool offset_in_int_range =
1686  imm.offset <= std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max();
1687  OpIndex base =
1688  offset_in_int_range ? mem_start : __ WordPtrAdd(mem_start, imm.offset);
1689  int32_t offset = offset_in_int_range ? static_cast<int32_t>(imm.offset) : 0;
1690  __ Store(base, final_index, store_value, store_kind, repr,
1691  compiler::kNoWriteBarrier, offset);
1692 
1693  if (v8_flags.trace_wasm_memory) {
1694  // TODO(14259): Implement memory tracing for multiple memories.
1695  CHECK_EQ(0, imm.memory->index);
1696  TraceMemoryOperation(decoder, true, repr, final_index, imm.offset);
1697  }
1698  }
1699 
1700  void StoreLane(FullDecoder* decoder, StoreType type,
1701  const MemoryAccessImmediate& imm, const Value& index,
1702  const Value& value, const uint8_t laneidx) {
1703  using compiler::turboshaft::Simd128LaneMemoryOp;
1704 
1705  MemoryRepresentation repr =
1706  MemoryRepresentation::FromMachineRepresentation(type.mem_rep());
1707 
1708  compiler::EnforceBoundsCheck enforce_bounds_check =
1709  (wasm::kPartialOOBWritesAreNoops || type.size() == 1)
1710  ? compiler::EnforceBoundsCheck::kCanOmitBoundsCheck
1711  : compiler::EnforceBoundsCheck::kNeedsBoundsCheck;
1712 
1713  auto [final_index, strategy] =
1714  BoundsCheckMem(imm.memory, repr, index.op, imm.offset,
1715  enforce_bounds_check, compiler::AlignmentCheck::kNo);
1716  Simd128LaneMemoryOp::Kind kind = GetMemoryAccessKind(repr, strategy);
1717 
1718  Simd128LaneMemoryOp::LaneKind lane_kind;
1719 
1720  switch (repr) {
1721  // TODO(manoskouk): Why use unsigned representations here as opposed to
1722  // LoadLane?
1723  case MemoryRepresentation::Uint8():
1724  lane_kind = Simd128LaneMemoryOp::LaneKind::k8;
1725  break;
1726  case MemoryRepresentation::Uint16():
1727  lane_kind = Simd128LaneMemoryOp::LaneKind::k16;
1728  break;
1729  case MemoryRepresentation::Uint32():
1730  lane_kind = Simd128LaneMemoryOp::LaneKind::k32;
1731  break;
1732  case MemoryRepresentation::Uint64():
1733  lane_kind = Simd128LaneMemoryOp::LaneKind::k64;
1734  break;
1735  default:
1736  UNREACHABLE();
1737  }
1738 
1739  // TODO(14108): If `offset` is in int range, use it as static offset, or
1740  // consider using a larger type as offset.
1741  __ Simd128LaneMemory(__ WordPtrAdd(MemStart(imm.mem_index), imm.offset),
1742  final_index, value.op,
1743  Simd128LaneMemoryOp::Mode::kStore, kind, lane_kind,
1744  laneidx, 0);
1745 
1746  if (v8_flags.trace_wasm_memory) {
1747  TraceMemoryOperation(decoder, true, repr, final_index, imm.offset);
1748  }
1749  }
1750 
1751  void CurrentMemoryPages(FullDecoder* decoder, const MemoryIndexImmediate& imm,
1752  Value* result) {
1753  V<WordPtr> result_wordptr =
1754  __ WordPtrShiftRightArithmetic(MemSize(imm.index), kWasmPageSizeLog2);
1755  // In the 32-bit case, truncation happens implicitly.
1756  if (imm.memory->is_memory64()) {
1757  result->op = __ ChangeIntPtrToInt64(result_wordptr);
1758  } else {
1759  result->op = __ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(result_wordptr);
1760  }
1761  }
1762 
1763  void MemoryGrow(FullDecoder* decoder, const MemoryIndexImmediate& imm,
1764  const Value& value, Value* result) {
1765  if (!imm.memory->is_memory64()) {
1766  result->op =
1767  CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmMemoryGrow>(
1768  decoder, {__ Word32Constant(imm.index), value.op});
1769  } else {
1770  Label<Word64> done(&asm_);
1771 
1772  IF (LIKELY(__ Uint64LessThanOrEqual(
1773  value.op, __ Word64Constant(static_cast<int64_t>(kMaxInt))))) {
1774  GOTO(done, __ ChangeInt32ToInt64(CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<
1775  BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmMemoryGrow>(
1776  decoder, {__ Word32Constant(imm.index),
1777  __ TruncateWord64ToWord32(value.op)})));
1778  } ELSE {
1779  GOTO(done, __ Word64Constant(int64_t{-1}));
1780  }
1781 
1782  BIND(done, result_64);
1783 
1784  result->op = result_64;
1785  }
1786  instance_cache_.ReloadCachedMemory();
1787  }

1810  V<Word32> GetStringIndexOf(FullDecoder* decoder, V<String> string,
1811  V<String> search, V<Word32> start) {
1812  // Clamp the start index.
1813  Label<Word32> clamped_start_label(&asm_);
1814  GOTO_IF(__ Int32LessThan(start, 0), clamped_start_label,
1815  __ Word32Constant(0));
1816  V<Word32> length = __ template LoadField<Word32>(
1817  string, compiler::AccessBuilder::ForStringLength());
1818  GOTO_IF(__ Int32LessThan(start, length), clamped_start_label, start);
1819  GOTO(clamped_start_label, length);
1820  BIND(clamped_start_label, clamped_start);
1821  start = clamped_start;
1822 
1823  // This can't overflow because we've clamped `start` above.
1824  V<Smi> start_smi = __ TagSmi(start);
1825  BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlag(decoder->zone(), false);
1826 
1827  V<Smi> result_value =
1828  CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmStringIndexOf>(
1829  decoder, {string, search, start_smi});
1830  BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlag(decoder->zone(), true);
1831 
1832  return __ UntagSmi(result_value);
1833  }

1883  V<WordPtr> right, DataViewOp op_type) {

1885  ThrowDataViewDetachedError(decoder, op_type);
1886  }

1892  __ ArrayBufferIsDetached(V<JSArrayBufferView>::Cast(dataview)))) {
1893  ThrowDataViewDetachedError(decoder, op_type);
1894  }

1904  // Converts a Smi or HeapNumber to an intptr. The input is not validated.
1905  V<WordPtr> ChangeTaggedNumberToIntPtr(V<Object> tagged) {
1906  Label<> smi_label(&asm_);
1907  Label<> heapnumber_label(&asm_);
1908  Label<WordPtr> done_label(&asm_);
1909 
1910  GOTO_IF(LIKELY(__ IsSmi(tagged)), smi_label);
1911  GOTO(heapnumber_label);
1912 
1913  BIND(smi_label);
1914  V<WordPtr> smi_length =
1915  __ ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(__ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(tagged)));
1916  GOTO(done_label, smi_length);
1917 
1918  BIND(heapnumber_label);
1919  V<Float64> float_value = __ template LoadField<Float64>(
1920  tagged, AccessBuilder::ForHeapNumberValue());
1921  if constexpr (Is64()) {
1922  DCHECK_EQ(WordPtr::bits, Word64::bits);
1923  GOTO(done_label,
1924  V<WordPtr>::Cast(
1925  __ TruncateFloat64ToInt64OverflowUndefined(float_value)));
1926  } else {
1927  GOTO(done_label,
1928  __ ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(
1929  __ TruncateFloat64ToInt32OverflowUndefined(float_value)));
1930  }
1931 
1932  BIND(done_label, length);
1933  return length;
1934  }
1935 
1936  // An `ArrayBuffer` can be resizable, i.e. it can shrink or grow.
1937  // A `SharedArrayBuffer` can be growable, i.e. it can only grow. A `DataView`
1938  // can be length-tracking or non-legth-tracking . A length-tracking `DataView`
1939  // is tracking the length of the underlying buffer, i.e. it doesn't have a
1940  // `byteLength` specified, which means that the length of the `DataView` is
1941  // the length (or remaining length if `byteOffset != 0`) of the underlying
1942  // array buffer. On the other hand, a non-length-tracking `DataView` has a
1943  // `byteLength`.
1944  // Depending on whether the buffer is resizable or growable and the `DataView`
1945  // is length-tracking or non-length-tracking, getting the byte length has to
1946  // be handled differently.
1947  V<WordPtr> GetDataViewByteLength(FullDecoder* decoder, V<Object> dataview,
1948  V<WordPtr> offset, DataViewOp op_type) {
1949  Label<WordPtr> done_label(&asm_);
1950  Label<> type_error_label(&asm_);
1951 
1952  GOTO_IF(UNLIKELY(__ IsSmi(dataview)), type_error_label);
1953 
1954  // Case 1):
1955  // - non-resizable ArrayBuffers, length-tracking and non-length-tracking
1956  // - non-growable SharedArrayBuffers, length-tracking and non-length-tr.
1957  // - growable SharedArrayBuffers, non-length-tracking
1958  IF (LIKELY(__ HasInstanceType(dataview, InstanceType::JS_DATA_VIEW_TYPE))) {
1959  if (op_type != DataViewOp::kByteLength) {
1960  DataViewRangeCheck(decoder, offset, __ IntPtrConstant(0), op_type);
1961  }
1962  DataViewDetachedBufferCheck(decoder, dataview, op_type);
1963  V<WordPtr> view_byte_length = __ LoadField<WordPtr>(
1964  dataview, AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewByteLength());
1965  GOTO(done_label, view_byte_length);
1966  }
1967 
1968  // Case 2):
1969  // - resizable ArrayBuffers, length-tracking and non-length-tracking
1970  // - growable SharedArrayBuffers, length-tracking
1971  GOTO_IF_NOT(LIKELY(__ HasInstanceType(
1972  dataview, InstanceType::JS_RAB_GSAB_DATA_VIEW_TYPE)),
1973  type_error_label);
1974  if (op_type != DataViewOp::kByteLength) {
1975  DataViewRangeCheck(decoder, offset, __ IntPtrConstant(0), op_type);
1976  }
1977  DataViewDetachedBufferCheck(decoder, dataview, op_type);
1978 
1979  V<Word32> bit_field = __ LoadField<Word32>(
1980  dataview, AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewBitField());
1981  V<Word32> length_tracking = __ Word32BitwiseAnd(
1982  bit_field, JSArrayBufferView::IsLengthTrackingBit::kMask);
1983  V<Word32> backed_by_rab_bit = __ Word32BitwiseAnd(
1984  bit_field, JSArrayBufferView::IsBackedByRabBit::kMask);
1985 
1986  V<Object> buffer = __ LoadField<Object>(
1987  dataview, compiler::AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewBuffer());
1988  V<WordPtr> buffer_byte_length = __ LoadField<WordPtr>(
1989  buffer, AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferByteLength());
1990  V<WordPtr> view_byte_offset = __ LoadField<WordPtr>(
1991  dataview, AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewByteOffset());
1992 
1993  // The final length for each case in Case 2) is calculated differently.
1994  // Case: resizable ArrayBuffers, LT and non-LT.
1995  IF (backed_by_rab_bit) {
1996  // DataViews with resizable ArrayBuffers can go out of bounds.
1997  IF (length_tracking) {
1998  ScopedVar<WordPtr> final_length(this, 0);
1999  IF (LIKELY(__ UintPtrLessThanOrEqual(view_byte_offset,
2000  buffer_byte_length))) {
2001  final_length = __ WordPtrSub(buffer_byte_length, view_byte_offset);
2002  }
2003  DataViewBoundsCheck(decoder, buffer_byte_length, view_byte_offset,
2004  op_type);
2005  GOTO(done_label, final_length);
2006  } ELSE {
2007  V<WordPtr> view_byte_length = __ LoadField<WordPtr>(
2008  dataview, AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewByteLength());
2009  DataViewBoundsCheck(decoder, buffer_byte_length,
2010  __ WordPtrAdd(view_byte_offset, view_byte_length),
2011  op_type);
2012 
2013  GOTO(done_label, view_byte_length);
2014  }
2015  }
2016  // Case: growable SharedArrayBuffers, LT.
2017  ELSE {
2018  V<Object> gsab_length_tagged = CallRuntime(
2019  decoder->zone(), Runtime::kGrowableSharedArrayBufferByteLength,
2020  {buffer}, __ NoContextConstant());
2021  V<WordPtr> gsab_length = ChangeTaggedNumberToIntPtr(gsab_length_tagged);
2022  ScopedVar<WordPtr> gsab_buffer_byte_length(this, 0);
2023  IF (LIKELY(__ UintPtrLessThanOrEqual(view_byte_offset, gsab_length))) {
2024  gsab_buffer_byte_length = __ WordPtrSub(gsab_length, view_byte_offset);
2025  }
2026  GOTO(done_label, gsab_buffer_byte_length);
2027  }
2028  __ Unreachable();
2029 
2030  BIND(type_error_label);
2031  ThrowDataViewTypeError(decoder, dataview, op_type);
2032 
2033  BIND(done_label, final_view_byte_length);
2034  return final_view_byte_length;
2035  }
2036 
2037  V<WordPtr> GetDataViewDataPtr(FullDecoder* decoder, V<Object> dataview,
2038  V<WordPtr> offset, DataViewOp op_type) {
2039  V<WordPtr> view_byte_length =
2040  GetDataViewByteLength(decoder, dataview, offset, op_type);
2041  V<WordPtr> view_byte_length_minus_size =
2042  __ WordPtrSub(view_byte_length, GetTypeSize(op_type));
2043  DataViewRangeCheck(decoder, view_byte_length_minus_size, offset, op_type);
2044  return __ LoadField<WordPtr>(
2045  dataview, compiler::AccessBuilder::ForJSDataViewDataPointer());
2046  }
2047 
2048  OpIndex DataViewGetter(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value args[],
2049  DataViewOp op_type) {
2050  V<Object> dataview = args[0].op;
2051  V<WordPtr> offset = __ ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(args[1].op);
2052  V<Word32> is_little_endian =
2053  (op_type == DataViewOp::kGetInt8 || op_type == DataViewOp::kGetUint8)
2054  ? __ Word32Constant(1)
2055  : args[2].op;
2056 
2057  V<WordPtr> data_ptr =
2058  GetDataViewDataPtr(decoder, dataview, offset, op_type);
2059  return __ LoadDataViewElement(dataview, data_ptr, offset, is_little_endian,
2060  GetExternalArrayType(op_type));
2061  }
2062 
2063  void DataViewSetter(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value args[],
2064  DataViewOp op_type) {
2065  V<Object> dataview = args[0].op;
2066  V<WordPtr> offset = __ ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(args[1].op);
2067  V<Word32> value = args[2].op;
2068  V<Word32> is_little_endian =
2069  (op_type == DataViewOp::kSetInt8 || op_type == DataViewOp::kSetUint8)
2070  ? __ Word32Constant(1)
2071  : args[3].op;
2072 
2073  V<WordPtr> data_ptr =
2074  GetDataViewDataPtr(decoder, dataview, offset, op_type);
2075  __ StoreDataViewElement(dataview, data_ptr, offset, value, is_little_endian,
2076  GetExternalArrayType(op_type));
2077  }

2079  // Adds a wasm type annotation to the graph and replaces any extern type with
2080  // the extern string type.
2081  template <typename T>
2082  V<T> AnnotateAsString(V<T> value, wasm::ValueType type) {
2083  DCHECK(type.is_reference_to(HeapType::kString) ||
2084  type.is_reference_to(HeapType::kExternString) ||
2085  type.is_reference_to(HeapType::kExtern));
2086  if (type.is_reference_to(HeapType::kExtern)) {
2087  type = ValueType::RefMaybeNull(kWasmRefExternString, type.nullability());
2088  }
2089  return __ AnnotateWasmType(value, type);
2090  }
