2092  void WellKnown_FastApi(FullDecoder* decoder, const CallFunctionImmediate& imm,
2093  const Value args[], Value returns[]) {
2094  uint32_t func_index = imm.index;
2095  V<Object> receiver = args[0].op;
2096  // TODO(14616): Fix this.
2097  V<FixedArray> imports_array = LOAD_IMMUTABLE_INSTANCE_FIELD(
2098  trusted_instance_data(false), WellKnownImports,
2099  MemoryRepresentation::TaggedPointer());
2100  V<Object> data = __ LoadFixedArrayElement(imports_array, func_index);
2101  V<Object> cached_map = __ Load(data, LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase(),
2102  MemoryRepresentation::TaggedPointer(),
2103  WasmFastApiCallData::kCachedMapOffset);
2104 
2105  Label<> if_equal_maps(&asm_);
2106  Label<> if_unknown_receiver(&asm_);
2107  GOTO_IF(__ IsSmi(receiver), if_unknown_receiver);
2108 
2109  V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(V<Object>::Cast(receiver));
2110 
2111  // Clear the weak bit.
2112  cached_map = __ BitcastWordPtrToTagged(__ WordPtrBitwiseAnd(
2113  __ BitcastTaggedToWordPtr(cached_map), ~kWeakHeapObjectMask));
2114  GOTO_IF(__ TaggedEqual(map, cached_map), if_equal_maps);
2115  GOTO(if_unknown_receiver);
2116 
2117  BIND(if_unknown_receiver);
2118  V<NativeContext> context = instance_cache_.native_context();
2119  CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<
2120  BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmFastApiCallTypeCheckAndUpdateIC>(
2121  decoder, context, {data, receiver});
2122  GOTO(if_equal_maps);
2123 
2124  BIND(if_equal_maps);
2125  OpIndex receiver_handle = __ AdaptLocalArgument(receiver);
2126 
2127  const wasm::FunctionSig* sig = decoder->module_->functions[func_index].sig;
2128  size_t param_count = sig->parameter_count();
2129  DCHECK_LE(sig->return_count(), 1);
2130 
2131  const MachineSignature* callback_sig =
2132  env_->fast_api_signatures[func_index];
2133  // All normal parameters + the options as additional parameter at the end.
2134  MachineSignature::Builder builder(decoder->zone(), sig->return_count(),
2135  param_count + 1);
2136  if (sig->return_count()) {
2137  builder.AddReturn(callback_sig->GetReturn());
2138  }
2139  // The first parameter is the receiver. Because of the fake handle on the
2140  // stack the type is `Pointer`.
2141  builder.AddParam(MachineType::Pointer());
2142 
2143  for (size_t i = 0; i < callback_sig->parameter_count(); ++i) {
2144  builder.AddParam(callback_sig->GetParam(i));
2145  }
2146  // Options object.
2147  builder.AddParam(MachineType::Pointer());
2148 
2149  base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 16> inputs(param_count + 1);
2150 
2151  inputs[0] = receiver_handle;
2152 
2153  Label<> value_out_of_range(&asm_);
2154  for (size_t i = 1; i < param_count; ++i) {
2155  if (sig->GetParam(i).is_reference()) {
2156  inputs[i] = __ AdaptLocalArgument(args[i].op);
2157  } else if (callback_sig->GetParam(i - 1).representation() ==
2158  MachineRepresentation::kWord64) {
2159  if (sig->GetParam(i) == kWasmI64) {
2160  // If we already have an I64, then no conversion is needed neither for
2161  // int64 nor uint64.
2162  inputs[i] = args[i].op;
2163  } else if (callback_sig->GetParam(i - 1) == MachineType::Int64()) {
2164  if (sig->GetParam(i) == kWasmF64) {
2165  V<Tuple<Word64, Word32>> truncate =
2166  __ TryTruncateFloat64ToInt64(args[i].op);
2167  inputs[i] = __ template Projection<0>(truncate);
2168  GOTO_IF(UNLIKELY(
2169  __ Word32Equal(__ template Projection<1>(truncate), 0)),
2170  value_out_of_range);
2171  } else if (sig->GetParam(i) == kWasmI32) {
2172  inputs[i] = __ ChangeInt32ToInt64(args[i].op);
2173  } else {
2174  // TODO(ahaas): Handle values that are out of range of int64.
2175  CHECK_EQ(sig->GetParam(i), kWasmF32);
2176  V<Tuple<Word64, Word32>> truncate =
2177  __ TryTruncateFloat32ToInt64(args[i].op);
2178  inputs[i] = __ template Projection<0>(truncate);
2179  GOTO_IF(UNLIKELY(
2180  __ Word32Equal(__ template Projection<1>(truncate), 0)),
2181  value_out_of_range);
2182  }
2183  } else if (callback_sig->GetParam(i - 1) == MachineType::Uint64()) {
2184  if (sig->GetParam(i) == kWasmF64) {
2185  V<Tuple<Word64, Word32>> truncate =
2186  __ TryTruncateFloat64ToUint64(args[i].op);
2187  inputs[i] = __ template Projection<0>(truncate);
2188  GOTO_IF(UNLIKELY(
2189  __ Word32Equal(__ template Projection<1>(truncate), 0)),
2190  value_out_of_range);
2191  } else if (sig->GetParam(i) == kWasmI32) {
2192  inputs[i] = __ ChangeUint32ToUint64(args[i].op);
2193  } else {
2194  // TODO(ahaas): Handle values that are out of range of int64.
2195  CHECK_EQ(sig->GetParam(i), kWasmF32);
2196  V<Tuple<Word64, Word32>> truncate =
2197  __ TryTruncateFloat32ToUint64(args[i].op);
2198  inputs[i] = __ template Projection<0>(truncate);
2199  GOTO_IF(UNLIKELY(
2200  __ Word32Equal(__ template Projection<1>(truncate), 0)),
2201  value_out_of_range);
2202  }
2203  }
2204  } else {
2205  inputs[i] = args[i].op;
2206  }
2207  }
2208 
2209  OpIndex options_object;
2210  {
2211  const int kAlign = alignof(v8::FastApiCallbackOptions);
2212  const int kSize = sizeof(v8::FastApiCallbackOptions);
2213 
2214  options_object = __ StackSlot(kSize, kAlign);
2215 
2216  static_assert(
2217  sizeof(v8::FastApiCallbackOptions::isolate) == sizeof(intptr_t),
2218  "We expected 'isolate' to be pointer sized, but it is not.");
2219  __ StoreOffHeap(options_object,
2220  __ IsolateField(IsolateFieldId::kIsolateAddress),
2221  MemoryRepresentation::UintPtr(),
2222  offsetof(v8::FastApiCallbackOptions, isolate));
2223 
2224  V<Object> callback_data =
2225  __ Load(data, LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase(),
2226  MemoryRepresentation::TaggedPointer(),
2227  WasmFastApiCallData::kCallbackDataOffset);
2228  V<WordPtr> data_argument_to_pass = __ AdaptLocalArgument(callback_data);
2229 
2230  __ StoreOffHeap(options_object, data_argument_to_pass,
2231  MemoryRepresentation::UintPtr(),
2232  offsetof(v8::FastApiCallbackOptions, data));
2233  }
2234 
2235  inputs[param_count] = options_object;
2236 
2237  const CallDescriptor* call_descriptor =
2238  compiler::Linkage::GetSimplifiedCDescriptor(__ graph_zone(),
2239  builder.Get());
2240  const TSCallDescriptor* ts_call_descriptor = TSCallDescriptor::Create(
2241  call_descriptor, compiler::CanThrow::kNo,
2242  compiler::LazyDeoptOnThrow::kNo, __ graph_zone());
2243  OpIndex target_address = __ ExternalConstant(ExternalReference::Create(
2244  env_->fast_api_targets[func_index].load(std::memory_order_relaxed),
2245  ExternalReference::FAST_C_CALL));
2246 
2247  V<Context> native_context = instance_cache_.native_context();
2248 
2249  __ Store(__ LoadRootRegister(),
2250  __ BitcastHeapObjectToWordPtr(native_context),
2251  StoreOp::Kind::RawAligned(), MemoryRepresentation::UintPtr(),
2252  compiler::kNoWriteBarrier, Isolate::context_offset());
2253  BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlag(__ graph_zone(), false);
2254  auto [old_sp, old_limit] = BuildSwitchToTheCentralStackIfNeeded();
2255  OpIndex ret_val = __ Call(target_address, OpIndex::Invalid(),
2256  base::VectorOf(inputs), ts_call_descriptor);
2257  BuildSwitchBackFromCentralStack(old_sp, old_limit);
2258 
2259 #if DEBUG
2260  // Reset the context again after the call, to make sure nobody is using the
2261  // leftover context in the isolate.
2262  __ Store(__ LoadRootRegister(), __ WordPtrConstant(Context::kNoContext),
2263  StoreOp::Kind::RawAligned(), MemoryRepresentation::UintPtr(),
2264  compiler::kNoWriteBarrier, Isolate::context_offset());
2265 #endif
2266 
2267  V<Object> exception = __ Load(
2268  __ LoadRootRegister(), LoadOp::Kind::RawAligned(),
2269  MemoryRepresentation::UintPtr(), IsolateData::exception_offset());
2270 
2271  IF_NOT (LIKELY(
2272  __ TaggedEqual(exception, LOAD_ROOT(TheHoleValue)))) {
2273  CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<
2274  BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmPropagateException>(
2275  decoder, {}, CheckForException::kCatchInThisFrame);
2276  }
2277  BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlag(__ graph_zone(), true);
2278 
2279  if (callback_sig->return_count() > 0) {
2280  if (callback_sig->GetReturn() == MachineType::Bool()) {
2281  ret_val = __ WordBitwiseAnd(ret_val, __ Word32Constant(0xff),
2282  WordRepresentation::Word32());
2283  } else if (callback_sig->GetReturn() == MachineType::Int64()) {
2284  if (sig->GetReturn() == kWasmF64) {
2285  ret_val = __ ChangeInt64ToFloat64(ret_val);
2286  } else if (sig->GetReturn() == kWasmI32) {
2287  ret_val = __ TruncateWord64ToWord32(ret_val);
2288  } else if (sig->GetReturn() == kWasmF32) {
2289  ret_val = __ ChangeInt64ToFloat32(ret_val);
2290  }
2291  } else if (callback_sig->GetReturn() == MachineType::Uint64()) {
2292  if (sig->GetReturn() == kWasmF64) {
2293  ret_val = __ ChangeUint64ToFloat64(ret_val);
2294  } else if (sig->GetReturn() == kWasmI32) {
2295  ret_val = __ TruncateWord64ToWord32(ret_val);
2296  } else if (sig->GetReturn() == kWasmF32) {
2297  ret_val = __ ChangeUint64ToFloat32(ret_val);
2298  }
2299  }
2300  }
2301  Label<> done(&asm_);
2302  GOTO(done);
2303  BIND(value_out_of_range);
2304  auto [target, implicit_arg] =
2305  BuildImportedFunctionTargetAndImplicitArg(decoder, imm.index);
2306  BuildWasmCall(decoder, imm.sig, target, implicit_arg, args, returns,
2307  compiler::kWasmIndirectFunction);
2308  __ Unreachable();
2309  BIND(done);
2310  if (sig->return_count()) {
2311  returns[0].op = ret_val;
2312  }
2313  }
2314 
2315  bool HandleWellKnownImport(FullDecoder* decoder,
2316  const CallFunctionImmediate& imm,
2317  const Value args[], Value returns[]) {
2318  uint32_t index = imm.index;
2319  if (!decoder->module_) return false; // Only needed for tests.
2320  const WellKnownImportsList& well_known_imports =
2321  decoder->module_->type_feedback.well_known_imports;
2322  using WKI = WellKnownImport;
2323  WKI imported_op = well_known_imports.get(index);
2324  OpIndex result;
2325  switch (imported_op) {
2326  case WKI::kUninstantiated:
2327  case WKI::kGeneric:
2328  case WKI::kLinkError:
2329  return false;
2330 
2331  // JS String Builtins proposal.
2332  case WKI::kStringCast: {
2333  result = ExternRefToString(args[0]);
2334  decoder->detected_->add_imported_strings();
2335  break;
2336  }
2337  case WKI::kStringTest: {
2338  result = IsExternRefString(args[0]);
2339  decoder->detected_->add_imported_strings();
2340  break;
2341  }
2342  case WKI::kStringCharCodeAt: {
2343  V<String> string = ExternRefToString(args[0]);
2344  V<String> view = __ StringAsWtf16(string);
2345  // TODO(14108): Annotate `view`'s type.
2346  result = GetCodeUnitImpl(decoder, view, args[1].op);
2347  decoder->detected_->add_imported_strings();
2348  break;
2349  }
2350  case WKI::kStringCodePointAt: {
2351  V<String> string = ExternRefToString(args[0]);
2352  V<String> view = __ StringAsWtf16(string);
2353  // TODO(14108): Annotate `view`'s type.
2354  result = StringCodePointAt(decoder, view, args[1].op);
2355  decoder->detected_->add_imported_strings();
2356  break;
2357  }
2358  case WKI::kStringCompare: {
2359  V<String> a_string = ExternRefToString(args[0]);
2360  V<String> b_string = ExternRefToString(args[1]);
2361  result = __ UntagSmi(CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<
2362  BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmStringCompare>(
2363  decoder, {a_string, b_string}));
2364  decoder->detected_->add_imported_strings();
2365  break;
2366  }
2367  case WKI::kStringConcat: {
2368  V<String> head_string = ExternRefToString(args[0]);
2369  V<String> tail_string = ExternRefToString(args[1]);
2370  V<HeapObject> native_context = instance_cache_.native_context();
2371  V<String> result_value = CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<
2372  BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmStringAdd_CheckNone>(
2373  decoder, V<Context>::Cast(native_context),
2374  {head_string, tail_string});
2375  result = __ AnnotateWasmType(result_value, kWasmRefExternString);
2376  decoder->detected_->add_imported_strings();
2377  break;
2378  }
2379  case WKI::kStringEquals: {
2380  // Using nullable type guards here because this instruction needs to
2381  // handle {null} without trapping.
2382  static constexpr bool kNullSucceeds = true;
2383  V<String> a_string = ExternRefToString(args[0], kNullSucceeds);
2384  V<String> b_string = ExternRefToString(args[1], kNullSucceeds);
2385  result = StringEqImpl(decoder, a_string, b_string, kWasmExternRef,
2386  kWasmExternRef);
2387  decoder->detected_->add_imported_strings();
2388  break;
2389  }
2390  case WKI::kStringFromCharCode: {
2391  V<Word32> capped = __ Word32BitwiseAnd(args[0].op, 0xFFFF);
2392  V<String> result_value = CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<
2393  BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmStringFromCodePoint>(decoder, {capped});
2394  result = __ AnnotateWasmType(result_value, kWasmRefExternString);
2395  decoder->detected_->add_imported_strings();
2396  break;
2397  }
2398  case WKI::kStringFromCodePoint: {
2399  V<String> result_value = CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<
2400  BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmStringFromCodePoint>(decoder,
2401  {args[0].op});
2402  result = __ AnnotateWasmType(result_value, kWasmRefExternString);
2403  decoder->detected_->add_imported_strings();
2404  break;
2405  }
2406  case WKI::kStringFromWtf16Array: {
2407  V<String> result_value = CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<
2408  BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmStringNewWtf16Array>(
2409  decoder,
2410  {V<WasmArray>::Cast(NullCheck(args[0])), args[1].op, args[2].op});
2411  result = __ AnnotateWasmType(result_value, kWasmRefExternString);
2412  decoder->detected_->add_imported_strings();
2413  break;
2414  }
2415  case WKI::kStringFromUtf8Array:
2416  result = StringNewWtf8ArrayImpl(
2417  decoder, unibrow::Utf8Variant::kLossyUtf8, args[0], args[1],
2418  args[2], kWasmRefExternString);
2419  decoder->detected_->add_imported_strings();
2420  break;
2421  case WKI::kStringIntoUtf8Array: {
2422  V<String> string = ExternRefToString(args[0]);
2423  result = StringEncodeWtf8ArrayImpl(
2424  decoder, unibrow::Utf8Variant::kLossyUtf8, string,
2425  V<WasmArray>::Cast(NullCheck(args[1])), args[2].op);
2426  decoder->detected_->add_imported_strings();
2427  break;
2428  }
2429  case WKI::kStringToUtf8Array: {
2430  V<String> string = ExternRefToString(args[0]);
2431  V<WasmArray> result_value = CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<
2432  BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmStringToUtf8Array>(decoder, {string});
2433  result = __ AnnotateWasmType(result_value, returns[0].type);
2434  decoder->detected_->add_imported_strings();
2435  break;
2436  }
2437  case WKI::kStringLength: {
2438  V<Object> string = ExternRefToString(args[0]);
2439  result = __ template LoadField<Word32>(
2440  string, compiler::AccessBuilder::ForStringLength());
2441  decoder->detected_->add_imported_strings();
2442  break;
2443  }
2444  case WKI::kStringMeasureUtf8: {
2445  V<String> string = ExternRefToString(args[0]);
2446  result = StringMeasureWtf8Impl(
2447  decoder, unibrow::Utf8Variant::kLossyUtf8, string);
2448  decoder->detected_->add_imported_strings();
2449  break;
2450  }
2451  case WKI::kStringSubstring: {
2452  V<String> string = ExternRefToString(args[0]);
2453  V<String> view = __ StringAsWtf16(string);
2454  // TODO(12868): Consider annotating {view}'s type when the typing story
2455  // for string views has been settled.
2456  V<String> result_value = CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<
2457  BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmStringViewWtf16Slice>(
2458  decoder, {view, args[1].op, args[2].op});
2459  result = __ AnnotateWasmType(result_value, kWasmRefExternString);
2460  decoder->detected_->add_imported_strings();
2461  break;
2462  }
2463  case WKI::kStringToWtf16Array: {
2464  V<String> string = ExternRefToString(args[0]);
2465  result = CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<
2466  BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmStringEncodeWtf16Array>(
2467  decoder,
2468  {string, V<WasmArray>::Cast(NullCheck(args[1])), args[2].op});
2469  decoder->detected_->add_imported_strings();
2470  break;
2471  }
2472 
2473  // Other string-related imports.
2474  case WKI::kDoubleToString: {
2475  BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlag(decoder->zone(), false);
2476  V<String> result_value = CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<
2477  BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmFloat64ToString>(decoder, {args[0].op});
2478  result = AnnotateAsString(result_value, returns[0].type);
2479  BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlag(decoder->zone(), true);
2480  decoder->detected_->Add(
2481  returns[0].type.is_reference_to(wasm::HeapType::kString)
2482  ? WasmDetectedFeature::stringref
2483  : WasmDetectedFeature::imported_strings);
2484  break;
2485  }
2486  case WKI::kIntToString: {
2487  BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlag(decoder->zone(), false);
2488  V<String> result_value =
2489  CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmIntToString>(
2490  decoder, {args[0].op, args[1].op});
2491  result = AnnotateAsString(result_value, returns[0].type);
2492  BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlag(decoder->zone(), true);
2493  decoder->detected_->Add(
2494  returns[0].type.is_reference_to(wasm::HeapType::kString)
2495  ? WasmDetectedFeature::stringref
2496  : WasmDetectedFeature::imported_strings);
2497  break;
2498  }
2499  case WKI::kParseFloat: {
2500  if (args[0].type.is_nullable()) {
2501  Label<Float64> done(&asm_);
2502  GOTO_IF(__ IsNull(args[0].op, args[0].type), done,
2503  __ Float64Constant(std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN()));
2504 
2505  BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlag(decoder->zone(), false);
2506  V<Float64> not_null_res = CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<
2507  BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmStringToDouble>(decoder, {args[0].op});
2508  BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlag(decoder->zone(), true);
2509  GOTO(done, not_null_res);
2510 
2511  BIND(done, result_f64);
2512  result = result_f64;
2513  } else {
2514  BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlag(decoder->zone(), false);
2515  result = CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<
2516  BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmStringToDouble>(decoder, {args[0].op});
2517  BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlag(decoder->zone(), true);
2518  }
2519  decoder->detected_->add_stringref();
2520  break;
2521  }
2522  case WKI::kStringIndexOf: {
2523  V<String> string = args[0].op;
2524  V<String> search = args[1].op;
2525  V<Word32> start = args[2].op;
2526 
2527  // If string is null, throw.
2528  if (args[0].type.is_nullable()) {
2529  IF (__ IsNull(string, args[0].type)) {
2530  CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<
2531  BuiltinCallDescriptor::ThrowIndexOfCalledOnNull>(decoder, {});
2532  __ Unreachable();
2533  }
2534  }
2535 
2536  // If search is null, replace it with "null".
2537  if (args[1].type.is_nullable()) {
2538  Label<String> search_done_label(&asm_);
2539  GOTO_IF_NOT(__ IsNull(search, args[1].type), search_done_label,
2540  search);
2541  GOTO(search_done_label, LOAD_ROOT(null_string));
2542  BIND(search_done_label, search_value);
2543  search = search_value;
2544  }
2545 
2546  result = GetStringIndexOf(decoder, string, search, start);
2547  decoder->detected_->add_stringref();
2548  break;
2549  }
2550  case WKI::kStringIndexOfImported: {
2551  // As the `string` and `search` parameters are externrefs, we have to
2552  // make sure they are strings. To enforce this, we inline only if a
2553  // (successful) `"js-string":"cast"` was performed before.
2554  if (!(IsExplicitStringCast(args[0]) && IsExplicitStringCast(args[1]))) {
2555  return false;
2556  }
2557  V<String> string = args[0].op;
2558  V<String> search = args[1].op;
2559  V<Word32> start = args[2].op;
2560 
2561  result = GetStringIndexOf(decoder, string, search, start);
2562  decoder->detected_->add_imported_strings();
2563  break;
2564  }
2565  case WKI::kStringToLocaleLowerCaseStringref:
2566  // TODO(14108): Implement.
2567  return false;
2568  case WKI::kStringToLowerCaseStringref: {
2569 #if V8_INTL_SUPPORT
2570  V<String> string = args[0].op;
2571  if (args[0].type.is_nullable()) {
2572  IF (__ IsNull(string, args[0].type)) {
2573  CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<
2574  BuiltinCallDescriptor::ThrowToLowerCaseCalledOnNull>(decoder,
2575  {});
2576  __ Unreachable();
2577  }
2578  }
2579  V<String> result_value = CallStringToLowercase(decoder, string);
2580  result = __ AnnotateWasmType(result_value, kWasmRefString);
2581  decoder->detected_->add_stringref();
2582  break;
2583 #else
2584  return false;
2585 #endif
2586  }
2587  case WKI::kStringToLowerCaseImported: {
2588  // We have to make sure that the externref `string` parameter is a
2589  // string. To enforce this, we inline only if a (successful)
2590  // `"js-string":"cast"` was performed before.
2591 #if V8_INTL_SUPPORT
2592  if (!IsExplicitStringCast(args[0])) {
2593  return false;
2594  }
2595  V<String> string = args[0].op;
2596  V<String> result_value = CallStringToLowercase(decoder, string);
2597  result = __ AnnotateWasmType(result_value, kWasmRefExternString);
2598  decoder->detected_->add_imported_strings();
2599  break;
2600 #else
2601  return false;
2602 #endif
2603  }
2604 
2605  // DataView related imports.
2606  // Note that we don't support DataView imports for resizable ArrayBuffers.
2607  case WKI::kDataViewGetBigInt64: {
2608  result = DataViewGetter(decoder, args, DataViewOp::kGetBigInt64);
2609  break;
2610  }
2611  case WKI::kDataViewGetBigUint64:
2612  result = DataViewGetter(decoder, args, DataViewOp::kGetBigUint64);
2613  break;
2614  case WKI::kDataViewGetFloat32:
2615  result = DataViewGetter(decoder, args, DataViewOp::kGetFloat32);
2616  break;
2617  case WKI::kDataViewGetFloat64:
2618  result = DataViewGetter(decoder, args, DataViewOp::kGetFloat64);
2619  break;
2620  case WKI::kDataViewGetInt8:
2621  result = DataViewGetter(decoder, args, DataViewOp::kGetInt8);
2622  break;
2623  case WKI::kDataViewGetInt16:
2624  result = DataViewGetter(decoder, args, DataViewOp::kGetInt16);
2625  break;
2626  case WKI::kDataViewGetInt32:
2627  result = DataViewGetter(decoder, args, DataViewOp::kGetInt32);
2628  break;
2629  case WKI::kDataViewGetUint8:
2630  result = DataViewGetter(decoder, args, DataViewOp::kGetUint8);
2631  break;
2632  case WKI::kDataViewGetUint16:
2633  result = DataViewGetter(decoder, args, DataViewOp::kGetUint16);
2634  break;
2635  case WKI::kDataViewGetUint32:
2636  result = DataViewGetter(decoder, args, DataViewOp::kGetUint32);
2637  break;
2638  case WKI::kDataViewSetBigInt64:
2639  DataViewSetter(decoder, args, DataViewOp::kSetBigInt64);
2640  break;
2641  case WKI::kDataViewSetBigUint64:
2642  DataViewSetter(decoder, args, DataViewOp::kSetBigUint64);
2643  break;
2644  case WKI::kDataViewSetFloat32:
2645  DataViewSetter(decoder, args, DataViewOp::kSetFloat32);
2646  break;
2647  case WKI::kDataViewSetFloat64:
2648  DataViewSetter(decoder, args, DataViewOp::kSetFloat64);
2649  break;
2650  case WKI::kDataViewSetInt8:
2651  DataViewSetter(decoder, args, DataViewOp::kSetInt8);
2652  break;
2653  case WKI::kDataViewSetInt16:
2654  DataViewSetter(decoder, args, DataViewOp::kSetInt16);
2655  break;
2656  case WKI::kDataViewSetInt32:
2657  DataViewSetter(decoder, args, DataViewOp::kSetInt32);
2658  break;
2659  case WKI::kDataViewSetUint8:
2660  DataViewSetter(decoder, args, DataViewOp::kSetUint8);
2661  break;
2662  case WKI::kDataViewSetUint16:
2663  DataViewSetter(decoder, args, DataViewOp::kSetUint16);
2664  break;
2665  case WKI::kDataViewSetUint32:
2666  DataViewSetter(decoder, args, DataViewOp::kSetUint32);
2667  break;
2668  case WKI::kDataViewByteLength: {
2669  V<Object> dataview = args[0].op;
2670  V<WordPtr> view_byte_length =
2671  GetDataViewByteLength(decoder, dataview, DataViewOp::kByteLength);
2672  if constexpr (Is64()) {
2673  result =
2674  __ ChangeInt64ToFloat64(__ ChangeIntPtrToInt64(view_byte_length));
2675  } else {
2676  result = __ ChangeInt32ToFloat64(
2677  __ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(view_byte_length));
2678  }
2679  break;
2680  }
2681 
2682  // Math functions.
2683  case WKI::kMathF64Acos:
2684  result = __ Float64Acos(args[0].op);
2685  break;
2686  case WKI::kMathF64Asin:
2687  result = __ Float64Asin(args[0].op);
2688  break;
2689  case WKI::kMathF64Atan:
2690  result = __ Float64Atan(args[0].op);
2691  break;
2692  case WKI::kMathF64Atan2:
2693  result = __ Float64Atan2(args[0].op, args[1].op);
2694  break;
2695  case WKI::kMathF64Cos:
2696  result = __ Float64Cos(args[0].op);
2697  break;
2698  case WKI::kMathF64Sin:
2699  result = __ Float64Sin(args[0].op);
2700  break;
2701  case WKI::kMathF64Tan:
2702  result = __ Float64Tan(args[0].op);
2703  break;
2704  case WKI::kMathF64Exp:
2705  result = __ Float64Exp(args[0].op);
2706  break;
2707  case WKI::kMathF64Log:
2708  result = __ Float64Log(args[0].op);
2709  break;
2710  case WKI::kMathF64Pow:
2711  result = __ Float64Power(args[0].op, args[1].op);
2712  break;
2713  case WKI::kMathF64Sqrt:
2714  result = __ Float64Sqrt(args[0].op);
2715  break;
2716 
2717  // Fast API calls.
2718  case WKI::kFastAPICall: {
2719  WellKnown_FastApi(decoder, imm, args, returns);
2720  result = returns[0].op;
2721  break;
2722  }
2723  }
2724  if (v8_flags.trace_wasm_inlining) {
2725  PrintF("[function %d: call to %d is well-known %s]\n", func_index_, index,
2726  WellKnownImportName(imported_op));
2727  }
2728  if (!*assumptions_) *assumptions_ = std::make_unique<AssumptionsJournal>();
2729  (*assumptions_)->RecordAssumption(index, imported_op);
2730  returns[0].op = result;
2731  return true;
2732  }
2733 
2734  void CallDirect(FullDecoder* decoder, const CallFunctionImmediate& imm,
2735  const Value args[], Value returns[]) {
2736  feedback_slot_++;
2737  if (imm.index < decoder->module_->num_imported_functions) {
2738  if (HandleWellKnownImport(decoder, imm, args, returns)) {
2739  return;
2740  }
2741  auto [target, implicit_arg] =
2742  BuildImportedFunctionTargetAndImplicitArg(decoder, imm.index);
2743  BuildWasmCall(decoder, imm.sig, target, implicit_arg, args, returns,
2744  compiler::kWasmIndirectFunction);
2745  } else {
2746  // Locally defined function.
2747  if (should_inline(decoder, feedback_slot_,
2748  decoder->module_->functions[imm.index].code.length())) {
2749  if (v8_flags.trace_wasm_inlining) {
2750  PrintF("[function %d%s: inlining direct call #%d to function %d]\n",
2751  func_index_, mode_ == kRegular ? "" : " (inlined)",
2752  feedback_slot_, imm.index);
2753  }
2754  InlineWasmCall(decoder, imm.index, imm.sig, 0, false, args, returns);
2755  } else {
2756  V<WordPtr> callee =
2757  __ RelocatableConstant(imm.index, RelocInfo::WASM_CALL);
2758  BuildWasmCall(decoder, imm.sig, callee,
2759  trusted_instance_data(
2760  decoder->module_->function_is_shared(imm.index)),
2761  args, returns);
2762  }
2763  }
2764  }
2765 
2766  void ReturnCall(FullDecoder* decoder, const CallFunctionImmediate& imm,
2767  const Value args[]) {
2768  feedback_slot_++;
2769  if (imm.index < decoder->module_->num_imported_functions) {
2770  auto [target, implicit_arg] =
2771  BuildImportedFunctionTargetAndImplicitArg(decoder, imm.index);
2772  BuildWasmMaybeReturnCall(decoder, imm.sig, target, implicit_arg, args,
2773  compiler::kWasmIndirectFunction);
2774  } else {
2775  // Locally defined function.
2776  if (should_inline(decoder, feedback_slot_,
2777  decoder->module_->functions[imm.index].code.length())) {
2778  if (v8_flags.trace_wasm_inlining) {
2779  PrintF(
2780  "[function %d%s: inlining direct tail call #%d to function %d]\n",
2781  func_index_, mode_ == kRegular ? "" : " (inlined)",
2782  feedback_slot_, imm.index);
2783  }
2784  InlineWasmCall(decoder, imm.index, imm.sig, 0, true, args, nullptr);
2785  } else {
2786  BuildWasmMaybeReturnCall(
2787  decoder, imm.sig,
2788  __ RelocatableConstant(imm.index, RelocInfo::WASM_CALL),
2789  trusted_instance_data(
2790  decoder->module_->function_is_shared(imm.index)),
2791  args);
2792  }
2793  }
2794  }
2795 
2796  void CallIndirect(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& index,
2797  const CallIndirectImmediate& imm, const Value args[],
2798  Value returns[]) {
2799  if (v8_flags.wasm_inlining_call_indirect) {
2800  CHECK(v8_flags.wasm_inlining);
2801  feedback_slot_++;
2802  // In case of being unreachable, skip it because it tries to access nodes
2803  // which might be non-existent (OpIndex::Invalid()) in unreachable code.
2804  if (__ generating_unreachable_operations()) return;
2805 
2806  if (should_inline(decoder, feedback_slot_,
2807  std::numeric_limits<int>::max())) {
2808  V<WordPtr> index_wordptr = TableAddressToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(
2809  imm.table_imm.table->address_type, index.op);
2810 
2811  DCHECK(!shared_);
2812  // Load the instance here even though it's only used below, in the hope
2813  // that load elimination can use it when fetching the target next.
2814  V<WasmTrustedInstanceData> instance = trusted_instance_data(kNotShared);
2815 
2816  // We are only interested in the target here for comparison against
2817  // the inlined call target below.
2818  // In particular, we don't need a dynamic type or null check: If the
2819  // actual call target (at runtime) is equal to the inlined call target,
2820  // we know already from the static check on the inlinee (see below) that
2821  // the inlined code has the right signature.
2822  constexpr bool kNeedsTypeOrNullCheck = false;
2823  auto [target, implicit_arg] = BuildIndirectCallTargetAndImplicitArg(
2824  decoder, index_wordptr, imm, kNeedsTypeOrNullCheck);
2825 
2826  size_t return_count = imm.sig->return_count();
2827  base::Vector<InliningTree*> feedback_cases =
2828  inlining_decisions_->function_calls()[feedback_slot_];
2829  std::vector<base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 2>> case_returns(return_count);
2830  // The slow path is the non-inlined generic `call_indirect`,
2831  // or a deopt node if that is enabled.
2832  constexpr int kSlowpathCase = 1;
2833  base::SmallVector<TSBlock*, wasm::kMaxPolymorphism + kSlowpathCase>
2834  case_blocks;
2835  for (size_t i = 0; i < feedback_cases.size() + kSlowpathCase; i++) {
2836  case_blocks.push_back(__ NewBlock());
2837  }
2838  // Block for the slowpath, i.e., the not-inlined call or deopt.
2839  TSBlock* no_inline_block = case_blocks.back();
2840  // Block for merging results after the inlined code.
2841  TSBlock* merge = __ NewBlock();
2842 
2843  // Always create a frame state, but rely on DCE to remove it in case we
2844  // end up not using deopts. This allows us to share the frame state
2845  // between a deopt due to wrong instance and deopt due to wrong target.
2846  V<FrameState> frame_state =
2847  CreateFrameState(decoder, imm.sig, &index, args);
2848  bool use_deopt_slowpath = deopts_enabled();
2849  DCHECK_IMPLIES(use_deopt_slowpath, frame_state.valid());
2850  if (use_deopt_slowpath &&
2851  inlining_decisions_->has_non_inlineable_targets()[feedback_slot_]) {
2852  if (v8_flags.trace_wasm_inlining) {
2853  PrintF(
2854  "[function %d%s: Not emitting deopt slow-path for "
2855  "call_indirect #%d as feedback contains non-inlineable "
2856  "targets]\n",
2857  func_index_, mode_ == kRegular ? "" : " (inlined)",
2858  feedback_slot_);
2859  }
2860  use_deopt_slowpath = false;
2861  }
2862 
2863  // Wasm functions are semantically closures over the instance, but
2864  // when we inline a target in the following, we implicitly assume the
2865  // inlinee instance is the same as the caller's instance.
2866  // Directly jump to the non-inlined slowpath if that's violated.
2867  // Note that for `call_ref` this isn't necessary, because the funcref
2868  // equality check already captures both code and instance equality.
2869  constexpr BranchHint kUnlikelyCrossInstanceCall = BranchHint::kTrue;
2870  // Note that the `implicit_arg` can never be a `WasmImportData`,
2871  // since we don't inline imported functions right now.
2872  __ Branch({__ TaggedEqual(implicit_arg, instance),
2873  kUnlikelyCrossInstanceCall},
2874  case_blocks[0], no_inline_block);
2875 
2876  for (size_t i = 0; i < feedback_cases.size(); i++) {
2877  __ Bind(case_blocks[i]);
2878  InliningTree* tree = feedback_cases[i];
2879  if (!tree || !tree->is_inlined()) {
2880  // Fall through to the next case.
2881  __ Goto(case_blocks[i + 1]);
2882  // Do not use the deopt slowpath if we decided to not inline (at
2883  // least) one call target.
2884  // Otherwise, this could lead to a deopt loop.
2885  use_deopt_slowpath = false;
2886  continue;
2887  }
2888  uint32_t inlined_index = tree->function_index();
2889  // Ensure that we only inline if the inlinee's signature is compatible
2890  // with the call_indirect. In other words, perform the type check that
2891  // would normally be done dynamically (see above
2892  // `BuildIndirectCallTargetAndImplicitArg`) statically on the inlined
2893  // target. This can fail, e.g., because the mapping of feedback back
2894  // to function indices may produce spurious targets, or because the
2895  // feedback in the JS heap has been corrupted by a vulnerability.
2896  if (!InlineTargetIsTypeCompatible(
2897  decoder->module_, imm.sig,
2898  decoder->module_->functions[inlined_index].sig)) {
2899  __ Goto(case_blocks[i + 1]);
2900  continue;
2901  }
2902 
2903  V<Word32> inlined_target =
2904  __ RelocatableWasmIndirectCallTarget(inlined_index);
2905 
2906  bool is_last_feedback_case = (i == feedback_cases.size() - 1);
2907  if (use_deopt_slowpath && is_last_feedback_case) {
2908  DeoptIfNot(decoder, __ Word32Equal(target, inlined_target),
2909  frame_state);
2910  } else {
2911  TSBlock* inline_block = __ NewBlock();
2912  BranchHint hint =
2913  is_last_feedback_case ? BranchHint::kTrue : BranchHint::kNone;
2914  __ Branch({__ Word32Equal(target, inlined_target), hint},
2915  inline_block, case_blocks[i + 1]);
2916  __ Bind(inline_block);
2917  }
2918 
2919  SmallZoneVector<Value, 4> direct_returns(return_count,
2920  decoder->zone_);
2921  if (v8_flags.trace_wasm_inlining) {
2922  PrintF(
2923  "[function %d%s: Speculatively inlining call_indirect #%d, "
2924  "case #%zu, to function %d]\n",
2925  func_index_, mode_ == kRegular ? "" : " (inlined)",
2926  feedback_slot_, i, inlined_index);
2927  }
2928  InlineWasmCall(decoder, inlined_index, imm.sig,
2929  static_cast<uint32_t>(i), false, args,
2930  direct_returns.data());
2931 
2932  if (__ current_block() != nullptr) {
2933  // Only add phi inputs and a Goto to {merge} if the current_block is
2934  // not nullptr. If the current_block is nullptr, it means that the
2935  // inlined body unconditionally exits early (likely an unconditional
2936  // trap or throw).
2937  for (size_t ret = 0; ret < direct_returns.size(); ret++) {
2938  case_returns[ret].push_back(direct_returns[ret].op);
2939  }
2940  __ Goto(merge);
2941  }
2942  }
2943 
2944  __ Bind(no_inline_block);
2945  if (use_deopt_slowpath) {
2946  // We need this unconditional deopt only for the "instance check",
2947  // as the last "target check" already uses a `DeoptIfNot` node.
2948  Deopt(decoder, frame_state);
2949  } else {
2950  auto [call_target, call_implicit_arg] =
2951  BuildIndirectCallTargetAndImplicitArg(decoder, index_wordptr,
2952  imm);
2953  SmallZoneVector<Value, 4> indirect_returns(return_count,
2954  decoder->zone_);
2955  BuildWasmCall(decoder, imm.sig, call_target, call_implicit_arg, args,
2956  indirect_returns.data(),
2957  compiler::kWasmIndirectFunction);
2958  for (size_t ret = 0; ret < indirect_returns.size(); ret++) {
2959  case_returns[ret].push_back(indirect_returns[ret].op);
2960  }
2961  __ Goto(merge);
2962  }
2963 
2964  __ Bind(merge);
2965  for (size_t i = 0; i < case_returns.size(); i++) {
2966  returns[i].op = __ Phi(base::VectorOf(case_returns[i]),
2967  RepresentationFor(imm.sig->GetReturn(i)));
2968  }
2969 
2970  return;
2971  } // should_inline
2972  } // v8_flags.wasm_inlining_call_indirect
2973 
2974  // Didn't inline.
2975  V<WordPtr> index_wordptr = TableAddressToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(
2976  imm.table_imm.table->address_type, index.op);
2977  auto [target, implicit_arg] =
2978  BuildIndirectCallTargetAndImplicitArg(decoder, index_wordptr, imm);
2979  BuildWasmCall(decoder, imm.sig, target, implicit_arg, args, returns,
2980  compiler::kWasmIndirectFunction);
2981  }
2982

2984  const CallIndirectImmediate& imm,
2985  const Value args[]) {
2986  if (v8_flags.wasm_inlining_call_indirect) {
2987  CHECK(v8_flags.wasm_inlining);
2988  feedback_slot_++;
2989 
2990  if (should_inline(decoder, feedback_slot_,
2991  std::numeric_limits<int>::max())) {
2992  V<WordPtr> index_wordptr = TableAddressToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(
2993  imm.table_imm.table->address_type, index.op);
2994 
2995  DCHECK(!shared_);
2996  // Load the instance here even though it's only used below, in the hope
2997  // that load elimination can use it when fetching the target next.
2998  V<WasmTrustedInstanceData> instance = trusted_instance_data(kNotShared);

3082  } // should_inline
3083  } // v8_flags.wasm_inlining_call_indirect

3085  // Didn't inline.

3091  compiler::kWasmIndirectFunction);
3092  }

3094  void CallRef(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& func_ref,
3095  const FunctionSig* sig, const Value args[], Value returns[]) {
3096  // TODO(14108): As the slot needs to be aligned with Liftoff, ideally the
3097  // stack slot index would be provided by the decoder and passed to both
3098  // Liftoff and Turbofan.
3099  feedback_slot_++;
3100  // In case of being unreachable, skip it because it tries to access nodes
3101  // which might be non-existent (OpIndex::Invalid()) in unreachable code.
3102  if (__ generating_unreachable_operations()) return;
3103 
3104  if (should_inline(decoder, feedback_slot_,
3105  std::numeric_limits<int>::max())) {
3106  DCHECK(!shared_);
3107  V<FixedArray> func_refs = LOAD_IMMUTABLE_INSTANCE_FIELD(
3108  trusted_instance_data(kNotShared), FuncRefs,
3109  MemoryRepresentation::TaggedPointer());
3110 
3111  size_t return_count = sig->return_count();
3112  base::Vector<InliningTree*> feedback_cases =
3113  inlining_decisions_->function_calls()[feedback_slot_];
3114  std::vector<base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 2>> case_returns(return_count);
3115  // The slow path is the non-inlined generic `call_ref`,
3116  // or a deopt node if that is enabled.
3117  constexpr int kSlowpathCase = 1;
3118  base::SmallVector<TSBlock*, wasm::kMaxPolymorphism + kSlowpathCase>
3119  case_blocks;
3120  for (size_t i = 0; i < feedback_cases.size() + kSlowpathCase; i++) {
3121  case_blocks.push_back(__ NewBlock());
3122  }
3123  TSBlock* merge = __ NewBlock();
3124  __ Goto(case_blocks[0]);
3125 
3126  bool use_deopt_slowpath = deopts_enabled();
3127  for (size_t i = 0; i < feedback_cases.size(); i++) {
3128  __ Bind(case_blocks[i]);
3129  InliningTree* tree = feedback_cases[i];
3130  if (!tree || !tree->is_inlined()) {
3131  // Fall through to the next case.
3132  __ Goto(case_blocks[i + 1]);
3133  // Do not use the deopt slowpath if we decided to not inline (at
3134  // least) one call target. Otherwise, this could lead to a deopt loop.
3135  use_deopt_slowpath = false;
3136  continue;
3137  }
3138  uint32_t inlined_index = tree->function_index();
3139  DCHECK(!decoder->module_->function_is_shared(inlined_index));
3140  V<Object> inlined_func_ref =
3141  __ LoadFixedArrayElement(func_refs, inlined_index);
3142 
3143  bool is_last_feedback_case = (i == feedback_cases.size() - 1);
3144  if (use_deopt_slowpath && is_last_feedback_case) {
3145  if (inlining_decisions_
3146  ->has_non_inlineable_targets()[feedback_slot_]) {
3147  if (v8_flags.trace_wasm_inlining) {
3148  PrintF(
3149  "[function %d%s: Not emitting deopt slow-path for "
3150  "call_ref #%d as feedback contains non-inlineable "
3151  "targets]\n",
3152  func_index_, mode_ == kRegular ? "" : " (inlined)",
3153  feedback_slot_);
3154  }
3155  use_deopt_slowpath = false;
3156  }
3157  }
3158  bool emit_deopt = use_deopt_slowpath && is_last_feedback_case;
3159  if (emit_deopt) {
3160  V<FrameState> frame_state =
3161  CreateFrameState(decoder, sig, &func_ref, args);
3162  if (frame_state.valid()) {
3163  DeoptIfNot(decoder, __ TaggedEqual(func_ref.op, inlined_func_ref),
3164  frame_state);
3165  } else {
3166  emit_deopt = false;
3167  use_deopt_slowpath = false;
3168  }
3169  }
3170  if (!emit_deopt) {
3171  TSBlock* inline_block = __ NewBlock();
3172  BranchHint hint =
3173  is_last_feedback_case ? BranchHint::kTrue : BranchHint::kNone;
3174  __ Branch({__ TaggedEqual(func_ref.op, inlined_func_ref), hint},
3175  inline_block, case_blocks[i + 1]);
3176  __ Bind(inline_block);
3177  }
3178 
3179  SmallZoneVector<Value, 4> direct_returns(return_count, decoder->zone_);
3180  if (v8_flags.trace_wasm_inlining) {
3181  PrintF(
3182  "[function %d%s: Speculatively inlining call_ref #%d, case #%zu, "
3183  "to function %d]\n",
3184  func_index_, mode_ == kRegular ? "" : " (inlined)",
3185  feedback_slot_, i, inlined_index);
3186  }
3187  InlineWasmCall(decoder, inlined_index, sig, static_cast<uint32_t>(i),
3188  false, args, direct_returns.data());
3189 
3190  if (__ current_block() != nullptr) {
3191  // Only add phi inputs and a Goto to {merge} if the current_block is
3192  // not nullptr. If the current_block is nullptr, it means that the
3193  // inlined body unconditionally exits early (likely an unconditional
3194  // trap or throw).
3195  for (size_t ret = 0; ret < direct_returns.size(); ret++) {
3196  case_returns[ret].push_back(direct_returns[ret].op);
3197  }
3198  __ Goto(merge);
3199  }
3200  }
3201 
3202  if (!use_deopt_slowpath) {
3203  TSBlock* no_inline_block = case_blocks.back();
3204  __ Bind(no_inline_block);
3205  auto [target, implicit_arg] =
3206  BuildFunctionReferenceTargetAndImplicitArg(func_ref.op,
3207  func_ref.type);
3208  SmallZoneVector<Value, 4> ref_returns(return_count, decoder->zone_);
3209  BuildWasmCall(decoder, sig, target, implicit_arg, args,
3210  ref_returns.data(), compiler::kWasmIndirectFunction);
3211  for (size_t ret = 0; ret < ref_returns.size(); ret++) {
3212  case_returns[ret].push_back(ref_returns[ret].op);
3213  }
3214  __ Goto(merge);
3215  }
3216 
3217  __ Bind(merge);
3218  for (size_t i = 0; i < case_returns.size(); i++) {
3219  returns[i].op = __ Phi(base::VectorOf(case_returns[i]),
3220  RepresentationFor(sig->GetReturn(i)));
3221  }
3222  } else {
3223  auto [target, implicit_arg] = BuildFunctionReferenceTargetAndImplicitArg(
3224  func_ref.op, func_ref.type);
3225  BuildWasmCall(decoder, sig, target, implicit_arg, args, returns,
3226  compiler::kWasmIndirectFunction);
3227  }
3228  }

3230  void ReturnCallRef(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& func_ref,
3231  const FunctionSig* sig, const Value args[]) {
3232  feedback_slot_++;
3233 
3234  if (should_inline(decoder, feedback_slot_,
3235  std::numeric_limits<int>::max())) {
3236  DCHECK(!shared_);
3237  V<FixedArray> func_refs = LOAD_IMMUTABLE_INSTANCE_FIELD(
3238  trusted_instance_data(kNotShared), FuncRefs,
3239  MemoryRepresentation::TaggedPointer());

3251

3259  }

3261  DCHECK(!decoder->module_->function_is_shared(inlined_index));

3264 
3265  TSBlock* inline_block = __ NewBlock();
3266  bool is_last_case = (i == feedback_cases.size() - 1);
3267  BranchHint hint = is_last_case ? BranchHint::kTrue : BranchHint::kNone;
3268  __ Branch({__ TaggedEqual(func_ref.op, inlined_func_ref), hint},
3269  inline_block, case_blocks[i + 1]);

3276  feedback_slot_, i, inlined_index);
3277  }
3278  InlineWasmCall(decoder, inlined_index, sig, static_cast<uint32_t>(i),
3279  true, args, nullptr);

3282  DCHECK_NULL(__ current_block());
3283  }
3284 
3285  TSBlock* no_inline_block = case_blocks.back();
3286  __ Bind(no_inline_block);
3287  }
3288  auto [target, implicit_arg] =
3289  BuildFunctionReferenceTargetAndImplicitArg(func_ref.op, func_ref.type);
3290  BuildWasmMaybeReturnCall(decoder, sig, target, implicit_arg, args,
3291  compiler::kWasmIndirectFunction);
3292  }
3293 
3294  void BrOnNull(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& ref_object, uint32_t depth,
3295  bool pass_null_along_branch, Value* result_on_fallthrough) {
3296  result_on_fallthrough->op = ref_object.op;
3297  IF (UNLIKELY(__ IsNull(ref_object.op, ref_object.type))) {
3298  int drop_values = pass_null_along_branch ? 0 : 1;
3299  BrOrRet(decoder, depth, drop_values);
3300  }
3301  }
3302 
3303  void BrOnNonNull(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& ref_object, Value* result,
3304  uint32_t depth, bool /* drop_null_on_fallthrough */) {
3305  result->op = ref_object.op;
3306  IF_NOT (UNLIKELY(__ IsNull(ref_object.op, ref_object.type))) {
3307  BrOrRet(decoder, depth);
3308  }
3309  }

3311  void SimdOp(FullDecoder* decoder, WasmOpcode opcode, const Value* args,
3312  Value* result) {
3313  switch (opcode) {
3314 #define HANDLE_BINARY_OPCODE(kind) \
3315  case kExpr##kind: \
3316  result->op = \
3317  __ Simd128Binop(V<compiler::turboshaft::Simd128>::Cast(args[0].op), \
3318  V<compiler::turboshaft::Simd128>::Cast(args[1].op), \
3319  compiler::turboshaft::Simd128BinopOp::Kind::k##kind); \
3320  break;
3321  FOREACH_SIMD_128_BINARY_MANDATORY_OPCODE(HANDLE_BINARY_OPCODE)
3322 #undef HANDLE_BINARY_OPCODE
3323 #define HANDLE_F16X8_BIN_OPTIONAL_OPCODE(kind, extern_ref) \
3324  case kExprF16x8##kind: \
3325  if (SupportedOperations::float16()) { \
3326  result->op = __ Simd128Binop( \
3327  V<compiler::turboshaft::Simd128>::Cast(args[0].op), \
3328  V<compiler::turboshaft::Simd128>::Cast(args[1].op), \

3330  } else { \

3333  MemoryRepresentation::Simd128()); \

3524  break;

3527

3552  void SimdLaneOp(FullDecoder* decoder, WasmOpcode opcode,
3553  const SimdLaneImmediate& imm,
3554  base::Vector<const Value> inputs, Value* result) {
3555  using compiler::turboshaft::Simd128ExtractLaneOp;
3556  using compiler::turboshaft::Simd128ReplaceLaneOp;
3557  using Simd128 = compiler::turboshaft::Simd128;
3558  V<Simd128> input_val = V<Simd128>::Cast(inputs[0].op);
3559  switch (opcode) {
3560  case kExprI8x16ExtractLaneS:
3561  result->op = __ Simd128ExtractLane(
3562  input_val, Simd128ExtractLaneOp::Kind::kI8x16S, imm.lane);
3563  break;
3564  case kExprI8x16ExtractLaneU:
3565  result->op = __ Simd128ExtractLane(
3566  input_val, Simd128ExtractLaneOp::Kind::kI8x16U, imm.lane);
3567  break;
3568  case kExprI16x8ExtractLaneS:
3569  result->op = __ Simd128ExtractLane(
3570  input_val, Simd128ExtractLaneOp::Kind::kI16x8S, imm.lane);
3571  break;
3572  case kExprI16x8ExtractLaneU:
3573  result->op = __ Simd128ExtractLane(
3574  input_val, Simd128ExtractLaneOp::Kind::kI16x8U, imm.lane);
3575  break;
3576  case kExprI32x4ExtractLane:
3577  result->op = __ Simd128ExtractLane(
3578  input_val, Simd128ExtractLaneOp::Kind::kI32x4, imm.lane);
3579  break;
3580  case kExprI64x2ExtractLane:
3581  result->op = __ Simd128ExtractLane(
3582  input_val, Simd128ExtractLaneOp::Kind::kI64x2, imm.lane);
3583  break;
3584  case kExprF16x8ExtractLane:
3585  if (SupportedOperations::float16()) {
3586  result->op = __ Simd128ExtractLane(
3587  input_val, Simd128ExtractLaneOp::Kind::kF16x8, imm.lane);
3588  } else {
3589  auto f16 = __ Simd128ExtractLane(
3590  input_val, Simd128ExtractLaneOp::Kind::kI16x8S, imm.lane);
3591  result->op = CallCStackSlotToStackSlot(
3592  f16, ExternalReference::wasm_float16_to_float32(),
3593  MemoryRepresentation::Int16(), MemoryRepresentation::Float32());
3594  }
3595  break;
3596  case kExprF32x4ExtractLane:
3597  result->op = __ Simd128ExtractLane(
3598  input_val, Simd128ExtractLaneOp::Kind::kF32x4, imm.lane);
3599  break;
3600  case kExprF64x2ExtractLane:
3601  result->op = __ Simd128ExtractLane(
3602  input_val, Simd128ExtractLaneOp::Kind::kF64x2, imm.lane);
3603  break;
3604  case kExprI8x16ReplaceLane:
3605  result->op =
3606  __ Simd128ReplaceLane(input_val, V<Any>::Cast(inputs[1].op),
3607  Simd128ReplaceLaneOp::Kind::kI8x16, imm.lane);
3608  break;
3609  case kExprI16x8ReplaceLane:
3610  result->op =
3611  __ Simd128ReplaceLane(input_val, V<Simd128>::Cast(inputs[1].op),
3612  Simd128ReplaceLaneOp::Kind::kI16x8, imm.lane);
3613  break;
3614  case kExprI32x4ReplaceLane:
3615  result->op =
3616  __ Simd128ReplaceLane(input_val, V<Any>::Cast(inputs[1].op),
3617  Simd128ReplaceLaneOp::Kind::kI32x4, imm.lane);
3618  break;
3619  case kExprI64x2ReplaceLane:
3620  result->op =
3621  __ Simd128ReplaceLane(input_val, V<Any>::Cast(inputs[1].op),
3622  Simd128ReplaceLaneOp::Kind::kI64x2, imm.lane);
3623  break;
3624  case kExprF16x8ReplaceLane:
3625  if (SupportedOperations::float16()) {
3626  result->op = __ Simd128ReplaceLane(
3627  input_val, V<Any>::Cast(inputs[1].op),
3628  Simd128ReplaceLaneOp::Kind::kF16x8, imm.lane);
3629  } else {
3630  auto f16 = CallCStackSlotToStackSlot(
3631  inputs[1].op, ExternalReference::wasm_float32_to_float16(),
3632  MemoryRepresentation::Float32(), MemoryRepresentation::Int16());
3633  result->op = __ Simd128ReplaceLane(input_val, V<Any>::Cast(f16),
3634  Simd128ReplaceLaneOp::Kind::kI16x8,
3635  imm.lane);
3636  }
3637  break;
3638  case kExprF32x4ReplaceLane:
3639  result->op =
3640  __ Simd128ReplaceLane(input_val, V<Any>::Cast(inputs[1].op),
3641  Simd128ReplaceLaneOp::Kind::kF32x4, imm.lane);
3642  break;
3643  case kExprF64x2ReplaceLane:
3644  result->op =
3645  __ Simd128ReplaceLane(input_val, V<Any>::Cast(inputs[1].op),
3646  Simd128ReplaceLaneOp::Kind::kF64x2, imm.lane);
3647  break;
3648  default:
3649  UNREACHABLE();
3650  }
3651  }

3653  void Simd8x16ShuffleOp(FullDecoder* decoder, const Simd128Immediate& imm,
3654  const Value& input0, const Value& input1,
3655  Value* result) {
3656  result->op = __ Simd128Shuffle(
3657  V<compiler::turboshaft::Simd128>::Cast(input0.op),
3658  V<compiler::turboshaft::Simd128>::Cast(input1.op),
3659  compiler::turboshaft::Simd128ShuffleOp::Kind::kI8x16, imm.value);
3660  }

3662  void Try(FullDecoder* decoder, Control* block) {
3663  block->false_or_loop_or_catch_block = NewBlockWithPhis(decoder, nullptr);
3664  block->merge_block = NewBlockWithPhis(decoder, block->br_merge());
3665  }
3666 
3667  void Throw(FullDecoder* decoder, const TagIndexImmediate& imm,
3668  const Value arg_values[]) {
3669  size_t count = imm.tag->sig->parameter_count();
3670  SmallZoneVector<OpIndex, 16> values(count, decoder->zone_);
3671  for (size_t index = 0; index < count; index++) {
3672  values[index] = arg_values[index].op;
3673  }
3674 
3675  uint32_t encoded_size = WasmExceptionPackage::GetEncodedSize(imm.tag);
3676 
3677  V<FixedArray> values_array = CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<
3678  BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmAllocateFixedArray>(
3679  decoder, {__ IntPtrConstant(encoded_size)});
3680  uint32_t index = 0;
3681  const wasm::WasmTagSig* sig = imm.tag->sig;
3682 
3683  // Encode the exception values in {values_array}.
3684  for (size_t i = 0; i < count; i++) {
3685  OpIndex value = values[i];
3686  switch (sig->GetParam(i).kind()) {
3687  case kF32:
3688  value = __ BitcastFloat32ToWord32(value);
3689  [[fallthrough]];
3690  case kI32:
3691  BuildEncodeException32BitValue(values_array, index, value);
3692  // We need 2 Smis to encode a 32-bit value.
3693  index += 2;
3694  break;
3695  case kF64:
3696  value = __ BitcastFloat64ToWord64(value);
3697  [[fallthrough]];
3698  case kI64: {
3699  OpIndex upper_half =
3700  __ TruncateWord64ToWord32(__ Word64ShiftRightLogical(value, 32));
3701  BuildEncodeException32BitValue(values_array, index, upper_half);
3702  index += 2;
3703  OpIndex lower_half = __ TruncateWord64ToWord32(value);
3704  BuildEncodeException32BitValue(values_array, index, lower_half);
3705  index += 2;
3706  break;
3707  }
3708  case wasm::kRef:
3709  case wasm::kRefNull:
3710  __ StoreFixedArrayElement(values_array, index, value,
3711  compiler::kFullWriteBarrier);
3712  index++;
3713  break;
3714  case kS128: {
3715  using Simd128 = compiler::turboshaft::Simd128;
3716  V<Simd128> value_s128 = V<Simd128>::Cast(value);
3717  using Kind = compiler::turboshaft::Simd128ExtractLaneOp::Kind;
3718  BuildEncodeException32BitValue(values_array, index,
3719  V<Word32>::Cast(__ Simd128ExtractLane(
3720  value_s128, Kind::kI32x4, 0)));
3721  index += 2;
3722  BuildEncodeException32BitValue(values_array, index,
3723  V<Word32>::Cast(__ Simd128ExtractLane(
3724  value_s128, Kind::kI32x4, 1)));
3725  index += 2;
3726  BuildEncodeException32BitValue(values_array, index,
3727  V<Word32>::Cast(__ Simd128ExtractLane(
3728  value_s128, Kind::kI32x4, 2)));
3729  index += 2;
3730  BuildEncodeException32BitValue(values_array, index,
3731  V<Word32>::Cast(__ Simd128ExtractLane(
3732  value_s128, Kind::kI32x4, 3)));
3733  index += 2;
3734  break;
3735  }
3736  case kI8:
3737  case kI16:
3738  case kF16:
3739  case kVoid:
3740  case kTop:
3741  case kBottom:
3742  UNREACHABLE();
3743  }
3744  }
3745 
3746  // TODO(14616): Support shared tags.
3747  V<FixedArray> instance_tags =
3748  LOAD_IMMUTABLE_INSTANCE_FIELD(trusted_instance_data(false), TagsTable,
3749  MemoryRepresentation::TaggedPointer());
3750  auto tag = V<WasmTagObject>::Cast(
3751  __ LoadFixedArrayElement(instance_tags, imm.index));
3752 
3753  CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmThrow>(
3754  decoder, {tag, values_array}, CheckForException::kCatchInThisFrame);
3755  __ Unreachable();
3756  }
3757 
3758  void Rethrow(FullDecoder* decoder, Control* block) {
3759  CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmRethrow>(
3760  decoder, {block->exception}, CheckForException::kCatchInThisFrame);
3761  __ Unreachable();
3762  }
3763 
3764  void CatchException(FullDecoder* decoder, const TagIndexImmediate& imm,
3765  Control* block, base::Vector<Value> values) {
3766  if (deopts_enabled()) {
3767  if (v8_flags.trace_wasm_inlining) {
3768  PrintF(
3769  "[function %d%s: Disabling deoptimizations for speculative "
3770  "inlining due to legacy exception handling usage]\n",
3771  func_index_, mode_ == kRegular ? "" : " (inlined)");
3772  }
3773  disable_deopts();
3774  }
3775 
3776  BindBlockAndGeneratePhis(decoder, block->false_or_loop_or_catch_block,
3777  nullptr, &block->exception);
3778  V<NativeContext> native_context = instance_cache_.native_context();
3779  V<WasmTagObject> caught_tag = V<WasmTagObject>::Cast(
3780  CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmGetOwnProperty>(
3781  decoder, native_context,
3782  {block->exception, LOAD_ROOT(wasm_exception_tag_symbol)}));
3783  // TODO(14616): Support shared tags.
3784  V<FixedArray> instance_tags =
3785  LOAD_IMMUTABLE_INSTANCE_FIELD(trusted_instance_data(false), TagsTable,
3786  MemoryRepresentation::TaggedPointer());
3787  auto expected_tag = V<WasmTagObject>::Cast(
3788  __ LoadFixedArrayElement(instance_tags, imm.index));
3789  TSBlock* if_no_catch = NewBlockWithPhis(decoder, nullptr);
3790  SetupControlFlowEdge(decoder, if_no_catch);
3791 
3792  // If the tags don't match we continue with the next tag by setting the
3793  // no-catch environment as the new {block->false_or_loop_or_catch_block}
3794  // here.
3795  block->false_or_loop_or_catch_block = if_no_catch;
3796 
3797  if (imm.tag->sig->parameter_count() == 1 &&
3798  imm.tag->sig->GetParam(0).is_reference_to(HeapType::kExtern)) {
3799  // Check for the special case where the tag is WebAssembly.JSTag and the
3800  // exception is not a WebAssembly.Exception. In this case the exception is
3801  // caught and pushed on the operand stack.
3802  // Only perform this check if the tag signature is the same as
3803  // the JSTag signature, i.e. a single externref or (ref extern), otherwise
3804  // we know statically that it cannot be the JSTag.
3805  V<Word32> caught_tag_undefined =
3806  __ TaggedEqual(caught_tag, LOAD_ROOT(UndefinedValue));
3807  Label<Object> if_catch(&asm_);
3808  Label<> no_catch_merge(&asm_);
3809 
3810  IF (UNLIKELY(caught_tag_undefined)) {
3811  V<Object> tag_object = __ Load(
3812  native_context, LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase(),
3813  MemoryRepresentation::TaggedPointer(),
3814  NativeContext::OffsetOfElementAt(Context::WASM_JS_TAG_INDEX));
3815  V<Object> js_tag = __ Load(tag_object, LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase(),
3816  MemoryRepresentation::TaggedPointer(),
3817  WasmTagObject::kTagOffset);
3818  GOTO_IF(__ TaggedEqual(expected_tag, js_tag), if_catch,
3819  block->exception);
3820  GOTO(no_catch_merge);
3821  } ELSE {
3822  IF (__ TaggedEqual(caught_tag, expected_tag)) {
3823  UnpackWasmException(decoder, block->exception, values);
3824  GOTO(if_catch, values[0].op);
3825  }
3826  GOTO(no_catch_merge);
3827  }
3828 
3829  BIND(no_catch_merge);
3830  __ Goto(if_no_catch);
3831 
3832  BIND(if_catch, caught_exception);
3833  // The first unpacked value is the exception itself in the case of a JS
3834  // exception.
3835  values[0].op = caught_exception;
3836  } else {
3837  TSBlock* if_catch = __ NewBlock();
3838  __ Branch(ConditionWithHint(__ TaggedEqual(caught_tag, expected_tag)),
3839  if_catch, if_no_catch);
3840  __ Bind(if_catch);
3841  UnpackWasmException(decoder, block->exception, values);
3842  }
3843  }
3844 
3845  void Delegate(FullDecoder* decoder, uint32_t depth, Control* block) {
3846  BindBlockAndGeneratePhis(decoder, block->false_or_loop_or_catch_block,
3847  nullptr, &block->exception);
3848  if (depth == decoder->control_depth() - 1) {
3849  if (mode_ == kInlinedWithCatch) {
3850  if (block->exception.valid()) {
3851  return_phis_->AddIncomingException(block->exception);
3852  }
3853  __ Goto(return_catch_block_);
3854  } else {
3855  // We just throw to the caller, no need to handle the exception in this
3856  // frame.
3857  CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmRethrow>(
3858  decoder, {block->exception});
3859  __ Unreachable();
3860  }
3861  } else {
3862  DCHECK(decoder->control_at(depth)->is_try());
3863  TSBlock* target_catch =
3864  decoder->control_at(depth)->false_or_loop_or_catch_block;
3865  SetupControlFlowEdge(decoder, target_catch, 0, block->exception);
3866  __ Goto(target_catch);
3867  }
3868  }
3869 
3870  void CatchAll(FullDecoder* decoder, Control* block) {
3871  DCHECK(block->is_try_catchall() || block->is_try_catch());
3872  DCHECK_EQ(decoder->control_at(0), block);
3873 
3874  if (deopts_enabled()) {
3875  if (v8_flags.trace_wasm_inlining) {
3876  // TODO(42204618): Would it be worthwhile to add support for this?
3877  // The difficulty is the handling of the exception which is handled as a
3878  // value on the value stack in Liftoff but handled very differently in
3879  // Turboshaft (and it would need to be passed on in the FrameState).
3880  PrintF(
3881  "[function %d%s: Disabling deoptimizations for speculative "
3882  "inlining due to legacy exception handling usage]\n",
3883  func_index_, mode_ == kRegular ? "" : " (inlined)");
3884  }
3885  disable_deopts();
3886  }
3887 
3888  BindBlockAndGeneratePhis(decoder, block->false_or_loop_or_catch_block,
3889  nullptr, &block->exception);
3890  }
3891 
3892  void TryTable(FullDecoder* decoder, Control* block) { Try(decoder, block); }
3893 
3894  void CatchCase(FullDecoder* decoder, Control* block,
3895  const CatchCase& catch_case, base::Vector<Value> values) {
3896  // If this is the first catch case, {block->false_or_loop_or_catch_block} is
3897  // the block that was created on block entry, and is where all throwing
3898  // instructions in the try-table jump to if they throw.
3899  // Otherwise, {block->false_or_loop_or_catch_block} has been overwritten by
3900  // the previous handler, and is where we jump to if we did not catch the
3901  // exception yet.
3902  BindBlockAndGeneratePhis(decoder, block->false_or_loop_or_catch_block,
3903  nullptr, &block->exception);
3904  if (catch_case.kind == kCatchAll || catch_case.kind == kCatchAllRef) {
3905  if (catch_case.kind == kCatchAllRef) {
3906  DCHECK_EQ(values.size(), 1);
3907  values.last().op = block->exception;
3908  }
3909  BrOrRet(decoder, catch_case.br_imm.depth);
3910  return;
3911  }
3912  V<NativeContext> native_context = instance_cache_.native_context();
3913  V<WasmTagObject> caught_tag = V<WasmTagObject>::Cast(
3914  CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmGetOwnProperty>(
3915  decoder, native_context,
3916  {block->exception, LOAD_ROOT(wasm_exception_tag_symbol)}));
3917  // TODO(14616): Support shared tags.
3918  V<FixedArray> instance_tags =
3919  LOAD_IMMUTABLE_INSTANCE_FIELD(trusted_instance_data(false), TagsTable,
3920  MemoryRepresentation::TaggedPointer());
3921  auto expected_tag = V<WasmTagObject>::Cast(__ LoadFixedArrayElement(
3922  instance_tags, catch_case.maybe_tag.tag_imm.index));
3923  TSBlock* if_no_catch = NewBlockWithPhis(decoder, nullptr);
3924  SetupControlFlowEdge(decoder, if_no_catch);
3925 
3926  // If the tags don't match we continue with the next tag by setting the
3927  // no-catch environment as the new {block->false_or_loop_or_catch_block}
3928  // here.
3929  block->false_or_loop_or_catch_block = if_no_catch;
3930 
3931  if (catch_case.maybe_tag.tag_imm.tag->sig->parameter_count() == 1 &&
3932  catch_case.maybe_tag.tag_imm.tag->sig->GetParam(0) == kWasmExternRef) {
3933  // Check for the special case where the tag is WebAssembly.JSTag and the
3934  // exception is not a WebAssembly.Exception. In this case the exception is
3935  // caught and pushed on the operand stack.
3936  // Only perform this check if the tag signature is the same as
3937  // the JSTag signature, i.e. a single externref, otherwise
3938  // we know statically that it cannot be the JSTag.
3939  V<Word32> caught_tag_undefined =
3940  __ TaggedEqual(caught_tag, LOAD_ROOT(UndefinedValue));
3941  Label<Object> if_catch(&asm_);
3942  Label<> no_catch_merge(&asm_);
3943 
3944  IF (UNLIKELY(caught_tag_undefined)) {
3945  V<Object> tag_object = __ Load(
3946  native_context, LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase(),
3947  MemoryRepresentation::TaggedPointer(),
3948  NativeContext::OffsetOfElementAt(Context::WASM_JS_TAG_INDEX));
3949  V<Object> js_tag = __ Load(tag_object, LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase(),
3950  MemoryRepresentation::TaggedPointer(),
3951  WasmTagObject::kTagOffset);
3952  GOTO_IF(__ TaggedEqual(expected_tag, js_tag), if_catch,
3953  block->exception);
3954  GOTO(no_catch_merge);
3955  } ELSE {
3956  IF (__ TaggedEqual(caught_tag, expected_tag)) {
3957  if (catch_case.kind == kCatchRef) {
3958  UnpackWasmException(decoder, block->exception,
3959  values.SubVector(0, values.size() - 1));
3960  values.last().op = block->exception;
3961  } else {
3962  UnpackWasmException(decoder, block->exception, values);
3963  }
3964  GOTO(if_catch, values[0].op);
3965  }
3966  GOTO(no_catch_merge);
3967  }
3968 
3969  BIND(no_catch_merge);
3970  __ Goto(if_no_catch);
3971 
3972  BIND(if_catch, caught_exception);
3973  // The first unpacked value is the exception itself in the case of a JS
3974  // exception.
3975  values[0].op = caught_exception;
3976  } else {
3977  TSBlock* if_catch = __ NewBlock();
3978  __ Branch(ConditionWithHint(__ TaggedEqual(caught_tag, expected_tag)),
3979  if_catch, if_no_catch);
3980  __ Bind(if_catch);
3981  if (catch_case.kind == kCatchRef) {
3982  UnpackWasmException(decoder, block->exception,
3983  values.SubVector(0, values.size() - 1));
3984  values.last().op = block->exception;
3985  } else {
3986  UnpackWasmException(decoder, block->exception, values);
3987  }
3988  }
3989 
3990  BrOrRet(decoder, catch_case.br_imm.depth);
3991 
3992  bool is_last = &catch_case == &block->catch_cases.last();
3993  if (is_last && !decoder->HasCatchAll(block)) {
3994  BindBlockAndGeneratePhis(decoder, block->false_or_loop_or_catch_block,
3995  nullptr, &block->exception);
3996  ThrowRef(decoder, block->exception);
3997  }
3998  }

4002  }

4040  void AtomicNotify(FullDecoder* decoder, const MemoryAccessImmediate& imm,
4041  OpIndex index, OpIndex num_waiters_to_wake, Value* result) {
4042  V<WordPtr> converted_index;
4043  compiler::BoundsCheckResult bounds_check_result;
4044  std::tie(converted_index, bounds_check_result) = BoundsCheckMem(
4045  imm.memory, MemoryRepresentation::Int32(), index, imm.offset,
4046  compiler::EnforceBoundsCheck::kNeedsBoundsCheck,
4047  compiler::AlignmentCheck::kYes);
4048 
4049  OpIndex effective_offset = __ WordPtrAdd(converted_index, imm.offset);
4050  OpIndex addr = __ WordPtrAdd(MemStart(imm.mem_index), effective_offset);
4051 
4052  auto sig = FixedSizeSignature<MachineType>::Returns(MachineType::Int32())
4053  .Params(MachineType::Pointer(), MachineType::Uint32());
4054  result->op = CallC(&sig, ExternalReference::wasm_atomic_notify(),
4055  {addr, num_waiters_to_wake});
4056  }
4057 
4058  void AtomicWait(FullDecoder* decoder, WasmOpcode opcode,
4059  const MemoryAccessImmediate& imm, OpIndex index,
4060  OpIndex expected, V<Word64> timeout, Value* result) {
4061  constexpr StubCallMode kStubMode = StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub;
4062  V<WordPtr> converted_index;
4063  compiler::BoundsCheckResult bounds_check_result;
4064  std::tie(converted_index, bounds_check_result) = BoundsCheckMem(
4065  imm.memory,
4066  opcode == kExprI32AtomicWait ? MemoryRepresentation::Int32()
4067  : MemoryRepresentation::Int64(),
4068  index, imm.offset, compiler::EnforceBoundsCheck::kNeedsBoundsCheck,
4069  compiler::AlignmentCheck::kYes);
4070 
4071  OpIndex effective_offset = __ WordPtrAdd(converted_index, imm.offset);
4072  V<BigInt> bigint_timeout = BuildChangeInt64ToBigInt(timeout, kStubMode);
4073 
4074  if (opcode == kExprI32AtomicWait) {
4075  result->op =
4076  CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmI32AtomicWait>(
4077  decoder, {__ Word32Constant(imm.memory->index), effective_offset,
4078  expected, bigint_timeout});
4079  return;
4080  }
4081  DCHECK_EQ(opcode, kExprI64AtomicWait);
4082  V<BigInt> bigint_expected = BuildChangeInt64ToBigInt(expected, kStubMode);
4083  result->op =
4084  CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmI64AtomicWait>(
4085  decoder, {__ Word32Constant(imm.memory->index), effective_offset,
4086  bigint_expected, bigint_timeout});
4087  }
4088 
4089  void AtomicOp(FullDecoder* decoder, WasmOpcode opcode, const Value args[],
4090  const size_t argc, const MemoryAccessImmediate& imm,
4091  Value* result) {
4092  if (opcode == WasmOpcode::kExprAtomicNotify) {
4093  return AtomicNotify(decoder, imm, args[0].op, args[1].op, result);
4094  }
4095  if (opcode == WasmOpcode::kExprI32AtomicWait ||
4096  opcode == WasmOpcode::kExprI64AtomicWait) {
4097  return AtomicWait(decoder, opcode, imm, args[0].op, args[1].op,
4098  args[2].op, result);
4099  }
4100  using Binop = compiler::turboshaft::AtomicRMWOp::BinOp;
4101  enum OpType { kBinop, kLoad, kStore };
4102  struct AtomicOpInfo {
4103  OpType op_type;
4104  // Initialize with a default value, to allow constexpr constructors.
4105  Binop bin_op = Binop::kAdd;
4106  RegisterRepresentation in_out_rep;
4107  MemoryRepresentation memory_rep;
4108 
4109  constexpr AtomicOpInfo(Binop bin_op, RegisterRepresentation in_out_rep,
4110  MemoryRepresentation memory_rep)
4111  : op_type(kBinop),
4112  bin_op(bin_op),
4113  in_out_rep(in_out_rep),
4114  memory_rep(memory_rep) {}
4115 
4116  constexpr AtomicOpInfo(OpType op_type, RegisterRepresentation in_out_rep,
4117  MemoryRepresentation memory_rep)
4118  : op_type(op_type), in_out_rep(in_out_rep), memory_rep(memory_rep) {}
4119 
4120  static constexpr AtomicOpInfo Get(wasm::WasmOpcode opcode) {
4121  switch (opcode) {
4122 #define CASE_BINOP(OPCODE, BINOP, RESULT, INPUT) \
4123  case WasmOpcode::kExpr##OPCODE: \
4124  return AtomicOpInfo(Binop::k##BINOP, RegisterRepresentation::RESULT(), \
4125  MemoryRepresentation::INPUT());
4126 #define RMW_OPERATION(V) \
4127  V(I32AtomicAdd, Add, Word32, Uint32) \
4128  V(I32AtomicAdd8U, Add, Word32, Uint8) \
4129  V(I32AtomicAdd16U, Add, Word32, Uint16) \
4130  V(I32AtomicSub, Sub, Word32, Uint32) \

4135  V(I32AtomicAnd16U, And, Word32, Uint16) \

4137  V(I32AtomicOr8U, Or, Word32, Uint8) \
4138  V(I32AtomicOr16U, Or, Word32, Uint16) \
4139  V(I32AtomicXor, Xor, Word32, Uint32) \

4141  V(I32AtomicXor16U, Xor, Word32, Uint16) \

4151  V(I64AtomicAdd32U, Add, Word64, Uint32) \
4152  V(I64AtomicSub, Sub, Word64, Uint64) \

4154  V(I64AtomicSub16U, Sub, Word64, Uint16) \

4158  V(I64AtomicAnd16U, And, Word64, Uint16) \
4159  V(I64AtomicAnd32U, And, Word64, Uint32) \
4160  V(I64AtomicOr, Or, Word64, Uint64) \
4161  V(I64AtomicOr8U, Or, Word64, Uint8) \
4162  V(I64AtomicOr16U, Or, Word64, Uint16) \
4163  V(I64AtomicOr32U, Or, Word64, Uint32) \
4164  V(I64AtomicXor, Xor, Word64, Uint64) \
4165  V(I64AtomicXor8U, Xor, Word64, Uint8) \
4166  V(I64AtomicXor16U, Xor, Word64, Uint16) \
4167  V(I64AtomicXor32U, Xor, Word64, Uint32) \

4180 #define CASE_LOAD(OPCODE, RESULT, INPUT) \
4181  case WasmOpcode::kExpr##OPCODE: \
4182  return AtomicOpInfo(kLoad, RegisterRepresentation::RESULT(), \
4183  MemoryRepresentation::INPUT());
4184 #define LOAD_OPERATION(V) \
