4196  case WasmOpcode::kExpr##OPCODE: \
4197  return AtomicOpInfo(kStore, RegisterRepresentation::INPUT(), \
4198  MemoryRepresentation::OUTPUT());
4199 #define STORE_OPERATION(V) \
4200  V(I32AtomicStore, Word32, Uint32) \
4201  V(I32AtomicStore16U, Word32, Uint16) \
4202  V(I32AtomicStore8U, Word32, Uint8) \
4203  V(I64AtomicStore, Word64, Uint64) \
4204  V(I64AtomicStore32U, Word64, Uint32) \
4205  V(I64AtomicStore16U, Word64, Uint16) \
4206  V(I64AtomicStore8U, Word64, Uint8)
4207  STORE_OPERATION(CASE_STORE)
4208 #undef STORE_OPERATION_OPERATION
4209 #undef CASE_STORE
4210  default:
4211  UNREACHABLE();
4212  }
4213  }
4214  };
4215 
4216  AtomicOpInfo info = AtomicOpInfo::Get(opcode);
4217  V<WordPtr> index;
4218  compiler::BoundsCheckResult bounds_check_result;
4219  std::tie(index, bounds_check_result) =
4220  BoundsCheckMem(imm.memory, info.memory_rep, args[0].op, imm.offset,
4221  compiler::EnforceBoundsCheck::kCanOmitBoundsCheck,
4222  compiler::AlignmentCheck::kYes);
4223  // MemoryAccessKind::kUnaligned is impossible due to explicit aligment
4224  // check.
4225  MemoryAccessKind access_kind =
4226  bounds_check_result == compiler::BoundsCheckResult::kTrapHandler
4227  ? MemoryAccessKind::kProtectedByTrapHandler
4228  : MemoryAccessKind::kNormal;
4229 
4230  if (info.op_type == kBinop) {
4231  if (info.bin_op == Binop::kCompareExchange) {
4232  result->op = __ AtomicCompareExchange(
4233  MemBuffer(imm.memory->index, imm.offset), index, args[1].op,
4234  args[2].op, info.in_out_rep, info.memory_rep, access_kind,
4235  RegisterRepresentation::WordPtr());
4236  return;
4237  }
4238  result->op = __ AtomicRMW(MemBuffer(imm.memory->index, imm.offset), index,
4239  args[1].op, info.bin_op, info.in_out_rep,
4240  info.memory_rep, access_kind,
4241  RegisterRepresentation::WordPtr());
4242  return;
4243  }
4244  if (info.op_type == kStore) {
4245  OpIndex value = args[1].op;
4246  if (info.in_out_rep == RegisterRepresentation::Word64() &&
4247  info.memory_rep != MemoryRepresentation::Uint64()) {
4248  value = __ TruncateWord64ToWord32(value);
4249  }
4250 #ifdef V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN
4251  // Reverse the value bytes before storing.
4252  DCHECK(info.in_out_rep == RegisterRepresentation::Word32() ||
4253  info.in_out_rep == RegisterRepresentation::Word64());
4254  wasm::ValueType wasm_type =
4255  info.in_out_rep == RegisterRepresentation::Word32() ? wasm::kWasmI32
4256  : wasm::kWasmI64;
4257  value = BuildChangeEndiannessStore(
4258  value, info.memory_rep.ToMachineType().representation(), wasm_type);
4259 #endif
4260  __ Store(MemBuffer(imm.memory->index, imm.offset), index, value,
4261  access_kind == MemoryAccessKind::kProtectedByTrapHandler
4262  ? LoadOp::Kind::Protected().Atomic()
4263  : LoadOp::Kind::RawAligned().Atomic(),
4264  info.memory_rep, compiler::kNoWriteBarrier);
4265  return;
4266  }
4267  DCHECK_EQ(info.op_type, kLoad);
4268  RegisterRepresentation loaded_value_rep = info.in_out_rep;
4269 #if V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN
4270  // Do not sign-extend / zero-extend the value to 64 bits as the bytes need
4271  // to be reversed first to keep little-endian load / store semantics. Still
4272  // extend for 1 byte loads as it doesn't require reversing any bytes.
4273  bool needs_zero_extension_64 = false;
4274  if (info.in_out_rep == RegisterRepresentation::Word64() &&
4275  info.memory_rep.SizeInBytes() < 8 &&
4276  info.memory_rep.SizeInBytes() != 1) {
4277  needs_zero_extension_64 = true;
4278  loaded_value_rep = RegisterRepresentation::Word32();
4279  }
4280 #endif
4281  result->op =
4282  __ Load(MemBuffer(imm.memory->index, imm.offset), index,
4283  access_kind == MemoryAccessKind::kProtectedByTrapHandler
4284  ? LoadOp::Kind::Protected().Atomic()
4285  : LoadOp::Kind::RawAligned().Atomic(),
4286  info.memory_rep, loaded_value_rep);
4287 
4288 #ifdef V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN
4289  // Reverse the value bytes after load.
4290  DCHECK(info.in_out_rep == RegisterRepresentation::Word32() ||
4291  info.in_out_rep == RegisterRepresentation::Word64());
4292  wasm::ValueType wasm_type =
4293  info.in_out_rep == RegisterRepresentation::Word32() ? wasm::kWasmI32
4294  : wasm::kWasmI64;
4295  result->op = BuildChangeEndiannessLoad(
4296  result->op, info.memory_rep.ToMachineType(), wasm_type);
4297 
4298  if (needs_zero_extension_64) {
4299  result->op = __ ChangeUint32ToUint64(result->op);
4300  }
4301 #endif
4302  }
4303 
4304  void AtomicFence(FullDecoder* decoder) {
4305  __ MemoryBarrier(AtomicMemoryOrder::kSeqCst);
4306  }
4307 
4308  void MemoryInit(FullDecoder* decoder, const MemoryInitImmediate& imm,
4309  const Value& dst, const Value& src, const Value& size) {
4310  V<WordPtr> dst_uintptr = MemoryAddressToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(
4311  imm.memory.memory->address_type, dst.op);
4312  DCHECK_EQ(size.type, kWasmI32);
4313  auto sig = FixedSizeSignature<MachineType>::Returns(MachineType::Int32())
4314  .Params(MachineType::Pointer(), MachineType::Uint32(),
4315  MachineType::UintPtr(), MachineType::Uint32(),
4316  MachineType::Uint32(), MachineType::Uint32());
4317  // TODO(14616): Fix sharedness.
4318  V<Word32> result =
4319  CallC(&sig, ExternalReference::wasm_memory_init(),
4320  {__ BitcastHeapObjectToWordPtr(trusted_instance_data(false)),
4321  __ Word32Constant(imm.memory.index), dst_uintptr, src.op,
4322  __ Word32Constant(imm.data_segment.index), size.op});
4323  __ TrapIfNot(result, TrapId::kTrapMemOutOfBounds);
4324  }
4325 
4326  void InlineMemCopy(const WasmMemory* dst_memory, const WasmMemory* src_memory,
4327  V<WordPtr> dst_offset, V<WordPtr> src_offset,
4328  V<WordPtr> size_op, int32_t bytes_to_copy) {
4329  if (dst_memory->index == src_memory->index) {
4330  // Bounds check the read and write from the same memory.
4331  V<WordPtr> mem_size = MemSize(src_memory->index);
4332  V<WordPtr> offset_limit = __ WordPtrSub(mem_size, size_op);
4333  __ TrapIfNot(__ Word32BitwiseAnd(
4334  __ Word32BitwiseAnd(
4335  __ UintPtrLessThanOrEqual(src_offset, offset_limit),
4336  __ UintPtrLessThanOrEqual(dst_offset, offset_limit)),
4337  __ UintPtrLessThanOrEqual(size_op, mem_size)),
4338  TrapId::kTrapMemOutOfBounds);
4339  } else {
4340  // Insert bounds checks for src and dst memories.
4341  auto BoundsCheck = [this](const WasmMemory* memory, V<WordPtr> offset,
4342  V<WordPtr> size_op) {
4343  V<WordPtr> mem_size = MemSize(memory->index);
4344  V<WordPtr> offset_limit = __ WordPtrSub(mem_size, size_op);
4345  __ TrapIfNot(__ Word32BitwiseAnd(
4346  __ UintPtrLessThanOrEqual(size_op, mem_size),
4347  __ UintPtrLessThanOrEqual(offset, offset_limit)),
4348  TrapId::kTrapMemOutOfBounds);
4349  };
4350  BoundsCheck(src_memory, src_offset, size_op);
4351  BoundsCheck(dst_memory, dst_offset, size_op);
4352  }
4353 
4354  // We've performed the bounds check above.
4355  constexpr auto strategy = compiler::BoundsCheckResult::kDynamicallyChecked;
4356 
4357  // Calculate the effective addresses of src and dst.
4358  V<WordPtr> src_mem_start = MemStart(src_memory->index);
4359  V<WordPtr> dst_mem_start = MemStart(dst_memory->index);
4360  V<WordPtr> src_base = __ WordPtrAdd(src_mem_start, src_offset);
4361  V<WordPtr> dst_base = __ WordPtrAdd(dst_mem_start, dst_offset);
4362 
4363  // Try to use the largest types first for the transfer.
4364  base::SmallVector<MemoryRepresentation, 5> memory_reps;
4365  if (CpuFeatures::SupportsWasmSimd128()) {
4366  memory_reps = base::SmallVector<MemoryRepresentation, 5>(
4367  {MemoryRepresentation::Simd128(), MemoryRepresentation::Uint64(),
4368  MemoryRepresentation::Uint32(), MemoryRepresentation::Uint16(),
4369  MemoryRepresentation::Uint8()});
4370  } else {
4371  memory_reps = base::SmallVector<MemoryRepresentation, 5>(
4372  {MemoryRepresentation::Uint64(), MemoryRepresentation::Uint32(),
4373  MemoryRepresentation::Uint16(), MemoryRepresentation::Uint8()});
4374  }
4375 
4376  // Load all of the data into registers.
4377  base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 16> loads;
4378  int32_t load_bytes_remaining = bytes_to_copy;
4379  int32_t load_offset = 0;
4380  for (MemoryRepresentation mem_rep : memory_reps) {
4381  RegisterRepresentation result_rep = mem_rep.ToRegisterRepresentation();
4382  LoadOp::Kind load_kind = GetMemoryAccessKind(mem_rep, strategy);
4383  DCHECK_EQ(load_kind, LoadOp::Kind::RawAligned().NotLoadEliminable());
4384  uint8_t bytes_per_load = mem_rep.SizeInBytes();
4385  unsigned num_loads = load_bytes_remaining / mem_rep.SizeInBytes();
4386  for (unsigned i = 0; i < num_loads; ++i) {
4387  loads.push_back(__ Load(src_base, OpIndex::Invalid(), load_kind,
4388  mem_rep, result_rep, load_offset));
4389  load_offset += bytes_per_load;
4390  load_bytes_remaining -= bytes_per_load;
4391  }
4392  }
4393 
4394  // Copy to the destination.
4395  int32_t store_bytes_remaining = bytes_to_copy;
4396  int32_t store_offset = 0;
4397  unsigned store_index = 0;
4398  for (MemoryRepresentation mem_rep : memory_reps) {
4399  StoreOp::Kind store_kind = GetMemoryAccessKind(mem_rep, strategy);
4400  DCHECK_EQ(store_kind, StoreOp::Kind::RawAligned().NotLoadEliminable());
4401  uint8_t bytes_per_store = mem_rep.SizeInBytes();
4402  unsigned num_stores = store_bytes_remaining / mem_rep.SizeInBytes();
4403  for (unsigned i = 0; i < num_stores; ++i) {
4404  __ Store(dst_base, OpIndex::Invalid(), loads[store_index], store_kind,
4405  mem_rep, compiler::kNoWriteBarrier, store_offset);
4406  ++store_index;
4407  store_offset += bytes_per_store;
4408  store_bytes_remaining -= bytes_per_store;
4409  }
4410  }
4411  DCHECK_EQ(load_bytes_remaining, 0);
4412  DCHECK_EQ(store_bytes_remaining, 0);
4413  DCHECK_EQ(load_offset, store_offset);
4414  DCHECK_EQ(store_index, loads.size());
4415  }
4416 
4417  void MemoryCopy(FullDecoder* decoder, const MemoryCopyImmediate& imm,
4418  const Value& dst, const Value& src, const Value& size) {
4419  const WasmMemory* dst_memory = imm.memory_dst.memory;
4420  const WasmMemory* src_memory = imm.memory_src.memory;
4421  V<WordPtr> dst_offset =
4422  MemoryAddressToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(dst_memory->address_type, dst.op);
4423  V<WordPtr> src_offset =
4424  MemoryAddressToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(src_memory->address_type, src.op);
4425  AddressType min_address_type =
4426  dst_memory->is_memory64() && src_memory->is_memory64()
4427  ? AddressType::kI64
4428  : AddressType::kI32;
4429  V<WordPtr> size_op =
4430  MemoryAddressToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(min_address_type, size.op);
4431 
4432  // If we're copying a small, constant, number of bytes then perform the
4433  // copy inline instead of making a call. Only do this when unaligned
4434  // accesses are supported and only when we have 64-bit support, otherwise
4435  // the register pressure will likely be too high.
4436 #ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_64_BIT
4437  DCHECK_IMPLIES(!size.op.valid(), __ generating_unreachable_operations());
4438  if ((v8_flags.wasm_memcpy_inlining) &&
4439  !__ generating_unreachable_operations()) {
4440  static constexpr uint32_t kMaxInlineBytes = 112;
4441  if (SupportedOperations::HasFullUnalignedSupport()) {
4442  auto const_size =
4443  __ output_graph().Get(size.op).template TryCast<ConstantOp>();
4444  if (const_size && const_size->integral() <= kMaxInlineBytes) {
4445  InlineMemCopy(dst_memory, src_memory, dst_offset, src_offset, size_op,
4446  static_cast<int32_t>(const_size->integral()));
4447  return;
4448  }
4449  }
4450  }
4451 #endif // V8_TARGET_ARCH_64_BIT
4452 
4453  auto sig = FixedSizeSignature<MachineType>::Returns(MachineType::Int32())
4454  .Params(MachineType::Pointer(), MachineType::Uint32(),
4455  MachineType::Uint32(), MachineType::UintPtr(),
4456  MachineType::UintPtr(), MachineType::UintPtr());
4457  // TODO(14616): Fix sharedness.
4458  V<Word32> result =
4459  CallC(&sig, ExternalReference::wasm_memory_copy(),
4460  {__ BitcastHeapObjectToWordPtr(trusted_instance_data(false)),
4461  __ Word32Constant(imm.memory_dst.index),
4462  __ Word32Constant(imm.memory_src.index), dst_offset, src_offset,
4463  size_op});
4464  __ TrapIfNot(result, TrapId::kTrapMemOutOfBounds);
4465  }
4466 
4467  void MemoryFill(FullDecoder* decoder, const MemoryIndexImmediate& imm,
4468  const Value& dst, const Value& value, const Value& size) {
4469  AddressType address_type = imm.memory->address_type;
4470  V<WordPtr> dst_uintptr =
4471  MemoryAddressToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(address_type, dst.op);
4472  V<WordPtr> size_uintptr =
4473  MemoryAddressToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(address_type, size.op);
4474  auto sig = FixedSizeSignature<MachineType>::Returns(MachineType::Int32())
4475  .Params(MachineType::Pointer(), MachineType::Uint32(),
4476  MachineType::UintPtr(), MachineType::Uint8(),
4477  MachineType::UintPtr());
4478  // TODO(14616): Fix sharedness.
4479  V<Word32> result = CallC(
4480  &sig, ExternalReference::wasm_memory_fill(),
4481  {__ BitcastHeapObjectToWordPtr(trusted_instance_data(false)),
4482  __ Word32Constant(imm.index), dst_uintptr, value.op, size_uintptr});
4483 
4484  __ TrapIfNot(result, TrapId::kTrapMemOutOfBounds);
4485  }

4487  void DataDrop(FullDecoder* decoder, const IndexImmediate& imm) {
4488  // TODO(14616): Data segments aren't available during streaming compilation.
4489  // Discussion: github.com/WebAssembly/shared-everything-threads/issues/83
4490  bool shared = decoder->enabled_.has_shared() &&
4491  decoder->module_->data_segments[imm.index].shared;
4492  V<FixedUInt32Array> data_segment_sizes = LOAD_IMMUTABLE_INSTANCE_FIELD(
4493  trusted_instance_data(shared), DataSegmentSizes,
4494  MemoryRepresentation::TaggedPointer());
4495  __ Store(data_segment_sizes, __ Word32Constant(0),
4496  StoreOp::Kind::TaggedBase(), MemoryRepresentation::Int32(),
4497  compiler::kNoWriteBarrier,
4498  FixedUInt32Array::OffsetOfElementAt(imm.index));
4499  }

4501  void TableGet(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& index, Value* result,
4502  const TableIndexImmediate& imm) {
4503  V<WasmTableObject> table = LoadTable(decoder, imm);
4504  V<Smi> size_smi = __ Load(table, LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase(),
4505  MemoryRepresentation::TaggedSigned(),
4506  WasmTableObject::kCurrentLengthOffset);
4507  V<WordPtr> index_wordptr =
4508  TableAddressToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(imm.table->address_type, index.op);
4509  DCHECK_GE(kSmiMaxValue, wasm::max_table_size());
4510  V<Word32> in_bounds = __ UintPtrLessThan(
4511  index_wordptr, __ ChangeUint32ToUintPtr(__ UntagSmi(size_smi)));
4512  __ TrapIfNot(in_bounds, TrapId::kTrapTableOutOfBounds);
4513  V<FixedArray> entries = __ Load(table, LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase(),
4514  MemoryRepresentation::TaggedPointer(),
4515  WasmTableObject::kEntriesOffset);
4516  OpIndex entry = __ LoadFixedArrayElement(entries, index_wordptr);
4517 
4518  if (imm.table->type.ref_type_kind() == RefTypeKind::kFunction) {
4519  // If the entry has map type Tuple2, call WasmFunctionTableGet which will
4520  // initialize the function table entry.
4521  Label<Object> resolved(&asm_);
4522  Label<> call_runtime(&asm_);
4523  // The entry is a WasmFuncRef, WasmNull, or Tuple2. Hence
4524  // it is safe to cast it to HeapObject.
4525  V<Map> entry_map = __ LoadMapField(V<HeapObject>::Cast(entry));
4526  V<Word32> instance_type = __ LoadInstanceTypeField(entry_map);
4527  GOTO_IF(
4528  UNLIKELY(__ Word32Equal(instance_type, InstanceType::TUPLE2_TYPE)),
4529  call_runtime);
4530  // Otherwise the entry is WasmFuncRef or WasmNull; we are done.
4531  GOTO(resolved, entry);
4532 
4533  BIND(call_runtime);
4534  bool extract_shared_data = !shared_ && imm.table->shared;
4535  GOTO(resolved,
4536  CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<
4537  BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmFunctionTableGet>(
4538  decoder, {__ IntPtrConstant(imm.index), index_wordptr,
4539  __ Word32Constant(extract_shared_data ? 1 : 0)}));
4540 
4541  BIND(resolved, resolved_entry);
4542  result->op = resolved_entry;
4543  } else {
4544  result->op = entry;
4545  }
4546  result->op = AnnotateResultIfReference(result->op, imm.table->type);
4547  }

4549  void TableSet(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& index, const Value& value,
4550  const TableIndexImmediate& imm) {
4551  bool extract_shared_data = !shared_ && imm.table->shared;
4552 
4553  V<WordPtr> index_wordptr =
4554  TableAddressToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(imm.table->address_type, index.op);
4555 
4556  if (imm.table->type.ref_type_kind() == RefTypeKind::kFunction) {
4557  CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmTableSetFuncRef>(
4558  decoder, {__ IntPtrConstant(imm.index),
4559  __ Word32Constant(extract_shared_data ? 1 : 0),
4560  index_wordptr, value.op});
4561  } else {
4562  CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmTableSet>(
4563  decoder, {__ IntPtrConstant(imm.index),
4564  __ Word32Constant(extract_shared_data ? 1 : 0),
4565  index_wordptr, value.op});
4566  }
4567  }

4569  void TableInit(FullDecoder* decoder, const TableInitImmediate& imm,
4570  const Value& dst_val, const Value& src_val,
4571  const Value& size_val) {
4572  const WasmTable* table = imm.table.table;
4573  V<WordPtr> dst_wordptr =
4574  TableAddressToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(table->address_type, dst_val.op);
4575  V<Word32> src = src_val.op;
4576  V<Word32> size = size_val.op;
4577  DCHECK_EQ(table->shared, table->shared);
4578  CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmTableInit>(
4579  decoder, {
4580  dst_wordptr,
4581  src,
4582  size,
4583  __ NumberConstant(imm.table.index),
4584  __ NumberConstant(imm.element_segment.index),
4585  __ NumberConstant((!shared_ && table->shared) ? 1 : 0),
4586  });
4587  }

4589  void TableCopy(FullDecoder* decoder, const TableCopyImmediate& imm,
4590  const Value& dst_val, const Value& src_val,
4591  const Value& size_val) {
4592  const WasmTable* dst_table = imm.table_dst.table;
4593  const WasmTable* src_table = imm.table_src.table;
4594  V<WordPtr> dst_wordptr =
4595  TableAddressToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(dst_table->address_type, dst_val.op);
4596  V<WordPtr> src_wordptr =
4597  TableAddressToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(src_table->address_type, src_val.op);
4598  AddressType min_address_type =
4599  dst_table->is_table64() && src_table->is_table64() ? AddressType::kI64
4600  : AddressType::kI32;
4601  V<WordPtr> size_wordptr =
4602  TableAddressToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(min_address_type, size_val.op);
4603  bool table_is_shared = imm.table_dst.table->shared;
4604  // TODO(14616): Is this too restrictive?
4605  DCHECK_EQ(table_is_shared, imm.table_src.table->shared);
4606  CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmTableCopy>(
4607  decoder, {dst_wordptr, src_wordptr, size_wordptr,
4608  __ NumberConstant(imm.table_dst.index),
4609  __ NumberConstant(imm.table_src.index),
4610  __ NumberConstant((!shared_ && table_is_shared) ? 1 : 0)});
4611  }

4613  void TableGrow(FullDecoder* decoder, const TableIndexImmediate& imm,
4614  const Value& value, const Value& delta, Value* result) {
4615  Label<Word32> end(&asm_);
4616  V<WordPtr> delta_wordptr;
4617 
4618  // If `delta` is OOB, return -1.
4619  if (!imm.table->is_table64()) {
4620  delta_wordptr = __ ChangeUint32ToUintPtr(delta.op);
4621  } else if constexpr (Is64()) {
4622  delta_wordptr = delta.op;
4623  } else {
4624  GOTO_IF(UNLIKELY(__ TruncateWord64ToWord32(
4625  __ Word64ShiftRightLogical(delta.op, 32))),
4626  end, __ Word32Constant(-1));
4627  delta_wordptr = V<WordPtr>::Cast(__ TruncateWord64ToWord32(delta.op));
4628  }
4629 
4630  bool extract_shared_data = !shared_ && imm.table->shared;
4631  DCHECK_GE(kSmiMaxValue, wasm::max_table_size());
4632  V<Word32> call_result = __ UntagSmi(
4633  CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmTableGrow>(
4634  decoder, {__ NumberConstant(imm.index), delta_wordptr,
4635  __ Word32Constant(extract_shared_data), value.op}));
4636  GOTO(end, call_result);
4637 
4638  BIND(end, result_i32);
4639  if (imm.table->is_table64()) {
4640  result->op = __ ChangeInt32ToInt64(result_i32);
4641  } else {
4642  result->op = result_i32;
4643  }
4644  }

4646  void TableFill(FullDecoder* decoder, const TableIndexImmediate& imm,
4647  const Value& start, const Value& value, const Value& count) {
4648  V<WordPtr> start_wordptr =
4649  TableAddressToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(imm.table->address_type, start.op);
4650  V<WordPtr> count_wordptr =
4651  TableAddressToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(imm.table->address_type, count.op);
4652  bool extract_shared_data = !shared_ && imm.table->shared;
4653  CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmTableFill>(
4654  decoder,
4655  {start_wordptr, count_wordptr, __ Word32Constant(extract_shared_data),
4656  __ NumberConstant(imm.index), value.op});
4657  }

4662  trusted_instance_data(imm.table->shared), Tables,
4663  MemoryRepresentation::TaggedPointer());

4668  void TableSize(FullDecoder* decoder, const TableIndexImmediate& imm,

4672  table, LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase(), MemoryRepresentation::TaggedSigned(),
4673  WasmTableObject::kCurrentLengthOffset));
4674  if (imm.table->is_table64()) {
4675  result->op = __ ChangeUint32ToUint64(size_word32);

4681  void ElemDrop(FullDecoder* decoder, const IndexImmediate& imm) {
4682  // Note: Contrary to data segments, elem segments occur before the code
4683  // section, so we can be sure that they're available even during streaming
4684  // compilation.
4685  bool shared = decoder->module_->elem_segments[imm.index].shared;
4686  V<FixedArray> elem_segments = LOAD_IMMUTABLE_INSTANCE_FIELD(
4687  trusted_instance_data(shared), ElementSegments,
4688  MemoryRepresentation::TaggedPointer());
4689  __ StoreFixedArrayElement(elem_segments, imm.index,
4690  LOAD_ROOT(EmptyFixedArray),
4691  compiler::kFullWriteBarrier);
4692  }

4694  void StructNew(FullDecoder* decoder, const StructIndexImmediate& imm,
4695  const Value& descriptor, const Value args[], Value* result) {

4698  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < field_count; ++i) {
4699  args_vector[i] = args[i].op;
4700  }
4701  result->op =
4702  StructNewImpl(decoder, imm, descriptor, args_vector.data(), true);
4703  }

4711  args[i] = DefaultValue(field_type);

4714  }

4759 
4760  void StructAtomicRMW(FullDecoder* decoder, WasmOpcode opcode,
4761  const Value& struct_object, const FieldImmediate& field,
4762  const Value& field_value, AtomicMemoryOrder memory_order,
4763  Value* result) {
4764  if (!field.struct_imm.shared) {
4765  // On some architectures atomic operations require aligned accesses while
4766  // unshared objects don't have the required alignment. For simplicity we
4767  // do the same on all platforms and for all rmw operations (even though
4768  // only 64 bit operations should run into alignment problems).
4769  // TODO(mliedtke): Reconsider this if atomic operations on unshared
4770  // objects remain part of the spec proposal.
4771  const StructType* struct_type = field.struct_imm.struct_type;
4772  ValueKind field_kind = struct_type->field(field.field_imm.index).kind();
4773  V<Any> old_value = __ StructGet(
4774  struct_object.op, struct_type, field.struct_imm.index,
4775  field.field_imm.index, true,
4776  struct_object.type.is_nullable() ? compiler::kWithNullCheck
4777  : compiler::kWithoutNullCheck,
4778  {});
4779  result->op = old_value;
4780  V<Any> new_value;
4781  if (field_kind == ValueKind::kI32) {
4782  V<Word32> old = V<Word32>::Cast(old_value);
4783  switch (opcode) {
4784  case kExprStructAtomicAdd:
4785  new_value = __ Word32Add(old, field_value.op);
4786  break;
4787  case kExprStructAtomicSub:
4788  new_value = __ Word32Sub(old, field_value.op);
4789  break;
4790  case kExprStructAtomicAnd:
4791  new_value = __ Word32BitwiseAnd(old, field_value.op);
4792  break;
4793  case kExprStructAtomicOr:
4794  new_value = __ Word32BitwiseOr(old, field_value.op);
4795  break;
4796  case kExprStructAtomicXor:
4797  new_value = __ Word32BitwiseXor(old, field_value.op);
4798  break;
4799  case kExprStructAtomicExchange:
4800  new_value = field_value.op;
4801  break;
4802  default:
4803  UNREACHABLE();
4804  }
4805  } else if (field_kind == ValueKind::kI64) {
4806  V<Word64> old = V<Word64>::Cast(old_value);
4807  switch (opcode) {
4808  case kExprStructAtomicAdd:
4809  new_value = __ Word64Add(old, field_value.op);
4810  break;
4811  case kExprStructAtomicSub:
4812  new_value = __ Word64Sub(old, field_value.op);
4813  break;
4814  case kExprStructAtomicAnd:
4815  new_value = __ Word64BitwiseAnd(old, field_value.op);
4816  break;
4817  case kExprStructAtomicOr:
4818  new_value = __ Word64BitwiseOr(old, field_value.op);
4819  break;
4820  case kExprStructAtomicXor:
4821  new_value = __ Word64BitwiseXor(old, field_value.op);
4822  break;
4823  case kExprStructAtomicExchange:
4824  new_value = field_value.op;
4825  break;
4826  default:
4827  UNREACHABLE();
4828  }
4829  } else {
4830  CHECK(is_reference(field_kind));
4831  CHECK_EQ(opcode, kExprStructAtomicExchange);
4832  new_value = field_value.op;
4833  }
4834  DCHECK(new_value.valid());
4835  __ StructSet(struct_object.op, new_value, struct_type,
4836  field.struct_imm.index, field.field_imm.index,
4837  compiler::kWithoutNullCheck, {});
4838  return;
4839  }
4840 
4841  using BinOp = compiler::turboshaft::StructAtomicRMWOp::BinOp;
4842  BinOp op = ([](WasmOpcode opcode) -> BinOp {
4843  switch (opcode) {
4844  case kExprStructAtomicAdd:
4845  return BinOp::kAdd;
4846  case kExprStructAtomicSub:
4847  return BinOp::kSub;
4848  case kExprStructAtomicAnd:
4849  return BinOp::kAnd;
4850  case kExprStructAtomicOr:
4851  return BinOp::kOr;
4852  case kExprStructAtomicXor:
4853  return BinOp::kXor;
4854  case kExprStructAtomicExchange:
4855  return BinOp::kExchange;
4856  default:
4857  UNIMPLEMENTED();
4858  }
4859  })(opcode);
4860  result->op = __ StructAtomicRMW(
4861  struct_object.op, field_value.op, OpIndex::Invalid(), op,
4862  field.struct_imm.struct_type, field.struct_imm.index,
4863  field.field_imm.index,
4864  struct_object.type.is_nullable() ? compiler::kWithNullCheck
4865  : compiler::kWithoutNullCheck,
4866  memory_order);
4867  }
4868 
4869  void StructAtomicCompareExchange(
4870  FullDecoder* decoder, WasmOpcode opcode, const Value& struct_object,
4871  const FieldImmediate& field, const Value& expected_value,
4872  const Value& new_value, AtomicMemoryOrder memory_order, Value* result) {
4873  const StructType* struct_type = field.struct_imm.struct_type;
4874  ValueKind field_kind = struct_type->field(field.field_imm.index).kind();
4875 
4876  if (field_kind == ValueKind::kRef || field_kind == ValueKind::kRefNull) {
4877  UNIMPLEMENTED();
4878  }
4879 
4880  if (!field.struct_imm.shared && field_kind == ValueKind::kI64) {
4881  // On some architectures atomic operations require aligned accesses while
4882  // unshared objects don't have the required alignment. For simplicity we
4883  // do the same on all platforms.
4884  // TODO(mliedtke): Reconsider this if atomic operations on unshared
4885  // objects remain part of the spec proposal.
4886  V<Word64> old_value = V<Word64>::Cast(__ StructGet(
4887  struct_object.op, struct_type, field.struct_imm.index,
4888  field.field_imm.index, true,
4889  struct_object.type.is_nullable() ? compiler::kWithNullCheck
4890  : compiler::kWithoutNullCheck,
4891  {}));
4892  result->op = old_value;
4893  IF (__ Word64Equal(old_value, expected_value.op)) {
4894  __ StructSet(struct_object.op, new_value.op, struct_type,
4895  field.struct_imm.index, field.field_imm.index,
4896  compiler::kWithoutNullCheck, {});
4897  }
4898  return;
4899  }
4900 
4901  result->op = __ StructAtomicRMW(
4902  struct_object.op, new_value.op, expected_value.op,
4903  compiler::turboshaft::StructAtomicRMWOp::BinOp::kCompareExchange,
4904  field.struct_imm.struct_type, field.struct_imm.index,
4905  field.field_imm.index,
4906  struct_object.type.is_nullable() ? compiler::kWithNullCheck
4907  : compiler::kWithoutNullCheck,
4908  memory_order);
4909  }

4963  void ArrayAtomicRMW(FullDecoder* decoder, WasmOpcode opcode,
4964  const Value& array_obj, const ArrayIndexImmediate& imm,
4965  const Value& index, const Value& value,
4966  AtomicMemoryOrder order, Value* result) {
4967  if (!array_obj.type.is_shared()) {
4968  // On some architectures atomic operations require aligned accesses while
4969  // unshared objects don't have the required alignment. For simplicity we
4970  // do the same on all platforms and for all rmw operations (even though
4971  // only 64 bit operations should run into alignment problems).
4972  // TODO(mliedtke): Reconsider this if atomic operations on unshared
4973  // objects remain part of the spec proposal.
4974  auto array_value = V<WasmArrayNullable>::Cast(array_obj.op);
4975  BoundsCheckArray(array_value, index.op, array_obj.type);
4976  V<Any> old_value =
4977  __ ArrayGet(array_value, index.op, imm.array_type, true, {});
4978  result->op = old_value;
4979  V<Word> new_value;
4980  ValueType element_type = imm.array_type->element_type();
4981  if (element_type == kWasmI32) {
4982  V<Word32> old = V<Word32>::Cast(old_value);
4983  switch (opcode) {
4984  case kExprArrayAtomicAdd:
4985  new_value = __ Word32Add(old, value.op);
4986  break;
4987  case kExprArrayAtomicSub:
4988  new_value = __ Word32Sub(old, value.op);
4989  break;
4990  case kExprArrayAtomicAnd:
4991  new_value = __ Word32BitwiseAnd(old, value.op);
4992  break;
4993  case kExprArrayAtomicOr:
4994  new_value = __ Word32BitwiseOr(old, value.op);
4995  break;
4996  case kExprArrayAtomicXor:
4997  new_value = __ Word32BitwiseXor(old, value.op);
4998  break;
4999  case kExprArrayAtomicExchange:
5000  new_value = value.op;
5001  break;
5002  default:
5003  UNREACHABLE();
5004  }
5005  } else if (element_type == kWasmI64) {
5006  V<Word64> old = V<Word64>::Cast(old_value);
5007  switch (opcode) {
5008  case kExprArrayAtomicAdd:
5009  new_value = __ Word64Add(old, value.op);
5010  break;
5011  case kExprArrayAtomicSub:
5012  new_value = __ Word64Sub(old, value.op);
5013  break;
5014  case kExprArrayAtomicAnd:
5015  new_value = __ Word64BitwiseAnd(old, value.op);
5016  break;
5017  case kExprArrayAtomicOr:
5018  new_value = __ Word64BitwiseOr(old, value.op);
5019  break;
5020  case kExprArrayAtomicXor:
5021  new_value = __ Word64BitwiseXor(old, value.op);
5022  break;
5023  case kExprArrayAtomicExchange:
5024  new_value = value.op;
5025  break;
5026  default:
5027  UNREACHABLE();
5028  }
5029  } else {
5030  CHECK(element_type.is_reference());
5031  CHECK_EQ(opcode, kExprArrayAtomicExchange);
5032  new_value = value.op;
5033  }
5034  DCHECK(new_value.valid());
5035  __ ArraySet(array_value, index.op, new_value,
5036  imm.array_type->element_type(), {});
5037  return;
5038  }
5039 
5040  using BinOp = compiler::turboshaft::ArrayAtomicRMWOp::BinOp;
5041  BinOp op = ([](WasmOpcode opcode) -> BinOp {
5042  switch (opcode) {
5043  case kExprArrayAtomicAdd:
5044  return BinOp::kAdd;
5045  case kExprArrayAtomicSub:
5046  return BinOp::kSub;
5047  case kExprArrayAtomicAnd:
5048  return BinOp::kAnd;
5049  case kExprArrayAtomicOr:
5050  return BinOp::kOr;
5051  case kExprArrayAtomicXor:
5052  return BinOp::kXor;
5053  case kExprArrayAtomicExchange:
5054  return BinOp::kExchange;
5055  default:
5056  UNIMPLEMENTED();
5057  }
5058  })(opcode);
5059  auto array_value = V<WasmArrayNullable>::Cast(array_obj.op);
5060  BoundsCheckArray(array_value, index.op, array_obj.type);
5061  result->op =
5062  __ ArrayAtomicRMW(array_value, index.op, value.op, OpIndex::Invalid(),
5063  op, imm.array_type->element_type(), order);
5064  }
5065 
5066  void ArrayAtomicCompareExchange(FullDecoder* decoder, WasmOpcode opcode,
5067  const Value& array_obj,
5068  const ArrayIndexImmediate& imm,
5069  const Value& index,
5070  const Value& expected_value,
5071  const Value& new_value,
5072  AtomicMemoryOrder order, Value* result) {
5073  auto array_value = V<WasmArrayNullable>::Cast(array_obj.op);
5074  BoundsCheckArray(array_value, index.op, array_obj.type);
5075 
5076  if (imm.array_type->element_type().is_reference()) {
5077  UNIMPLEMENTED();
5078  }
5079 
5080  if (!array_obj.type.is_shared() &&
5081  imm.array_type->element_type() == kWasmI64) {
5082  // On some architectures atomic operations require aligned accesses while
5083  // unshared objects don't have the required alignment. For simplicity we
5084  // do the same on all platforms.
5085  // TODO(mliedtke): Reconsider this if atomic operations on unshared
5086  // objects remain part of the spec proposal.
5087  V<Word64> old_value = V<Word64>::Cast(
5088  __ ArrayGet(array_value, index.op, imm.array_type, true, {}));
5089  result->op = old_value;
5090  IF (__ Word64Equal(old_value, expected_value.op)) {
5091  __ ArraySet(array_value, index.op, new_value.op,
5092  imm.array_type->element_type(), {});
5093  }
5094  return;
5095  }
5096 
5097  result->op = __ ArrayAtomicRMW(
5098  array_value, index.op, new_value.op, expected_value.op,
5099  compiler::turboshaft::ArrayAtomicRMWOp::BinOp::kCompareExchange,
5100  imm.array_type->element_type(), order);
5101  }

5104  result->op = __ ArrayLength(V<WasmArrayNullable>::Cast(array_obj.op),
5105  array_obj.type.is_nullable()
5106  ? compiler::kWithNullCheck
5107  : compiler::kWithoutNullCheck);
5108  }
5109 
5110  void ArrayCopy(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& dst, const Value& dst_index,
5111  const Value& src, const Value& src_index,
5112  const ArrayIndexImmediate& src_imm, const Value& length) {
5113  V<WasmArrayNullable> src_array = V<WasmArrayNullable>::Cast(src.op);
5114  V<WasmArrayNullable> dst_array = V<WasmArrayNullable>::Cast(dst.op);
5115  BoundsCheckArrayWithLength(dst_array, dst_index.op, length.op,
5116  dst.type.is_nullable()
5117  ? compiler::kWithNullCheck
5118  : compiler::kWithoutNullCheck);
5119  BoundsCheckArrayWithLength(src_array, src_index.op, length.op,
5120  src.type.is_nullable()
5121  ? compiler::kWithNullCheck
5122  : compiler::kWithoutNullCheck);
5123 
5124  ValueType element_type = src_imm.array_type->element_type();
5125 
5126  IF_NOT (__ Word32Equal(length.op, 0)) {
5127  // Values determined by test/mjsunit/wasm/array-copy-benchmark.js on x64.
5128  int array_copy_max_loop_length;
5129  switch (element_type.kind()) {
5130  case wasm::kI32:
5131  case wasm::kI64:
5132  case wasm::kI8:
5133  case wasm::kI16:
5134  array_copy_max_loop_length = 20;
5135  break;
5136  case wasm::kF16: // TODO(irezvov): verify the threshold for F16.
5137  case wasm::kF32:
5138  case wasm::kF64:
5139  array_copy_max_loop_length = 35;
5140  break;
5141  case wasm::kS128:
5142  array_copy_max_loop_length = 100;
5143  break;
5144  case wasm::kRef:
5145  case wasm::kRefNull:
5146  array_copy_max_loop_length = 15;
5147  break;
5148  case wasm::kVoid:
5149  case kTop:
5150  case wasm::kBottom:
5151  UNREACHABLE();
5152  }
5153 
5154  IF (__ Uint32LessThan(array_copy_max_loop_length, length.op)) {
5155  // Builtin
5156  MachineType arg_types[]{MachineType::TaggedPointer(),
5157  MachineType::Uint32(),
5158  MachineType::TaggedPointer(),
5159  MachineType::Uint32(), MachineType::Uint32()};
5160  MachineSignature sig(0, 5, arg_types);
5161 
5162  CallC(&sig, ExternalReference::wasm_array_copy(),
5163  {dst_array, dst_index.op, src_array, src_index.op, length.op});
5164  } ELSE {
5165  V<Word32> src_end_index =
5166  __ Word32Sub(__ Word32Add(src_index.op, length.op), 1);
5167 
5168  IF (__ Uint32LessThan(src_index.op, dst_index.op)) {
5169  // Reverse
5170  V<Word32> dst_end_index =
5171  __ Word32Sub(__ Word32Add(dst_index.op, length.op), 1);
5172  ScopedVar<Word32> src_index_loop(this, src_end_index);
5173  ScopedVar<Word32> dst_index_loop(this, dst_end_index);
5174 
5175  WHILE(__ Word32Constant(1)) {
5176  V<Any> value = __ ArrayGet(src_array, src_index_loop,
5177  src_imm.array_type, true, {});
5178  __ ArraySet(dst_array, dst_index_loop, value, element_type, {});
5179 
5180  IF_NOT (__ Uint32LessThan(src_index.op, src_index_loop)) BREAK;
5181 
5182  src_index_loop = __ Word32Sub(src_index_loop, 1);
5183  dst_index_loop = __ Word32Sub(dst_index_loop, 1);
5184  }
5185  } ELSE {
5186  ScopedVar<Word32> src_index_loop(this, src_index.op);
5187  ScopedVar<Word32> dst_index_loop(this, dst_index.op);
5188 
5189  WHILE(__ Word32Constant(1)) {
5190  V<Any> value = __ ArrayGet(src_array, src_index_loop,
5191  src_imm.array_type, true, {});
5192  __ ArraySet(dst_array, dst_index_loop, value, element_type, {});
5193 
5194  IF_NOT (__ Uint32LessThan(src_index_loop, src_end_index)) BREAK;
5195 
5196  src_index_loop = __ Word32Add(src_index_loop, 1);
5197  dst_index_loop = __ Word32Add(dst_index_loop, 1);
5198  }
5199  }
5200  }
5201  }
5202  }
5203 
5204  void ArrayFill(FullDecoder* decoder, ArrayIndexImmediate& imm,
5205  const Value& array, const Value& index, const Value& value,
5206  const Value& length) {
5207  const bool emit_write_barrier =
5208  imm.array_type->element_type().is_reference();
5209  auto array_value = V<WasmArrayNullable>::Cast(array.op);
5210  V<WasmArray> array_not_null = BoundsCheckArrayWithLength(
5211  array_value, index.op, length.op,
5212  array.type.is_nullable() ? compiler::kWithNullCheck
5213  : compiler::kWithoutNullCheck);
5214  ArrayFillImpl(array_not_null, V<Word32>::Cast(index.op),
5215  V<Any>::Cast(value.op), V<Word32>::Cast(length.op),
5216  imm.array_type, emit_write_barrier);
5217  }
5218 
5219  void ArrayNewFixed(FullDecoder* decoder, const ArrayIndexImmediate& array_imm,
5220  const IndexImmediate& length_imm, const Value elements[],
5221  Value* result) {
5222  const wasm::ArrayType* type = array_imm.array_type;
5223  wasm::ValueType element_type = type->element_type();
5224  int element_count = length_imm.index;
5225  // Initialize the array header.
5226  bool shared = decoder->module_->type(array_imm.index).is_shared;
5227  V<Map> rtt = __ RttCanon(managed_object_maps(shared), array_imm.index);
5228  V<WasmArray> array = __ WasmAllocateArray(rtt, element_count, type, shared);
5229  // Initialize all elements.
5230  for (int i = 0; i < element_count; i++) {
5231  __ ArraySet(array, __ Word32Constant(i), elements[i].op, element_type,
5232  {});
5233  }
5234  result->op = array;
5235  }
5236 
5237  void ArrayNewSegment(FullDecoder* decoder,
5238  const ArrayIndexImmediate& array_imm,
5239  const IndexImmediate& segment_imm, const Value& offset,
5240  const Value& length, Value* result) {
5241  bool is_element = array_imm.array_type->element_type().is_reference();
5242  // TODO(14616): Data segments aren't available during streaming compilation.
5243  // Discussion: github.com/WebAssembly/shared-everything-threads/issues/83
5244  bool segment_is_shared =
5245  decoder->enabled_.has_shared() &&
5246  (is_element
5247  ? decoder->module_->elem_segments[segment_imm.index].shared
5248  : decoder->module_->data_segments[segment_imm.index].shared);
5249  // TODO(14616): Add DCHECK that array sharedness is equal to `shared`?
5250  V<WasmArray> result_value =
5251  CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmArrayNewSegment>(
5252  decoder,
5253  {__ Word32Constant(segment_imm.index), offset.op, length.op,
5254  __ SmiConstant(Smi::FromInt(is_element ? 1 : 0)),
5255  __ SmiConstant(Smi::FromInt(!shared_ && segment_is_shared)),
5256  __ RttCanon(managed_object_maps(segment_is_shared),
5257  array_imm.index)});
5258  result->op = __ AnnotateWasmType(result_value, result->type);
5259  }
5260 
5261  void ArrayInitSegment(FullDecoder* decoder,
5262  const ArrayIndexImmediate& array_imm,
5263  const IndexImmediate& segment_imm, const Value& array,
5264  const Value& array_index, const Value& segment_offset,
5265  const Value& length) {
5266  bool is_element = array_imm.array_type->element_type().is_reference();
5267  // TODO(14616): Segments aren't available during streaming compilation.
5268  bool segment_is_shared =
5269  decoder->enabled_.has_shared() &&
5270  (is_element
5271  ? decoder->module_->elem_segments[segment_imm.index].shared
5272  : decoder->module_->data_segments[segment_imm.index].shared);
5273  // TODO(14616): Is this too restrictive?
5274  DCHECK_EQ(segment_is_shared,
5275  decoder->module_->type(array_imm.index).is_shared);
5276  CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmArrayInitSegment>(
5277  decoder,
5278  {array_index.op, segment_offset.op, length.op,
5279  __ SmiConstant(Smi::FromInt(segment_imm.index)),
5280  __ SmiConstant(Smi::FromInt(is_element ? 1 : 0)),
5281  __ SmiConstant(Smi::FromInt((!shared_ && segment_is_shared) ? 1 : 0)),
5282  array.op});
5283  }
5284 
5285  void RefI31(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& input, Value* result) {
5286  if constexpr (SmiValuesAre31Bits()) {
5287  V<Word32> shifted =
5288  __ Word32ShiftLeft(input.op, kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize);
5289  if constexpr (Is64()) {
5290  // The uppermost bits don't matter.
5291  result->op = __ BitcastWord32ToWord64(shifted);
5292  } else {
5293  result->op = shifted;
5294  }
5295  } else {
5296  // Set the topmost bit to sign-extend the second bit. This way,
5297  // interpretation in JS (if this value escapes there) will be the same as
5298  // i31.get_s.
5299  V<WordPtr> input_wordptr = __ ChangeUint32ToUintPtr(input.op);
5300  result->op = __ WordPtrShiftRightArithmetic(
5301  __ WordPtrShiftLeft(input_wordptr, kSmiShiftSize + kSmiTagSize + 1),
5302  1);
5303  }
5304  result->op =
5305  __ AnnotateWasmType(__ BitcastWordPtrToSmi(result->op), result->type);
5306  }
5307 
5308  void I31GetS(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& input, Value* result) {
5309  V<Object> input_non_null = NullCheck(input);
5310  if constexpr (SmiValuesAre31Bits()) {
5311  result->op = __ Word32ShiftRightArithmeticShiftOutZeros(
5312  __ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(__ BitcastTaggedToWordPtr(input_non_null)),
5313  kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize);
5314  } else {
5315  // Topmost bit is already sign-extended.
5316  result->op = __ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(
5317  __ WordPtrShiftRightArithmeticShiftOutZeros(
5318  __ BitcastTaggedToWordPtr(input_non_null),
5319  kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize));
5320  }
5321  }
5322 
5323  void I31GetU(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& input, Value* result) {
5324  V<Object> input_non_null = NullCheck(input);
5325  if constexpr (SmiValuesAre31Bits()) {
5326  result->op = __ Word32ShiftRightLogical(
5327  __ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(__ BitcastTaggedToWordPtr(input_non_null)),
5328  kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize);
5329  } else {
5330  // Topmost bit is sign-extended, remove it.
5331  result->op = __ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(__ WordPtrShiftRightLogical(
5332  __ WordPtrShiftLeft(__ BitcastTaggedToWordPtr(input_non_null), 1),
5333  kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize + 1));
5334  }
5335  }
5336 
5337  void RefGetDesc(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& ref_val, Value* result) {
5338  // Implicit null checks don't cover the map load.
5339  V<Object> ref = NullCheck(ref_val);
5340  V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(ref);
5341  result->op = __ Load(map, LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase().Immutable(),
5342  MemoryRepresentation::TaggedPointer(),
5343  Map::kInstanceDescriptorsOffset);
5344  }
5345 
5346  compiler::ExactOrSubtype GetExactness(FullDecoder* decoder, HeapType target) {
5347  // For exact target types, an exact match is needed for correctness;
5348  // for final target types, it's a performance optimization.
5349  if (target.is_exact() ||
5350  decoder->module_->type(target.ref_index()).is_final) {
5351  return compiler::kExactMatchOnly;
5352  }
5353  return compiler::kMayBeSubtype;
5354  }

5357  Value* result, bool null_succeeds) {
5358  V<Map> rtt = __ RttCanon(managed_object_maps(target.is_shared()),
5359  target.ref_index());
5360  compiler::WasmTypeCheckConfig config{
5361  object.type,
5362  ValueType::RefMaybeNull(target,
5363  null_succeeds ? kNullable : kNonNullable),
5364  GetExactness(decoder, target)};
5365  result->op = __ WasmTypeCheck(object.op, rtt, config);
5366  }

5377  void RefCast(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& object, Value* result) {
5378  if (v8_flags.experimental_wasm_assume_ref_cast_succeeds) {
5379  // TODO(14108): Implement type guards.
5380  Forward(decoder, object, result);
5381  return;
5382  }
5383  ValueType target = result->type;
5384  V<Map> rtt = __ RttCanon(managed_object_maps(target.is_shared()),
5385  target.ref_index());
5386  compiler::WasmTypeCheckConfig config{
5387  object.type, target, GetExactness(decoder, target.heap_type())};
5388  result->op = __ WasmTypeCast(object.op, rtt, config);
5389  }

5498  void StringNewWtf8(FullDecoder* decoder, const MemoryIndexImmediate& imm,
5499  const unibrow::Utf8Variant variant, const Value& offset,
5500  const Value& size, Value* result) {
5501  V<Word32> memory = __ Word32Constant(imm.index);
5502  V<Smi> variant_smi =
5503  __ SmiConstant(Smi::FromInt(static_cast<int>(variant)));
5504  V<WordPtr> index =
5505  MemoryAddressToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(imm.memory->address_type, offset.op);
5506  V<WasmStringRefNullable> result_value =
5507  CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmStringNewWtf8>(
5508  decoder, {index, size.op, memory, variant_smi});
5509  result->op = __ AnnotateWasmType(result_value, result->type);
5510  }
5511 
5512  // TODO(jkummerow): This check would be more elegant if we made
5513  // {ArrayNewSegment} a high-level node that's lowered later.
5514  // Returns the call on success, nullptr otherwise (like `TryCast`).
5515  const CallOp* IsArrayNewSegment(V<Object> array) {
5516  DCHECK_IMPLIES(!array.valid(), __ generating_unreachable_operations());
5517  if (__ generating_unreachable_operations()) return nullptr;
5518  if (const WasmTypeAnnotationOp* annotation =
5519  __ output_graph().Get(array).TryCast<WasmTypeAnnotationOp>()) {
5520  array = annotation->value();
5521  }
5522  if (const DidntThrowOp* didnt_throw =
5523  __ output_graph().Get(array).TryCast<DidntThrowOp>()) {
5524  array = didnt_throw->throwing_operation();
5525  }
5526  const CallOp* call = __ output_graph().Get(array).TryCast<CallOp>();
5527  if (call == nullptr) return nullptr;
5528  uint64_t stub_id{};
5529  if (!OperationMatcher(__ output_graph())
5530  .MatchWasmStubCallConstant(call->callee(), &stub_id)) {
5531  return nullptr;
5532  }
5533  DCHECK_LT(stub_id, static_cast<uint64_t>(Builtin::kFirstBytecodeHandler));
5534  if (stub_id == static_cast<uint64_t>(Builtin::kWasmArrayNewSegment)) {
5535  return call;
5536  }
5537  return nullptr;
5538  }
5539 
5540  V<HeapObject> StringNewWtf8ArrayImpl(FullDecoder* decoder,
5541  const unibrow::Utf8Variant variant,
5542  const Value& array, const Value& start,
5543  const Value& end,
5544  ValueType result_type) {
5545  // Special case: shortcut a sequence "array from data segment" + "string
5546  // from wtf8 array" to directly create a string from the segment.
5547  V<internal::UnionOf<String, WasmNull, Null>> call;
5548  if (const CallOp* array_new = IsArrayNewSegment(array.op)) {
5549  // We can only pass 3 untagged parameters to the builtin (on 32-bit
5550  // platforms). The segment index is easy to tag: if it validated, it must
5551  // be in Smi range.
5552  OpIndex segment_index = array_new->input(1);
5553  int32_t index_val;
5554  OperationMatcher(__ output_graph())
5555  .MatchIntegralWord32Constant(segment_index, &index_val);
5556  V<Smi> index_smi = __ SmiConstant(Smi::FromInt(index_val));
5557  // Arbitrary choice for the second tagged parameter: the segment offset.
5558  OpIndex segment_offset = array_new->input(2);
5559  __ TrapIfNot(
5560  __ Uint32LessThan(segment_offset, __ Word32Constant(Smi::kMaxValue)),
5561  OpIndex::Invalid(), TrapId::kTrapDataSegmentOutOfBounds);
5562  V<Smi> offset_smi = __ TagSmi(segment_offset);
5563  OpIndex segment_length = array_new->input(3);
5564  V<Smi> variant_smi =
5565  __ SmiConstant(Smi::FromInt(static_cast<int32_t>(variant)));
5566  call = CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<
5567  BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmStringFromDataSegment>(
5568  decoder, {segment_length, start.op, end.op, index_smi, offset_smi,
5569  variant_smi});
5570  } else {
5571  // Regular path if the shortcut wasn't taken.
5572  call = CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<
5573  BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmStringNewWtf8Array>(
5574  decoder,
5575  {start.op, end.op, V<WasmArray>::Cast(NullCheck(array)),
5576  __ SmiConstant(Smi::FromInt(static_cast<int32_t>(variant)))});
5577  }
5578  DCHECK_IMPLIES(variant == unibrow::Utf8Variant::kUtf8NoTrap,
5579  result_type.is_nullable());
5580  // The builtin returns a WasmNull for kUtf8NoTrap, so nullable values in
5581  // combination with extern strings are not supported.
5582  DCHECK_NE(result_type, wasm::kWasmExternRef);
5583  return AnnotateAsString(call, result_type);
5584  }

5587  const unibrow::Utf8Variant variant,
5588  const Value& array, const Value& start,
5589  const Value& end, Value* result) {
5590  result->op = StringNewWtf8ArrayImpl(decoder, variant, array, start, end,
5591  result->type);
5592  }

5628  OpIndex StringMeasureWtf8Impl(FullDecoder* decoder,

5630  V<String> string) {

5638  BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmStringMeasureWtf8>(decoder, {string});
5639  case unibrow::Utf8Variant::kUtf8NoTrap:
5640  UNREACHABLE();
5641  }
5642  }

5705  void StringConcat(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& head, const Value& tail,
5706  Value* result) {

5708  V<String> result_value = CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<
5709  BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmStringAdd_CheckNone>(
5710  decoder, native_context,
5711  {V<String>::Cast(NullCheck(head)), V<String>::Cast(NullCheck(tail))});
5712  result->op = __ AnnotateWasmType(result_value, result->type);
5713  }
5714 
5715  V<Word32> StringEqImpl(FullDecoder* decoder, V<String> a, V<String> b,
5716  ValueType a_type, ValueType b_type) {
5717  Label<Word32> done(&asm_);
5718  // Covers "identical string pointer" and "both are null" cases.
5719  GOTO_IF(__ TaggedEqual(a, b), done, __ Word32Constant(1));
5720  if (a_type.is_nullable()) {
5721  GOTO_IF(__ IsNull(a, a_type), done, __ Word32Constant(0));
5722  }
5723  if (b_type.is_nullable()) {
5724  GOTO_IF(__ IsNull(b, b_type), done, __ Word32Constant(0));
5725  }
5726 
5727  // Strings with unequal lengths can't be equal.
5728  V<Word32> a_length =
5729  __ LoadField<Word32>(a, AccessBuilder::ForStringLength());
5730  V<Word32> b_length =
5731  __ LoadField<Word32>(b, AccessBuilder::ForStringLength());
5732  GOTO_IF_NOT(__ Word32Equal(a_length, b_length), done, __ Word32Constant(0));
5733 
5734  // Comparing the strings' hashes before calling the builtin has been tried,
5735  // but isn't likely to be useful unless Wasm gains an ability to trigger
5736  // string hash computation (or internalization, for that matter).
5737 
5738  V<WordPtr> length = __ ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(a_length);
5739  V<Boolean> result =
5740  CallBuiltinByPointer<BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmJSStringEqual>(
5741  decoder, {a, b, length});
5742 
5743  GOTO(done, __ IsRootConstant(result, RootIndex::kTrueValue));
5744 
5745  BIND(done, eq_result);
5746  return eq_result;
5747  }
5748 
5749  void StringEq(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& a, const Value& b,
5750  Value* result) {
5751  result->op = StringEqImpl(decoder, a.op, b.op, a.type, b.type);
5752  }

5776  void StringViewWtf8Encode(FullDecoder* decoder,
5777  const MemoryIndexImmediate& memory,
5778  const unibrow::Utf8Variant variant,
5779  const Value& view, const Value& addr,
5780  const Value& pos, const Value& bytes,
5781  Value* next_pos, Value* bytes_written) {

5783  MemoryAddressToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(memory.memory->address_type, addr.op);
5784  V<Smi> mem_index = __ SmiConstant(Smi::FromInt(memory.index));
5785  V<Smi> utf8 = __ SmiConstant(Smi::FromInt(static_cast<int32_t>(variant)));
5786  OpIndex result = CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<
5787  BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmStringViewWtf8Encode>(
5788  decoder, {address, pos.op, bytes.op,
5789  V<ByteArray>::Cast(NullCheck(view)), mem_index, utf8});
5790  next_pos->op = __ Projection(result, 0, RepresentationFor(next_pos->type));
5791  bytes_written->op =
5792  __ Projection(result, 1, RepresentationFor(bytes_written->type));
5793  }

5807 
5808  V<Word32> GetCodeUnitImpl(FullDecoder* decoder, V<String> string,
5809  V<Word32> offset) {
5810  auto prepare = __ StringPrepareForGetCodeUnit(string);
5811  V<Object> base = __ template Projection<0>(prepare);
5812  V<WordPtr> base_offset = __ template Projection<1>(prepare);
5813  V<Word32> charwidth_shift = __ template Projection<2>(prepare);
5814 
5815  // Bounds check.
5816  V<Word32> length = LoadStringLength(string);
5817  __ TrapIfNot(__ Uint32LessThan(offset, length),
5818  TrapId::kTrapStringOffsetOutOfBounds);
5819 
5820  Label<> onebyte(&asm_);
5821  Label<> bailout(&asm_);
5822  Label<Word32> done(&asm_);
5823  GOTO_IF(UNLIKELY(__ Word32Equal(charwidth_shift,
5824  compiler::kCharWidthBailoutSentinel)),
5825  bailout);
5826  GOTO_IF(__ Word32Equal(charwidth_shift, 0), onebyte);
5827 
5828  // Two-byte.
5829  V<WordPtr> object_offset = __ WordPtrAdd(
5830  __ WordPtrMul(__ ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(offset), 2), base_offset);
5831  // Bitcast the tagged to a wordptr as the offset already contains the
5832  // kHeapObjectTag handling. Furthermore, in case of external strings the
5833  // tagged value is a smi 0, which doesn't really encode a tagged load.
5834  V<WordPtr> base_ptr = __ BitcastTaggedToWordPtr(base);
5835  V<Word32> result_value =
5836  __ Load(base_ptr, object_offset, LoadOp::Kind::RawAligned().Immutable(),
5837  MemoryRepresentation::Uint16());
5838  GOTO(done, result_value);
5839 
5840  // One-byte.
5841  BIND(onebyte);
5842  object_offset = __ WordPtrAdd(__ ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(offset), base_offset);
5843  // Bitcast the tagged to a wordptr as the offset already contains the
5844  // kHeapObjectTag handling. Furthermore, in case of external strings the
5845  // tagged value is a smi 0, which doesn't really encode a tagged load.
5846  base_ptr = __ BitcastTaggedToWordPtr(base);
5847  result_value =
5848  __ Load(base_ptr, object_offset, LoadOp::Kind::RawAligned().Immutable(),
5849  MemoryRepresentation::Uint8());
5850  GOTO(done, result_value);
5851 
5852  BIND(bailout);
5853  GOTO(done, CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<
5854  BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmStringViewWtf16GetCodeUnit>(
5855  decoder, {string, offset}));
5856 
5857  BIND(done, final_result);
5858  // Make sure the original string is kept alive as long as we're operating
5859  // on pointers extracted from it (otherwise e.g. external strings' resources
5860  // might get freed prematurely).
5861  __ Retain(string);
5862  return final_result;
5863  }
5864 
5865  void StringViewWtf16GetCodeUnit(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& view,
5866  const Value& pos, Value* result) {
5867  result->op =
5868  GetCodeUnitImpl(decoder, V<String>::Cast(NullCheck(view)), pos.op);
5869  }
5870 
5871  V<Word32> StringCodePointAt(FullDecoder* decoder, V<String> string,
5872  V<Word32> offset) {
5873  auto prepare = __ StringPrepareForGetCodeUnit(string);
5874  V<Object> base = __ template Projection<0>(prepare);
5875  V<WordPtr> base_offset = __ template Projection<1>(prepare);
5876  V<Word32> charwidth_shift = __ template Projection<2>(prepare);
5877 
5878  // Bounds check.
5879  V<Word32> length = LoadStringLength(string);
5880  __ TrapIfNot(__ Uint32LessThan(offset, length),
5881  TrapId::kTrapStringOffsetOutOfBounds);
5882 
5883  Label<> onebyte(&asm_);
5884  Label<> bailout(&asm_);
5885  Label<Word32> done(&asm_);
5886  GOTO_IF(
5887  __ Word32Equal(charwidth_shift, compiler::kCharWidthBailoutSentinel),
5888  bailout);
5889  GOTO_IF(__ Word32Equal(charwidth_shift, 0), onebyte);
5890 
5891  // Two-byte.
5892  V<WordPtr> object_offset = __ WordPtrAdd(
5893  __ WordPtrMul(__ ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(offset), 2), base_offset);
5894  // Bitcast the tagged to a wordptr as the offset already contains the
5895  // kHeapObjectTag handling. Furthermore, in case of external strings the
5896  // tagged value is a smi 0, which doesn't really encode a tagged load.
5897  V<WordPtr> base_ptr = __ BitcastTaggedToWordPtr(base);
5898  V<Word32> lead =
5899  __ Load(base_ptr, object_offset, LoadOp::Kind::RawAligned().Immutable(),
5900  MemoryRepresentation::Uint16());
5901  V<Word32> is_lead_surrogate =
5902  __ Word32Equal(__ Word32BitwiseAnd(lead, 0xFC00), 0xD800);
5903  GOTO_IF_NOT(is_lead_surrogate, done, lead);
5904  V<Word32> trail_offset = __ Word32Add(offset, 1);
5905  GOTO_IF_NOT(__ Uint32LessThan(trail_offset, length), done, lead);
5906  V<Word32> trail = __ Load(
5907  base_ptr, __ WordPtrAdd(object_offset, __ IntPtrConstant(2)),
5908  LoadOp::Kind::RawAligned().Immutable(), MemoryRepresentation::Uint16());
5909  V<Word32> is_trail_surrogate =
5910  __ Word32Equal(__ Word32BitwiseAnd(trail, 0xFC00), 0xDC00);
5911  GOTO_IF_NOT(is_trail_surrogate, done, lead);
5912  V<Word32> surrogate_bias =
5913  __ Word32Constant(0x10000 - (0xD800 << 10) - 0xDC00);
5914  V<Word32> result = __ Word32Add(__ Word32ShiftLeft(lead, 10),
5915  __ Word32Add(trail, surrogate_bias));
5916  GOTO(done, result);
5917 
5918  // One-byte.
5919  BIND(onebyte);
5920  object_offset = __ WordPtrAdd(__ ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(offset), base_offset);
5921  // Bitcast the tagged to a wordptr as the offset already contains the
5922  // kHeapObjectTag handling. Furthermore, in case of external strings the
5923  // tagged value is a smi 0, which doesn't really encode a tagged load.
5924  base_ptr = __ BitcastTaggedToWordPtr(base);
5925  result =
5926  __ Load(base_ptr, object_offset, LoadOp::Kind::RawAligned().Immutable(),
5927  MemoryRepresentation::Uint8());
5928  GOTO(done, result);
5929 
5930  BIND(bailout);
5931  GOTO(done, CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<
5932  BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmStringCodePointAt>(
5933  decoder, {string, offset}));
5934 
5935  BIND(done, final_result);
5936  // Make sure the original string is kept alive as long as we're operating
5937  // on pointers extracted from it (otherwise e.g. external strings' resources
5938  // might get freed prematurely).
5939  __ Retain(string);
5940  return final_result;
5941  }
