6023  void StringHash(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& string, Value* result) {
6024  V<String> string_val = V<String>::Cast(NullCheck(string));
6025 
6026  Label<> runtime_label(&Asm());
6027  Label<Word32> end_label(&Asm());
6028 
6029  V<Word32> raw_hash = __ template LoadField<Word32>(
6030  string_val, compiler::AccessBuilder::ForNameRawHashField());
6031  V<Word32> hash_not_computed_mask =
6032  __ Word32Constant(static_cast<int32_t>(Name::kHashNotComputedMask));
6033  static_assert(Name::HashFieldTypeBits::kShift == 0);
6034  V<Word32> hash_not_computed =
6035  __ Word32BitwiseAnd(raw_hash, hash_not_computed_mask);
6036  GOTO_IF(hash_not_computed, runtime_label);
6037 
6038  // Fast path if hash is already computed: Decode raw hash value.
6039  static_assert(Name::HashBits::kLastUsedBit == kBitsPerInt - 1);
6040  V<Word32> hash = __ Word32ShiftRightLogical(
6041  raw_hash, static_cast<int32_t>(Name::HashBits::kShift));
6042  GOTO(end_label, hash);
6043 
6044  BIND(runtime_label);
6045  V<Word32> hash_runtime =
6046  CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmStringHash>(
6047  decoder, {string_val});
6048  GOTO(end_label, hash_runtime);
6049 
6050  BIND(end_label, hash_val);
6051  result->op = hash_val;
6052  }
6053 
6054  void Forward(FullDecoder* decoder, const Value& from, Value* to) {
6055  to->op = from.op;
6056  }
6057 
6058  private:
6059  // The InstanceCache caches commonly used fields of the
6060  // WasmTrustedInstanceData.
6061  // We can extend the set of cached fields as needed.
6062  // This caching serves two purposes:
6063  // (1) It makes sure that the respective fields are loaded early on, as
6064  // opposed to within conditional branches, so the values are easily
6065  // reusable.
6066  // (2) It makes sure that the loaded values are actually reused.
6067  // It achieves these effects more reliably and more cheaply than general-
6068  // purpose optimizations could (loop peeling isn't always used; load
6069  // elimination struggles with arbitrary side effects of indexed stores;
6070  // we don't currently have a generic mechanism for hoisting loads out of
6071  // conditional branches).
6072  class InstanceCache {
6073  public:
6074  explicit InstanceCache(Assembler& assembler)
6075  : mem_start_(assembler), mem_size_(assembler), asm_(assembler) {}
6076 
6077  void Initialize(V<WasmTrustedInstanceData> trusted_instance_data,
6078  const WasmModule* mod) {
6079  DCHECK(!trusted_data_.valid()); // Only call {Initialize()} once.
6080  trusted_data_ = trusted_instance_data;
6081  managed_object_maps_ =
6082  __ Load(trusted_instance_data, LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase().Immutable(),
6083  MemoryRepresentation::TaggedPointer(),
6084  WasmTrustedInstanceData::kManagedObjectMapsOffset);
6085  native_context_ =
6086  __ Load(trusted_instance_data, LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase().Immutable(),
6087  MemoryRepresentation::TaggedPointer(),
6088  WasmTrustedInstanceData::kNativeContextOffset);
6089 
6090  if (!mod->memories.empty()) {
6091 #if DEBUG
6092  has_memory_ = true;
6093 #endif
6094  const WasmMemory& mem = mod->memories[0];
6095  memory_can_grow_ = mem.initial_pages != mem.maximum_pages;
6096  // For now, we don't cache the size of shared growable memories.
6097  // If we wanted to support this case, we would have to reload the
6098  // memory size when loop stack checks detect an interrupt request.
6099  // Since memory size caching is particularly important for asm.js,
6100  // which never uses growable or shared memories, this limitation is
6101  // considered acceptable for now.
6102  memory_size_cached_ = !mem.is_shared || !memory_can_grow_;
6103  // Trap handler enabled memories never move.
6104  // Memories that can't grow have no reason to move.
6105  // Shared memories can only be grown in-place.
6106  memory_can_move_ = mem.bounds_checks != kTrapHandler &&
6107  memory_can_grow_ && !mem.is_shared;
6108  memory_is_shared_ = mem.is_shared;
6109  if (memory_size_cached_) {
6110  mem_size_ = LoadMemSize();
6111  }
6112  mem_start_ = LoadMemStart();
6113  }
6114  }
6115 
6116  // TODO(14108): Port the dynamic "cached_memory_index" infrastructure
6117  // from Turbofan.
6118  void ReloadCachedMemory() {
6119  if (memory_can_move()) mem_start_ = LoadMemStart();
6120  if (memory_can_grow_ && memory_size_cached_) mem_size_ = LoadMemSize();
6121  }
6122 
6123  V<WasmTrustedInstanceData> trusted_instance_data() { return trusted_data_; }
6124  V<FixedArray> managed_object_maps() { return managed_object_maps_; }
6125  V<NativeContext> native_context() { return native_context_; }
6126  V<WordPtr> memory0_start() {
6127  DCHECK(has_memory_);
6128  return mem_start_;
6129  }
6130  V<WordPtr> memory0_size() {
6131  DCHECK(has_memory_);
6132  if (!memory_size_cached_) return LoadMemSize();
6133  return mem_size_;
6134  }
6135 
6136  private:
6137  static constexpr uint8_t kUnused = ~uint8_t{0};
6138 
6139  V<WordPtr> LoadMemStart() {
6140  DCHECK(has_memory_);
6141  // In contrast to memory size loads, we can mark memory start loads as
6142  // eliminable: shared memories never move, and non-shared memories can't
6143  // have their start modified by other threads.
6144  LoadOp::Kind kind = LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase();
6145  if (!memory_can_move()) kind = kind.Immutable();
6146  return __ Load(trusted_data_, kind, MemoryRepresentation::UintPtr(),
6147  WasmTrustedInstanceData::kMemory0StartOffset);
6148  }
6149 
6150  V<WordPtr> LoadMemSize() {
6151  DCHECK(has_memory_);
6152  LoadOp::Kind kind = LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase();
6153  if (memory_is_shared_ && memory_can_grow_) {
6154  // Memory size loads should not be load-eliminated as the memory size
6155  // can be modified by another thread.
6156  kind = kind.NotLoadEliminable();
6157  }
6158  if (!memory_can_grow_) kind = kind.Immutable();
6159  return __ Load(trusted_data_, kind, MemoryRepresentation::UintPtr(),
6160  WasmTrustedInstanceData::kMemory0SizeOffset);
6161  }
6162 
6163  bool memory_can_move() { return memory_can_move_; }
6164 
6165  // For compatibility with `__` macro.
6166  Assembler& Asm() { return asm_; }
6167 
6168  // Cached immutable fields (need no Phi nodes):
6169  V<WasmTrustedInstanceData> trusted_data_;
6170  V<FixedArray> managed_object_maps_;
6171  V<NativeContext> native_context_;
6172 
6173  // Cached mutable fields:
6174  ScopedVar<WordPtr> mem_start_;
6175  ScopedVar<WordPtr> mem_size_;
6176 
6177  // Other fields for internal usage.
6178  Assembler& asm_;
6179  bool memory_is_shared_{false};
6180  bool memory_can_grow_{false};
6181  bool memory_can_move_{false};
6182  bool memory_size_cached_{false};
6183 #if DEBUG
6184  bool has_memory_{false};
6185 #endif
6186  };
6187 
6188  enum class CheckForException { kNo, kCatchInThisFrame, kCatchInParentFrame };
6189 
6190  private:
6191  // Holds phi inputs for a specific block. These include SSA values, stack
6192  // merge values, and cached fields from the instance..
6193  // Conceptually, this is a two-dimensional, rectangular array of size
6194  // `phi_count * inputs_per_phi`, since each phi has the same number of inputs,
6195  // namely the number of incoming edges for this block.
6196  class BlockPhis {
6197  public:
6198  // Ctor for regular blocks.
6199  V8_INLINE BlockPhis(FullDecoder* decoder, Merge<Value>* merge)
6200  : incoming_exceptions_(decoder -> zone()) {
6201  // Allocate space and initialize the types of all phis.
6202  uint32_t num_locals = decoder->num_locals();
6203  uint32_t merge_arity = merge != nullptr ? merge->arity : 0;
6204 
6205  phi_count_ = num_locals + merge_arity;
6206  phi_types_ = decoder->zone()->AllocateArray<ValueType>(phi_count_);
6207 
6208  base::Vector<ValueType> locals = decoder->local_types();
6209  std::uninitialized_copy(locals.begin(), locals.end(), phi_types_);
6210  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < merge_arity; i++) {
6211  new (&phi_types_[num_locals + i]) ValueType((*merge)[i].type);
6212  }
6213  AllocatePhiInputs(decoder->zone());
6214  }
6215 
6216  // Consider this "private"; it's next to the constructors (where it's
6217  // called) for context.
6218  void AllocatePhiInputs(Zone* zone) {
6219  // Only reserve some space for the inputs to be added later.
6220  phi_inputs_capacity_total_ = phi_count_ * input_capacity_per_phi_;
6221  phi_inputs_ = zone->AllocateArray<OpIndex>(phi_inputs_capacity_total_);
6222 
6223 #ifdef DEBUG
6224  constexpr uint32_t kNoInputs = 0;
6225  input_count_per_phi_ = std::vector(phi_count_, kNoInputs);
6226 #endif
6227  }
6228 
6229  // Default ctor and later initialization for function returns.
6230  explicit BlockPhis(Zone* zone) : incoming_exceptions_(zone) {}
6231  void InitReturnPhis(base::Vector<const ValueType> return_types) {
6232  // For `return_phis_`, nobody should have inserted into `this` before
6233  // calling `InitReturnPhis`.
6234  DCHECK_EQ(phi_count_, 0);
6235  DCHECK_EQ(inputs_per_phi_, 0);
6236 
6237  uint32_t return_count = static_cast<uint32_t>(return_types.size());
6238  phi_count_ = return_count;
6239  phi_types_ = zone()->AllocateArray<ValueType>(phi_count_);
6240 
6241  std::uninitialized_copy(return_types.begin(), return_types.end(),
6242  phi_types_);
6243  AllocatePhiInputs(zone());
6244  }
6245 
6246  void AddInputForPhi(size_t phi_i, OpIndex input) {
6247  if (V8_UNLIKELY(phi_inputs_total_ >= phi_inputs_capacity_total_)) {
6248  GrowInputsVector();
6249  }
6250 
6251 #ifdef DEBUG
6252  // We rely on adding inputs in the order of phis, i.e.,
6253  // `AddInputForPhi(0, ...); AddInputForPhi(1, ...); ...`.
6254  size_t phi_inputs_start = phi_i * input_capacity_per_phi_;
6255  size_t phi_input_offset_from_start = inputs_per_phi_;
6256  CHECK_EQ(input_count_per_phi_[phi_i]++, phi_input_offset_from_start);
6257  size_t phi_input_offset = phi_inputs_start + phi_input_offset_from_start;
6258  CHECK_EQ(next_phi_input_add_offset_, phi_input_offset);
6259 #endif
6260  new (&phi_inputs_[next_phi_input_add_offset_]) OpIndex(input);
6261 
6262  phi_inputs_total_++;
6263  next_phi_input_add_offset_ += input_capacity_per_phi_;
6264  if (next_phi_input_add_offset_ >= phi_inputs_capacity_total_) {
6265  // We have finished adding the last input for all phis.
6266  inputs_per_phi_++;
6267  next_phi_input_add_offset_ = inputs_per_phi_;
6268 #ifdef DEBUG
6269  EnsureAllPhisHaveSameInputCount();
6270 #endif
6271  }
6272  }
6273 
6274  uint32_t phi_count() const { return phi_count_; }
6275 
6276  ValueType phi_type(size_t phi_i) const { return phi_types_[phi_i]; }
6277 
6278  base::Vector<const OpIndex> phi_inputs(size_t phi_i) const {
6279  size_t phi_inputs_start = phi_i * input_capacity_per_phi_;
6280  return base::VectorOf(&phi_inputs_[phi_inputs_start], inputs_per_phi_);
6281  }
6282 
6283  void AddIncomingException(OpIndex exception) {
6284  incoming_exceptions_.push_back(exception);
6285  }
6286 
6287  base::Vector<const OpIndex> incoming_exceptions() const {
6288  return base::VectorOf(incoming_exceptions_);
6289  }
6290 
6291 #if DEBUG
6292  void DcheckConsistency() { EnsureAllPhisHaveSameInputCount(); }
6293 #endif
6294 
6295  private:
6296  // Invariants:
6297  // The number of phis for a given block (e.g., locals, merged stack values,
6298  // and cached instance fields) is known when constructing the `BlockPhis`
6299  // and doesn't grow afterwards.
6300  // The number of _inputs_ for each phi is however _not_ yet known when
6301  // constructing this, but grows over time as new incoming edges for a given
6302  // block are created.
6303  // After such an edge is created, each phi has the same number of inputs.
6304  // When eventually creating a phi, we also need all inputs layed out
6305  // contiguously.
6306  // Due to those requirements, we write our own little container, see below.
6307 
6308  // First the backing storage:
6309  // Of size `phi_count_`, one type per phi.
6310  ValueType* phi_types_ = nullptr;
6311  // Of size `phi_inputs_capacity_total_ == phi_count_ *
6312  // input_capacity_per_phi_`, of which `phi_inputs_total_ == phi_count_ *
6313  // inputs_per_phi_` are set/initialized. All inputs for a given phi are
6314  // stored contiguously, but between them are uninitialized elements for
6315  // adding new inputs without reallocating.
6316  OpIndex* phi_inputs_ = nullptr;
6317 
6318  // Stored explicitly to save multiplications in the hot `AddInputForPhi()`.
6319  // Also pulled up to be in the same cache-line as `phi_inputs_`.
6320  uint32_t phi_inputs_capacity_total_ = 0; // Updated with `phi_inputs_`.
6321  uint32_t phi_inputs_total_ = 0;
6322  uint32_t next_phi_input_add_offset_ = 0;
6323 
6324  // The dimensions.
6325  uint32_t phi_count_ = 0;
6326  uint32_t inputs_per_phi_ = 0;
6327  static constexpr uint32_t kInitialInputCapacityPerPhi = 2;
6328  uint32_t input_capacity_per_phi_ = kInitialInputCapacityPerPhi;
6329 
6330 #ifdef DEBUG
6331  std::vector<uint32_t> input_count_per_phi_;
6332  void EnsureAllPhisHaveSameInputCount() const {
6333  CHECK_EQ(phi_inputs_total_, phi_count() * inputs_per_phi_);
6334  CHECK_EQ(phi_count(), input_count_per_phi_.size());
6335  CHECK(std::all_of(input_count_per_phi_.begin(),
6336  input_count_per_phi_.end(),
6337  [=, this](uint32_t input_count) {
6338  return input_count == inputs_per_phi_;
6339  }));
6340  }
6341 #endif
6342 
6343  // The number of `incoming_exceptions` is also not known when constructing
6344  // the block, but at least it is only one-dimensional, so we can use a
6345  // simple `ZoneVector`.
6346  ZoneVector<OpIndex> incoming_exceptions_;
6347 
6348  Zone* zone() { return incoming_exceptions_.zone(); }
6349 
6350  V8_NOINLINE V8_PRESERVE_MOST void GrowInputsVector() {
6351  // We should have always initialized some storage, see
6352  // `kInitialInputCapacityPerPhi`.
6353  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(phi_inputs_);
6354  DCHECK_NE(phi_inputs_capacity_total_, 0);
6355 
6356  OpIndex* old_phi_inputs = phi_inputs_;
6357  uint32_t old_input_capacity_per_phi = input_capacity_per_phi_;
6358  uint32_t old_phi_inputs_capacity_total = phi_inputs_capacity_total_;
6359 
6360  input_capacity_per_phi_ *= 2;
6361  phi_inputs_capacity_total_ *= 2;
6362  phi_inputs_ = zone()->AllocateArray<OpIndex>(phi_inputs_capacity_total_);
6363 
6364  // This is essentially a strided copy, where we expand the storage by
6365  // "inserting" unitialized elements in between contiguous stretches of
6366  // inputs belonging to the same phi.
6367 #ifdef DEBUG
6368  EnsureAllPhisHaveSameInputCount();
6369 #endif
6370  for (size_t phi_i = 0; phi_i < phi_count(); ++phi_i) {
6371  const OpIndex* old_begin =
6372  &old_phi_inputs[phi_i * old_input_capacity_per_phi];
6373  const OpIndex* old_end = old_begin + inputs_per_phi_;
6374  OpIndex* begin = &phi_inputs_[phi_i * input_capacity_per_phi_];
6375  std::uninitialized_copy(old_begin, old_end, begin);
6376  }
6377 
6378  zone()->DeleteArray(old_phi_inputs, old_phi_inputs_capacity_total);
6379  }
6380  };
6381 
6382  // Perform a null check if the input type is nullable.
6383  V<Object> NullCheck(const Value& value,
6384  TrapId trap_id = TrapId::kTrapNullDereference) {
6385  V<Object> not_null_value = V<Object>::Cast(value.op);
6386  if (value.type.is_nullable()) {
6387  not_null_value = __ AssertNotNull(value.op, value.type, trap_id);
6388  }
6389  return not_null_value;
6390  }
6391 
6392  // Creates a new block, initializes a {BlockPhis} for it, and registers it
6393  // with block_phis_. We pass a {merge} only if we later need to recover values
6394  // for that merge.
6395  TSBlock* NewBlockWithPhis(FullDecoder* decoder, Merge<Value>* merge) {
6396  TSBlock* block = __ NewBlock();
6397  block_phis_.emplace(block, BlockPhis(decoder, merge));
6398  return block;
6399  }
6400 
6401  // Sets up a control flow edge from the current SSA environment and a stack to
6402  // {block}. The stack is {stack_values} if present, otherwise the current
6403  // decoder stack.
6404  void SetupControlFlowEdge(FullDecoder* decoder, TSBlock* block,
6405  uint32_t drop_values = 0,
6406  V<Object> exception = OpIndex::Invalid(),
6407  Merge<Value>* stack_values = nullptr) {
6408  if (__ current_block() == nullptr) return;
6409  // It is guaranteed that this element exists.
6410  DCHECK_NE(block_phis_.find(block), block_phis_.end());
6411  BlockPhis& phis_for_block = block_phis_.find(block)->second;
6412  uint32_t merge_arity = static_cast<uint32_t>(phis_for_block.phi_count()) -
6413  decoder->num_locals();
6414 
6415  for (size_t i = 0; i < ssa_env_.size(); i++) {
6416  phis_for_block.AddInputForPhi(i, ssa_env_[i]);
6417  }
6418  // We never drop values from an explicit merge.
6419  DCHECK_IMPLIES(stack_values != nullptr, drop_values == 0);
6420  Value* stack_base = merge_arity == 0 ? nullptr
6421  : stack_values != nullptr
6422  ? &(*stack_values)[0]
6423  : decoder->stack_value(merge_arity + drop_values);
6424  for (size_t i = 0; i < merge_arity; i++) {
6425  DCHECK(stack_base[i].op.valid());
6426  phis_for_block.AddInputForPhi(decoder->num_locals() + i,
6427  stack_base[i].op);
6428  }
6429  if (exception.valid()) {
6430  phis_for_block.AddIncomingException(exception);
6431  }
6432  }
6433 
6434  OpIndex MaybePhi(base::Vector<const OpIndex> elements, ValueType type) {
6435  if (elements.empty()) return OpIndex::Invalid();
6436  for (size_t i = 1; i < elements.size(); i++) {
6437  if (elements[i] != elements[0]) {
6438  return __ Phi(elements, RepresentationFor(type));
6439  }
6440  }
6441  return elements[0];
6442  }
6443 
6444  // Binds a block, initializes phis for its SSA environment from its entry in
6445  // {block_phis_}, and sets values to its {merge} (if available) from the
6446  // its entry in {block_phis_}.
6447  void BindBlockAndGeneratePhis(FullDecoder* decoder, TSBlock* tsblock,
6448  Merge<Value>* merge,
6449  OpIndex* exception = nullptr) {
6450  __ Bind(tsblock);
6451  auto block_phis_it = block_phis_.find(tsblock);
6452  DCHECK_NE(block_phis_it, block_phis_.end());
6453  BlockPhis& block_phis = block_phis_it->second;
6454 
6455  uint32_t merge_arity = merge != nullptr ? merge->arity : 0;
6456  DCHECK_EQ(decoder->num_locals() + merge_arity, block_phis.phi_count());
6457 
6458 #ifdef DEBUG
6459  // Check consistency of Phi storage. We do this here rather than inside
6460  // {block_phis.phi_inputs()} to avoid overall O(n) complexity.
6461  block_phis.DcheckConsistency();
6462 #endif
6463 
6464  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < decoder->num_locals(); i++) {
6465  ssa_env_[i] = MaybePhi(block_phis.phi_inputs(i), block_phis.phi_type(i));
6466  }
6467  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < merge_arity; i++) {
6468  uint32_t phi_index = decoder->num_locals() + i;
6469  (*merge)[i].op = MaybePhi(block_phis.phi_inputs(phi_index),
6470  block_phis.phi_type(phi_index));
6471  }
6472  DCHECK_IMPLIES(exception == nullptr,
6473  block_phis.incoming_exceptions().empty());
6474  if (exception != nullptr && !exception->valid()) {
6475  *exception = MaybePhi(block_phis.incoming_exceptions(), kWasmExternRef);
6476  }
6477  block_phis_.erase(block_phis_it);
6478  }
6479 
6480  V<Any> DefaultValue(ValueType type) {
6481  switch (type.kind()) {
6482  case kI8:
6483  case kI16:
6484  case kI32:
6485  return __ Word32Constant(int32_t{0});
6486  case kI64:
6487  return __ Word64Constant(int64_t{0});
6488  case kF16:
6489  case kF32:
6490  return __ Float32Constant(0.0f);
6491  case kF64:
6492  return __ Float64Constant(0.0);
6493  case kRefNull:
6494  return __ Null(type);
6495  case kS128: {
6496  uint8_t value[kSimd128Size] = {};
6497  return __ Simd128Constant(value);
6498  }
6499  case kVoid:
6500  case kRef:
6501  case kTop:
6502  case kBottom:
6503  UNREACHABLE();
6504  }
6505  }
6506 
6507  private:
6508  V<FrameState> CreateFrameState(FullDecoder* decoder,
6509  const FunctionSig* callee_sig,
6510  const Value* func_ref_or_index,
6511  const Value args[]) {
6512  compiler::turboshaft::FrameStateData::Builder builder;
6513  if (parent_frame_state_.valid()) {
6514  builder.AddParentFrameState(parent_frame_state_.value());
6515  }
6516  // The first input is the closure for JS. (The instruction selector will
6517  // just skip this input as the liftoff frame doesn't have a closure.)
6518  V<Object> dummy_tagged = __ SmiZeroConstant();
6519  builder.AddInput(MachineType::AnyTagged(), dummy_tagged);
6520  // Add the parameters.
6521  size_t param_count = decoder->sig_->parameter_count();
6522  for (size_t i = 0; i < param_count; ++i) {
6523  builder.AddInput(decoder->sig_->GetParam(i).machine_type(), ssa_env_[i]);
6524  }
6525  // Add the context. Wasm doesn't have a JS context, so this is another
6526  // value skipped by the instruction selector.
6527  builder.AddInput(MachineType::AnyTagged(), dummy_tagged);
6528 
6529  // Add the wasm locals.
6530  for (size_t i = param_count; i < ssa_env_.size(); ++i) {
6531  builder.AddInput(
6532  decoder->local_type(static_cast<uint32_t>(i)).machine_type(),
6533  ssa_env_[i]);
6534  }
6535  // Add the wasm stack values.
6536  // Note that the decoder stack is already in the state after the call, i.e.
6537  // the callee and the arguments were already popped from the stack and the
6538  // returns are pushed. Therefore skip the results and manually add the
6539  // call_ref stack values.
6540  for (int32_t i = decoder->stack_size();
6541  i > static_cast<int32_t>(callee_sig->return_count()); --i) {
6542  Value* val = decoder->stack_value(i);
6543  builder.AddInput(val->type.machine_type(), val->op);
6544  }
6545  // Add the call_ref or call_indirect stack values.
6546  if (args != nullptr) {
6547  for (const Value& arg :
6548  base::VectorOf(args, callee_sig->parameter_count())) {
6549  builder.AddInput(arg.type.machine_type(), arg.op);
6550  }
6551  }
6552  if (func_ref_or_index) {
6553  builder.AddInput(func_ref_or_index->type.machine_type(),
6554  func_ref_or_index->op);
6555  }
6556  // The call_ref (callee) or the table index.
6557  const size_t kExtraLocals = func_ref_or_index != nullptr ? 1 : 0;
6558  size_t wasm_local_count = ssa_env_.size() - param_count;
6559  size_t local_count = kExtraLocals + decoder->stack_size() +
6560  wasm_local_count - callee_sig->return_count();
6561  local_count += args != nullptr ? callee_sig->parameter_count() : 0;
6562  Zone* zone = Asm().data()->compilation_zone();
6563  auto* function_info = zone->New<compiler::FrameStateFunctionInfo>(
6564  compiler::FrameStateType::kLiftoffFunction,
6565  static_cast<uint16_t>(param_count), 0, static_cast<int>(local_count),
6566  IndirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo>(), kNullMaybeHandle,
6567  GetLiftoffFrameSize(decoder), func_index_);
6568  auto* frame_state_info = zone->New<compiler::FrameStateInfo>(
6569  BytecodeOffset(decoder->pc_offset()),
6570  compiler::OutputFrameStateCombine::Ignore(), function_info);
6571 
6572  // Limit the maximum amount of inputs to a deopt node to a reasonably low
6573  // value. For each of these values extra metadata needs to be stored for the
6574  // deoptimizer while the performance upside of a deoptimization node doesn't
6575  // scale with the amount of inputs, so there are diminishing returns.
6576  constexpr size_t max_deopt_input_count = 500;
6577  // We don't want to include the instruction selector just for this limit.
6578  constexpr size_t max_isel_input_count =
6579  std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max();
6580  // Note that the instruction selector has limits on the maximum amount of
6581  // inputs for an instruction while nested FrameStates are unfolded, so the
6582  // total number of inputs after unfolding needs to be lower than
6583  // uint16_t::max (adding a random 42 here for additional "lower-level"
6584  // inputs that might not be accounted for in the FrameState inputs.)
6585  // The number of inputs might be doubled by the Int64Lowering on 32 bit
6586  // platforms.
6587  static_assert((max_deopt_input_count * 2 + 42) *
6588  InliningTree::kMaxInliningNestingDepth <
6589  max_isel_input_count);
6590  if (builder.Inputs().size() >= max_deopt_input_count) {
6591  if (v8_flags.trace_wasm_inlining) {
6592  PrintF(
6593  "[function %d%s: Disabling deoptimizations for speculative "
6594  "inlining as the deoptimization FrameState takes too many inputs "
6595  "(%zu vs. %zu)]\n",
6596  func_index_, mode_ == kRegular ? "" : " (inlined)",
6597  builder.Inputs().size(), max_deopt_input_count);
6598  }
6599  // If there are too many inputs, disable deopts completely for the rest of
6600  // the function as the FrameState could be needed by other deoptimization
6601  // points in case of nested inlining.
6602  disable_deopts();
6603  return OpIndex::Invalid();
6604  }
6605 
6606  return __ FrameState(
6607  builder.Inputs(), builder.inlined(),
6608  builder.AllocateFrameStateData(*frame_state_info, zone));
6609  }
6610 
6611  void DeoptIfNot(FullDecoder* decoder, OpIndex deopt_condition,
6612  V<FrameState> frame_state) {
6613  CHECK(deopts_enabled());
6614  DCHECK(frame_state.valid());
6615  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(deopt_condition, frame_state,
6616  DeoptimizeReason::kWrongCallTarget,
6617  compiler::FeedbackSource());
6618  }
6619 
6620  void Deopt(FullDecoder* decoder, V<FrameState> frame_state) {
6621  CHECK(deopts_enabled());
6622  DCHECK(frame_state.valid());
6623  __ Deoptimize(frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongCallTarget,
6624  compiler::FeedbackSource());
6625  }
6626 
6627  uint32_t GetLiftoffFrameSize(const FullDecoder* decoder) {
6628  if (liftoff_frame_size_ !=
6629  FunctionTypeFeedback::kUninitializedLiftoffFrameSize) {
6630  return liftoff_frame_size_;
6631  }
6632  const TypeFeedbackStorage& feedback = decoder->module_->type_feedback;
6633  base::MutexGuard mutex_guard(&feedback.mutex);
6634  auto function_feedback = feedback.feedback_for_function.find(func_index_);
6635  CHECK_NE(function_feedback, feedback.feedback_for_function.end());
6636  liftoff_frame_size_ = function_feedback->second.liftoff_frame_size;
6637  // The liftoff frame size is strictly required. If it is not properly set,
6638  // calling the function embedding the deopt node will always fail on the
6639  // stack check.
6640  CHECK_NE(liftoff_frame_size_,
6641  FunctionTypeFeedback::kUninitializedLiftoffFrameSize);
6642  return liftoff_frame_size_;
6643  }
6644 
6645  V<Word64> ExtractTruncationProjections(V<Tuple<Word64, Word32>> truncated) {
6646  V<Word64> result = __ template Projection<0>(truncated);
6647  V<Word32> check = __ template Projection<1>(truncated);
6648  __ TrapIf(__ Word32Equal(check, 0), TrapId::kTrapFloatUnrepresentable);
6649  return result;
6650  }
6651 
6652  std::pair<OpIndex, V<Word32>> BuildCCallForFloatConversion(
6653  OpIndex arg, MemoryRepresentation float_type,
6654  ExternalReference ccall_ref) {
6655  uint8_t slot_size = MemoryRepresentation::Int64().SizeInBytes();
6656  V<WordPtr> stack_slot = __ StackSlot(slot_size, slot_size);
6657  __ Store(stack_slot, arg, StoreOp::Kind::RawAligned(), float_type,
6658  compiler::WriteBarrierKind::kNoWriteBarrier);
6659  MachineType reps[]{MachineType::Int32(), MachineType::Pointer()};
6660  MachineSignature sig(1, 1, reps);
6661  V<Word32> overflow = CallC(&sig, ccall_ref, stack_slot);
6662  return {stack_slot, overflow};
6663  }
6664 
6665  OpIndex BuildCcallConvertFloat(OpIndex arg, MemoryRepresentation float_type,
6666  ExternalReference ccall_ref) {
6667  auto [stack_slot, overflow] =
6668  BuildCCallForFloatConversion(arg, float_type, ccall_ref);
6669  __ TrapIf(__ Word32Equal(overflow, 0),
6670  compiler::TrapId::kTrapFloatUnrepresentable);
6671  MemoryRepresentation int64 = MemoryRepresentation::Int64();
6672  return __ Load(stack_slot, LoadOp::Kind::RawAligned(), int64);
6673  }
6674 
6675  OpIndex BuildCcallConvertFloatSat(OpIndex arg,
6676  MemoryRepresentation float_type,
6677  ExternalReference ccall_ref,
6678  bool is_signed) {
6679  MemoryRepresentation int64 = MemoryRepresentation::Int64();
6680  uint8_t slot_size = int64.SizeInBytes();
6681  V<WordPtr> stack_slot = __ StackSlot(slot_size, slot_size);
6682  __ Store(stack_slot, arg, StoreOp::Kind::RawAligned(), float_type,
6683  compiler::WriteBarrierKind::kNoWriteBarrier);
6684  MachineType reps[]{MachineType::Pointer()};
6685  MachineSignature sig(0, 1, reps);
6686  CallC(&sig, ccall_ref, stack_slot);
6687  return __ Load(stack_slot, LoadOp::Kind::RawAligned(), int64);
6688  }

6690  OpIndex BuildIntToFloatConversionInstruction(
6691  OpIndex input, ExternalReference ccall_ref,
6692  MemoryRepresentation input_representation,
6693  MemoryRepresentation result_representation) {
6694  uint8_t slot_size = std::max(input_representation.SizeInBytes(),
6695  result_representation.SizeInBytes());
6696  V<WordPtr> stack_slot = __ StackSlot(slot_size, slot_size);
6697  __ Store(stack_slot, input, StoreOp::Kind::RawAligned(),
6698  input_representation, compiler::WriteBarrierKind::kNoWriteBarrier);
6699  MachineType reps[]{MachineType::Pointer()};
6700  MachineSignature sig(0, 1, reps);
6701  CallC(&sig, ccall_ref, stack_slot);
6702  return __ Load(stack_slot, LoadOp::Kind::RawAligned(),
6703  result_representation);
6704  }
6705 
6706  OpIndex BuildDiv64Call(OpIndex lhs, OpIndex rhs, ExternalReference ccall_ref,
6707  wasm::TrapId trap_zero) {
6708  MemoryRepresentation int64_rep = MemoryRepresentation::Int64();
6709  V<WordPtr> stack_slot =
6710  __ StackSlot(2 * int64_rep.SizeInBytes(), int64_rep.SizeInBytes());
6711  __ Store(stack_slot, lhs, StoreOp::Kind::RawAligned(), int64_rep,
6712  compiler::WriteBarrierKind::kNoWriteBarrier);
6713  __ Store(stack_slot, rhs, StoreOp::Kind::RawAligned(), int64_rep,
6714  compiler::WriteBarrierKind::kNoWriteBarrier,
6715  int64_rep.SizeInBytes());
6716 
6717  MachineType sig_types[] = {MachineType::Int32(), MachineType::Pointer()};
6718  MachineSignature sig(1, 1, sig_types);
6719  OpIndex rc = CallC(&sig, ccall_ref, stack_slot);
6720  __ TrapIf(__ Word32Equal(rc, 0), trap_zero);
6721  __ TrapIf(__ Word32Equal(rc, -1), TrapId::kTrapDivUnrepresentable);
6722  return __ Load(stack_slot, LoadOp::Kind::RawAligned(), int64_rep);
6723  }
6724 
6725  OpIndex UnOpImpl(WasmOpcode opcode, OpIndex arg,
6726  ValueType input_type /* for ref.is_null only*/) {
6727  switch (opcode) {
6728  case kExprI32Eqz:
6729  return __ Word32Equal(arg, 0);

6811  V<Float32> converted_back = __ ChangeInt32ToFloat32(converted);
6812 
6813  Label<Word32> done(&asm_);
6814 
6815  IF (LIKELY(__ Float32Equal(truncated, converted_back))) {
6816  GOTO(done, converted);
6817  } ELSE {
6818  // Overflow.
6819  IF (__ Float32Equal(arg, arg)) {
6820  // Not NaN.
6821  IF (__ Float32LessThan(arg, 0)) {
6822  // Negative arg.
6823  GOTO(done,
6824  __ Word32Constant(std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min()));
6825  } ELSE {
6826  // Positive arg.
6827  GOTO(done,
6828  __ Word32Constant(std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max()));
6829  }
6830  } ELSE {
6831  // NaN.
6832  GOTO(done, __ Word32Constant(0));
6833  }
6834  }
6835  BIND(done, result);
6836

7216  return __ ChangeUint32ToUint64(
7217  CallC(&sig, ExternalReference::wasm_word64_ctz(), arg));
7218  } else {
7219  // lower_word == 0 ? 32 + CTZ32(upper_word) : CTZ32(lower_word);

7221  __ TruncateWord64ToWord32(__ Word64ShiftRightLogical(arg, 32));
7222  OpIndex lower_word = __ TruncateWord64ToWord32(arg);

7224  FixedSizeSignature<MachineType>::Returns(MachineType::Uint32())
7225  .Params(MachineType::Uint32());

7228  GOTO(done,
7229  __ Word32Add(CallC(&sig, ExternalReference::wasm_word32_ctz(),
7230  upper_word),
7231  32));
7232  } ELSE {
7233  GOTO(done,
7234  CallC(&sig, ExternalReference::wasm_word32_ctz(), lower_word));
7235  }
7236  BIND(done, result);
7237  return __ ChangeUint32ToUint64(result);

7311  case kExprI32AsmjsLoadMem16U:
7312  return AsmjsLoadMem(arg, MemoryRepresentation::Uint16());
7313  case kExprI32AsmjsLoadMem:
7314  return AsmjsLoadMem(arg, MemoryRepresentation::Int32());
7315  case kExprF32AsmjsLoadMem:
7316  return AsmjsLoadMem(arg, MemoryRepresentation::Float32());
7317  case kExprF64AsmjsLoadMem:
7318  return AsmjsLoadMem(arg, MemoryRepresentation::Float64());
7319  case kExprI32AsmjsSConvertF32:
7320  case kExprI32AsmjsUConvertF32:
7321  return __ JSTruncateFloat64ToWord32(__ ChangeFloat32ToFloat64(arg));
7322  case kExprI32AsmjsSConvertF64:
7323  case kExprI32AsmjsUConvertF64:
7324  return __ JSTruncateFloat64ToWord32(arg);
7325  case kExprRefAsNonNull:
7326  // We abuse ref.as_non_null, which isn't otherwise used in this switch,
7327  // as a sentinel for the negation of ref.is_null.
7328  return __ Word32Equal(__ IsNull(arg, input_type), 0);
7329  case kExprAnyConvertExtern:
7330  return __ AnyConvertExtern(arg, input_type.is_shared());
7331  case kExprExternConvertAny:
7332  return __ ExternConvertAny(arg);
7333  default:
7334  UNREACHABLE();
7335  }
7336  }
7337 
7338  OpIndex BinOpImpl(WasmOpcode opcode, OpIndex lhs, OpIndex rhs) {
7339  switch (opcode) {
7340  case kExprI32Add:
7341  return __ Word32Add(lhs, rhs);
7342  case kExprI32Sub:
7343  return __ Word32Sub(lhs, rhs);
7344  case kExprI32Mul:
7345  return __ Word32Mul(lhs, rhs);
7346  case kExprI32DivS: {
7347  __ TrapIf(__ Word32Equal(rhs, 0), TrapId::kTrapDivByZero);
7348  V<Word32> unrepresentable_condition = __ Word32BitwiseAnd(
7349  __ Word32Equal(rhs, -1), __ Word32Equal(lhs, kMinInt));
7350  __ TrapIf(unrepresentable_condition, TrapId::kTrapDivUnrepresentable);
7351  return __ Int32Div(lhs, rhs);
7352  }
7353  case kExprI32DivU:
7354  __ TrapIf(__ Word32Equal(rhs, 0), TrapId::kTrapDivByZero);
7355  return __ Uint32Div(lhs, rhs);
7356  case kExprI32RemS: {
7357  __ TrapIf(__ Word32Equal(rhs, 0), TrapId::kTrapRemByZero);
7358  Label<Word32> done(&asm_);
7359  IF (UNLIKELY(__ Word32Equal(rhs, -1))) {
7360  GOTO(done, __ Word32Constant(0));
7361  } ELSE {
7362  GOTO(done, __ Int32Mod(lhs, rhs));
7363  };
7364 
7365  BIND(done, result);
7366  return result;
7367  }
7368  case kExprI32RemU:
7369  __ TrapIf(__ Word32Equal(rhs, 0), TrapId::kTrapRemByZero);
7370  return __ Uint32Mod(lhs, rhs);
7371  case kExprI32And:
7372  return __ Word32BitwiseAnd(lhs, rhs);
7373  case kExprI32Ior:
7374  return __ Word32BitwiseOr(lhs, rhs);
7375  case kExprI32Xor:
7376  return __ Word32BitwiseXor(lhs, rhs);
7377  case kExprI32Shl:
7378  // If possible, the bitwise-and gets optimized away later.
7379  return __ Word32ShiftLeft(lhs, __ Word32BitwiseAnd(rhs, 0x1f));
7380  case kExprI32ShrS:
7381  return __ Word32ShiftRightArithmetic(lhs,
7382  __ Word32BitwiseAnd(rhs, 0x1f));
7383  case kExprI32ShrU:
7384  return __ Word32ShiftRightLogical(lhs, __ Word32BitwiseAnd(rhs, 0x1f));
7385  case kExprI32Ror:
7386  return __ Word32RotateRight(lhs, __ Word32BitwiseAnd(rhs, 0x1f));
7387  case kExprI32Rol:
7388  if (SupportedOperations::word32_rol()) {
7389  return __ Word32RotateLeft(lhs, __ Word32BitwiseAnd(rhs, 0x1f));
7390  } else {
7391  return __ Word32RotateRight(
7392  lhs, __ Word32Sub(32, __ Word32BitwiseAnd(rhs, 0x1f)));
7393  }
7394  case kExprI32Eq:
7395  return __ Word32Equal(lhs, rhs);
7396  case kExprI32Ne:
7397  return __ Word32Equal(__ Word32Equal(lhs, rhs), 0);
7398  case kExprI32LtS:
7399  return __ Int32LessThan(lhs, rhs);
7400  case kExprI32LeS:
7401  return __ Int32LessThanOrEqual(lhs, rhs);
7402  case kExprI32LtU:
7403  return __ Uint32LessThan(lhs, rhs);
7404  case kExprI32LeU:
7405  return __ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(lhs, rhs);
7406  case kExprI32GtS:
7407  return __ Int32LessThan(rhs, lhs);
7408  case kExprI32GeS:
7409  return __ Int32LessThanOrEqual(rhs, lhs);
7410  case kExprI32GtU:
7411  return __ Uint32LessThan(rhs, lhs);
7412  case kExprI32GeU:
7413  return __ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(rhs, lhs);
7414  case kExprI64Add:
7415  return __ Word64Add(lhs, rhs);
7416  case kExprI64Sub:
7417  return __ Word64Sub(lhs, rhs);
7418  case kExprI64Mul:
7419  return __ Word64Mul(lhs, rhs);
7420  case kExprI64DivS: {
7421  if constexpr (!Is64()) {
7422  return BuildDiv64Call(lhs, rhs, ExternalReference::wasm_int64_div(),
7423  wasm::TrapId::kTrapDivByZero);
7424  }
7425  __ TrapIf(__ Word64Equal(rhs, 0), TrapId::kTrapDivByZero);
7426  V<Word32> unrepresentable_condition = __ Word32BitwiseAnd(
7427  __ Word64Equal(rhs, -1),
7428  __ Word64Equal(lhs, std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min()));
7429  __ TrapIf(unrepresentable_condition, TrapId::kTrapDivUnrepresentable);
7430  return __ Int64Div(lhs, rhs);
7431  }
7432  case kExprI64DivU:
7433  if constexpr (!Is64()) {
7434  return BuildDiv64Call(lhs, rhs, ExternalReference::wasm_uint64_div(),
7435  wasm::TrapId::kTrapDivByZero);
7436  }
7437  __ TrapIf(__ Word64Equal(rhs, 0), TrapId::kTrapDivByZero);
7438  return __ Uint64Div(lhs, rhs);
7439  case kExprI64RemS: {
7440  if constexpr (!Is64()) {
7441  return BuildDiv64Call(lhs, rhs, ExternalReference::wasm_int64_mod(),
7442  wasm::TrapId::kTrapRemByZero);
7443  }
7444  __ TrapIf(__ Word64Equal(rhs, 0), TrapId::kTrapRemByZero);
7445  Label<Word64> done(&asm_);
7446  IF (UNLIKELY(__ Word64Equal(rhs, -1))) {
7447  GOTO(done, __ Word64Constant(int64_t{0}));
7448  } ELSE {
7449  GOTO(done, __ Int64Mod(lhs, rhs));
7450  };
7451 
7452  BIND(done, result);
7453  return result;
7454  }
7455  case kExprI64RemU:
7456  if constexpr (!Is64()) {
7457  return BuildDiv64Call(lhs, rhs, ExternalReference::wasm_uint64_mod(),
7458  wasm::TrapId::kTrapRemByZero);
7459  }
7460  __ TrapIf(__ Word64Equal(rhs, 0), TrapId::kTrapRemByZero);
7461  return __ Uint64Mod(lhs, rhs);
7462  case kExprI64And:
7463  return __ Word64BitwiseAnd(lhs, rhs);
7464  case kExprI64Ior:
7465  return __ Word64BitwiseOr(lhs, rhs);
7466  case kExprI64Xor:
7467  return __ Word64BitwiseXor(lhs, rhs);
7468  case kExprI64Shl:
7469  // If possible, the bitwise-and gets optimized away later.
7470  return __ Word64ShiftLeft(
7471  lhs, __ Word32BitwiseAnd(__ TruncateWord64ToWord32(rhs), 0x3f));
7472  case kExprI64ShrS:
7473  return __ Word64ShiftRightArithmetic(
7474  lhs, __ Word32BitwiseAnd(__ TruncateWord64ToWord32(rhs), 0x3f));
7475  case kExprI64ShrU:
7476  return __ Word64ShiftRightLogical(
7477  lhs, __ Word32BitwiseAnd(__ TruncateWord64ToWord32(rhs), 0x3f));
7478  case kExprI64Ror:
7479  return __ Word64RotateRight(
7480  lhs, __ Word32BitwiseAnd(__ TruncateWord64ToWord32(rhs), 0x3f));
7481  case kExprI64Rol:
7482  if (SupportedOperations::word64_rol()) {
7483  return __ Word64RotateLeft(
7484  lhs, __ Word32BitwiseAnd(__ TruncateWord64ToWord32(rhs), 0x3f));
7485  } else {
7486  return __ Word64RotateRight(
7487  lhs, __ Word32BitwiseAnd(
7488  __ Word32Sub(64, __ TruncateWord64ToWord32(rhs)), 0x3f));
7489  }
7490  case kExprI64Eq:
7491  return __ Word64Equal(lhs, rhs);
7492  case kExprI64Ne:
7493  return __ Word32Equal(__ Word64Equal(lhs, rhs), 0);
7494  case kExprI64LtS:
7495  return __ Int64LessThan(lhs, rhs);
7496  case kExprI64LeS:
7497  return __ Int64LessThanOrEqual(lhs, rhs);
7498  case kExprI64LtU:
7499  return __ Uint64LessThan(lhs, rhs);
7500  case kExprI64LeU:
7501  return __ Uint64LessThanOrEqual(lhs, rhs);
7502  case kExprI64GtS:
7503  return __ Int64LessThan(rhs, lhs);
7504  case kExprI64GeS:
7505  return __ Int64LessThanOrEqual(rhs, lhs);
7506  case kExprI64GtU:
7507  return __ Uint64LessThan(rhs, lhs);
7508  case kExprI64GeU:
7509  return __ Uint64LessThanOrEqual(rhs, lhs);
7510  case kExprF32CopySign: {
7511  V<Word32> lhs_without_sign =
7512  __ Word32BitwiseAnd(__ BitcastFloat32ToWord32(lhs), 0x7fffffff);
7513  V<Word32> rhs_sign =
7514  __ Word32BitwiseAnd(__ BitcastFloat32ToWord32(rhs), 0x80000000);
7515  return __ BitcastWord32ToFloat32(
7516  __ Word32BitwiseOr(lhs_without_sign, rhs_sign));
7517  }
7518  case kExprF32Add:
7519  return __ Float32Add(lhs, rhs);
7520  case kExprF32Sub:
7521  return __ Float32Sub(lhs, rhs);
7522  case kExprF32Mul:
7523  return __ Float32Mul(lhs, rhs);
7524  case kExprF32Div:
7525  return __ Float32Div(lhs, rhs);
7526  case kExprF32Eq:
7527  return __ Float32Equal(lhs, rhs);
7528  case kExprF32Ne:
7529  return __ Word32Equal(__ Float32Equal(lhs, rhs), 0);
7530  case kExprF32Lt:
7531  return __ Float32LessThan(lhs, rhs);
7532  case kExprF32Le:
7533  return __ Float32LessThanOrEqual(lhs, rhs);
7534  case kExprF32Gt:
7535  return __ Float32LessThan(rhs, lhs);
7536  case kExprF32Ge:
7537  return __ Float32LessThanOrEqual(rhs, lhs);
7538  case kExprF32Min:
7539  return __ Float32Min(rhs, lhs);
7540  case kExprF32Max:
7541  return __ Float32Max(rhs, lhs);
7542  case kExprF64CopySign: {
7543  V<Word64> lhs_without_sign = __ Word64BitwiseAnd(
7544  __ BitcastFloat64ToWord64(lhs), 0x7fffffffffffffff);
7545  V<Word64> rhs_sign = __ Word64BitwiseAnd(__ BitcastFloat64ToWord64(rhs),
7546  0x8000000000000000);
7547  return __ BitcastWord64ToFloat64(
7548  __ Word64BitwiseOr(lhs_without_sign, rhs_sign));
7549  }
7550  case kExprF64Add:
7551  return __ Float64Add(lhs, rhs);
7552  case kExprF64Sub:
7553  return __ Float64Sub(lhs, rhs);
7554  case kExprF64Mul:
7555  return __ Float64Mul(lhs, rhs);
7556  case kExprF64Div:
7557  return __ Float64Div(lhs, rhs);
7558  case kExprF64Eq:
7559  return __ Float64Equal(lhs, rhs);
7560  case kExprF64Ne:
7561  return __ Word32Equal(__ Float64Equal(lhs, rhs), 0);
7562  case kExprF64Lt:
7563  return __ Float64LessThan(lhs, rhs);
7564  case kExprF64Le:
7565  return __ Float64LessThanOrEqual(lhs, rhs);
7566  case kExprF64Gt:
7567  return __ Float64LessThan(rhs, lhs);
7568  case kExprF64Ge:
7569  return __ Float64LessThanOrEqual(rhs, lhs);
7570  case kExprF64Min:
7571  return __ Float64Min(lhs, rhs);
7572  case kExprF64Max:
7573  return __ Float64Max(lhs, rhs);
7574  case kExprF64Pow:
7575  return __ Float64Power(lhs, rhs);
7576  case kExprF64Atan2:
7577  return __ Float64Atan2(lhs, rhs);
7578  case kExprF64Mod:
7579  return CallCStackSlotToStackSlot(
7580  lhs, rhs, ExternalReference::f64_mod_wrapper_function(),
7581  MemoryRepresentation::Float64());
7582  case kExprRefEq:
7583  return __ TaggedEqual(lhs, rhs);
7584  case kExprI32AsmjsDivS: {
7585  // asmjs semantics return 0 when dividing by 0.
7586  if (SupportedOperations::int32_div_is_safe()) {
7587  return __ Int32Div(lhs, rhs);
7588  }
7589  Label<Word32> done(&asm_);
7590  IF (UNLIKELY(__ Word32Equal(rhs, 0))) {
7591  GOTO(done, __ Word32Constant(0));
7592  } ELSE {
7593  IF (UNLIKELY(__ Word32Equal(rhs, -1))) {
7594  GOTO(done, __ Word32Sub(0, lhs));
7595  } ELSE {
7596  GOTO(done, __ Int32Div(lhs, rhs));
7597  }
7598  }
7599  BIND(done, result);
7600  return result;
7601  }
7602  case kExprI32AsmjsDivU: {
7603  // asmjs semantics return 0 when dividing by 0.
7604  if (SupportedOperations::uint32_div_is_safe()) {
7605  return __ Uint32Div(lhs, rhs);
7606  }
7607  Label<Word32> done(&asm_);
7608  IF (UNLIKELY(__ Word32Equal(rhs, 0))) {
7609  GOTO(done, __ Word32Constant(0));
7610  } ELSE {
7611  GOTO(done, __ Uint32Div(lhs, rhs));
7612  }
7613  BIND(done, result);
7614  return result;
7615  }
7616  case kExprI32AsmjsRemS: {
7617  // General case for signed integer modulus, with optimization for
7618  // (unknown) power of 2 right hand side.
7619  //
7620  // if 0 < rhs then
7621  // mask = rhs - 1
7622  // if rhs & mask != 0 then
7623  // lhs % rhs
7624  // else
7625  // if lhs < 0 then
7626  // -(-lhs & mask)
7627  // else
7628  // lhs & mask
7629  // else
7630  // if rhs < -1 then
7631  // lhs % rhs
7632  // else
7633  // zero
7634  Label<Word32> done(&asm_);
7635  IF (__ Int32LessThan(0, rhs)) {
7636  V<Word32> mask = __ Word32Sub(rhs, 1);
7637  IF (__ Word32Equal(__ Word32BitwiseAnd(rhs, mask), 0)) {
7638  IF (UNLIKELY(__ Int32LessThan(lhs, 0))) {
7639  V<Word32> neg_lhs = __ Word32Sub(0, lhs);
7640  V<Word32> combined = __ Word32BitwiseAnd(neg_lhs, mask);
7641  GOTO(done, __ Word32Sub(0, combined));
7642  } ELSE {
7643  GOTO(done, __ Word32BitwiseAnd(lhs, mask));
7644  }
7645  } ELSE {
7646  GOTO(done, __ Int32Mod(lhs, rhs));
7647  }
7648  } ELSE {
7649  IF (__ Int32LessThan(rhs, -1)) {
7650  GOTO(done, __ Int32Mod(lhs, rhs));
7651  } ELSE {
7652  GOTO(done, __ Word32Constant(0));
7653  }
7654  }
7655  BIND(done, result);
7656  return result;
7657  }
7658  case kExprI32AsmjsRemU: {
7659  // asmjs semantics return 0 for mod with 0.
7660  Label<Word32> done(&asm_);
7661  IF (UNLIKELY(__ Word32Equal(rhs, 0))) {
7662  GOTO(done, __ Word32Constant(0));
7663  } ELSE {
7664  GOTO(done, __ Uint32Mod(lhs, rhs));
7665  }
7666  BIND(done, result);
7667  return result;
7668  }
7669  case kExprI32AsmjsStoreMem8:
7670  AsmjsStoreMem(lhs, rhs, MemoryRepresentation::Int8());
7671  return rhs;
7672  case kExprI32AsmjsStoreMem16:
7673  AsmjsStoreMem(lhs, rhs, MemoryRepresentation::Int16());
7674  return rhs;
7675  case kExprI32AsmjsStoreMem:
7676  AsmjsStoreMem(lhs, rhs, MemoryRepresentation::Int32());
7677  return rhs;
7678  case kExprF32AsmjsStoreMem:
7679  AsmjsStoreMem(lhs, rhs, MemoryRepresentation::Float32());
7680  return rhs;
7681  case kExprF64AsmjsStoreMem:
7682  AsmjsStoreMem(lhs, rhs, MemoryRepresentation::Float64());
7683  return rhs;
7684  default:
7685  UNREACHABLE();
7686  }
7687  }
7688 
7689  std::pair<V<WordPtr>, compiler::BoundsCheckResult> BoundsCheckMem(
7690  const wasm::WasmMemory* memory, MemoryRepresentation repr, OpIndex index,
7691  uintptr_t offset, compiler::EnforceBoundsCheck enforce_bounds_check,
7692  compiler::AlignmentCheck alignment_check) {
7693  // The function body decoder already validated that the access is not
7694  // statically OOB.
7695  DCHECK(base::IsInBounds(offset, static_cast<uintptr_t>(repr.SizeInBytes()),
7696  memory->max_memory_size));
7697 
7698  wasm::BoundsCheckStrategy bounds_checks = memory->bounds_checks;
7699  // Convert the index to uintptr.
7700  // TODO(jkummerow): This should reuse MemoryAddressToUintPtrOrOOBTrap.
7701  V<WordPtr> converted_index = index;
7702  if (!memory->is_memory64()) {
7703  // Note: this doesn't just satisfy the compiler's internal consistency
7704  // checks, it's also load-bearing to prevent escaping from a compromised
7705  // sandbox (where in-sandbox corruption can cause the high word of
7706  // what's supposed to be an i32 to be non-zero).
7707  converted_index = __ ChangeUint32ToUintPtr(index);
7708  } else if (kSystemPointerSize == kInt32Size) {
7709  // Truncate index to 32-bit.
7710  converted_index = V<WordPtr>::Cast(__ TruncateWord64ToWord32(index));
7711  }
7712 
7713  const uintptr_t align_mask = repr.SizeInBytes() - 1;
7714  // Do alignment checks only for > 1 byte accesses (otherwise they trivially
7715  // pass).
7716  if (static_cast<bool>(alignment_check) && align_mask != 0) {
7717  // TODO(14108): Optimize constant index as per wasm-compiler.cc.
7718 
7719  // Unlike regular memory accesses, atomic memory accesses should trap if
7720  // the effective offset is misaligned.
7721  // TODO(wasm): this addition is redundant with one inserted by
7722  // {MemBuffer}.
7723  OpIndex effective_offset =
7724  __ WordPtrAdd(MemBuffer(memory->index, offset), converted_index);
7725 
7726  V<Word32> cond = __ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(__ WordPtrBitwiseAnd(
7727  effective_offset, __ IntPtrConstant(align_mask)));
7728  __ TrapIfNot(__ Word32Equal(cond, __ Word32Constant(0)),
7729  TrapId::kTrapUnalignedAccess);
7730  }
7731 
7732  // If no bounds checks should be performed (for testing), just return the
7733  // converted index and assume it to be in-bounds.
7734  if (bounds_checks == wasm::kNoBoundsChecks) {
7735  return {converted_index, compiler::BoundsCheckResult::kInBounds};
7736  }
7737 
7738  if (memory->is_memory64() && kSystemPointerSize == kInt32Size) {
7739  // In memory64 mode on 32-bit systems, the upper 32 bits need to be zero
7740  // to succeed the bounds check.
7741  DCHECK_EQ(kExplicitBoundsChecks, bounds_checks);
7742  V<Word32> high_word =
7743  __ TruncateWord64ToWord32(__ Word64ShiftRightLogical(index, 32));
7744  __ TrapIf(high_word, TrapId::kTrapMemOutOfBounds);
7745  }
7746 
7747  uintptr_t end_offset = offset + repr.SizeInBytes() - 1u;
7748  DCHECK_LT(end_offset, memory->max_memory_size);
7749 
7750  // The index can be invalid if we are generating unreachable operations.
7751  if (end_offset <= memory->min_memory_size && index.valid() &&
7752  __ output_graph().Get(index).Is<ConstantOp>()) {
7753  ConstantOp& constant_index_op =
7754  __ output_graph().Get(index).Cast<ConstantOp>();
7755  uintptr_t constant_index = memory->is_memory64()
7756  ? constant_index_op.word64()
7757  : constant_index_op.word32();
7758  if (constant_index < memory->min_memory_size - end_offset) {
7759  return {converted_index, compiler::BoundsCheckResult::kInBounds};
7760  }
7761  }
7762 
7763 #if V8_TRAP_HANDLER_SUPPORTED
7764  if (bounds_checks == kTrapHandler &&
7765  enforce_bounds_check ==
7766  compiler::EnforceBoundsCheck::kCanOmitBoundsCheck) {
7767  if (memory->is_memory64()) {
7768  // Bounds check `index` against `kMaxMemory64Size - end_offset`, such
7769  // that at runtime `index + end_offset` will be within
7770  // `kMaxMemory64Size`, where the trap handler can handle out-of-bound
7771  // accesses.
7772  V<Word32> cond = __ Uint64LessThan(
7773  V<Word64>::Cast(converted_index),
7774  __ Word64Constant(uint64_t{wasm::kMaxMemory64Size - end_offset}));
7775  __ TrapIfNot(cond, TrapId::kTrapMemOutOfBounds);
7776  }
7777  return {converted_index, compiler::BoundsCheckResult::kTrapHandler};
7778  }
7779 #else
7780  CHECK_NE(bounds_checks, kTrapHandler);
7781 #endif // V8_TRAP_HANDLER_SUPPORTED
7782 
7783  V<WordPtr> memory_size = MemSize(memory->index);
7784  if (end_offset > memory->min_memory_size) {
7785  // The end offset is larger than the smallest memory.
7786  // Dynamically check the end offset against the dynamic memory size.
7787  __ TrapIfNot(
7788  __ UintPtrLessThan(__ UintPtrConstant(end_offset), memory_size),
7789  TrapId::kTrapMemOutOfBounds);
7790  }
7791 
7792  // This produces a positive number since {end_offset <= min_size <=
7793  // mem_size}.
7794  V<WordPtr> effective_size = __ WordPtrSub(memory_size, end_offset);
7795  __ TrapIfNot(__ UintPtrLessThan(converted_index, effective_size),
7796  TrapId::kTrapMemOutOfBounds);
7797  return {converted_index, compiler::BoundsCheckResult::kDynamicallyChecked};
7798  }
7799 
7800  V<WordPtr> MemStart(uint32_t index) {
7801  if (index == 0) {
7802  // TODO(14108): Port TF's dynamic "cached_memory_index" infrastructure.
7803  return instance_cache_.memory0_start();
7804  } else {
7805  // TODO(14616): Fix sharedness.
7806  V<TrustedFixedAddressArray> instance_memories =
7807  LOAD_IMMUTABLE_PROTECTED_INSTANCE_FIELD(trusted_instance_data(false),
7808  MemoryBasesAndSizes,
7809  TrustedFixedAddressArray);
7810  return __ Load(instance_memories, LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase(),
7811  MemoryRepresentation::UintPtr(),
7812  TrustedFixedAddressArray::OffsetOfElementAt(2 * index));
7813  }
7814  }
7815 
7816  V<WordPtr> MemBuffer(uint32_t mem_index, uintptr_t offset) {
7817  V<WordPtr> mem_start = MemStart(mem_index);
7818  if (offset == 0) return mem_start;
7819  return __ WordPtrAdd(mem_start, offset);
7820  }
7821 
7822  V<WordPtr> MemSize(uint32_t index) {
7823  if (index == 0) {
7824  // TODO(14108): Port TF's dynamic "cached_memory_index" infrastructure.
7825  return instance_cache_.memory0_size();
7826  } else {
7827  // TODO(14616): Fix sharedness.
7828  V<TrustedByteArray> instance_memories =
7829  LOAD_IMMUTABLE_PROTECTED_INSTANCE_FIELD(trusted_instance_data(false),
7830  MemoryBasesAndSizes,
7831  TrustedByteArray);
7832  return __ Load(
7833  instance_memories, LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase().NotLoadEliminable(),
7834  MemoryRepresentation::UintPtr(),
7835  TrustedFixedAddressArray::OffsetOfElementAt(2 * index + 1));
7836  }
7837  }
7838 
7839  LoadOp::Kind GetMemoryAccessKind(
7840  MemoryRepresentation repr,
7841  compiler::BoundsCheckResult bounds_check_result) {
7842  LoadOp::Kind result;
7843  if (bounds_check_result == compiler::BoundsCheckResult::kTrapHandler) {
7844  DCHECK(repr == MemoryRepresentation::Int8() ||
7845  repr == MemoryRepresentation::Uint8() ||
7846  SupportedOperations::IsUnalignedLoadSupported(repr));
7847  result = LoadOp::Kind::Protected();
7848  } else if (repr != MemoryRepresentation::Int8() &&
7849  repr != MemoryRepresentation::Uint8() &&
7850  !SupportedOperations::IsUnalignedLoadSupported(repr)) {
7851  result = LoadOp::Kind::RawUnaligned();
7852  } else {
7853  result = LoadOp::Kind::RawAligned();
7854  }
7855  return result.NotLoadEliminable();
7856  }
7857 
7858  void TraceMemoryOperation(FullDecoder* decoder, bool is_store,
7859  MemoryRepresentation repr, V<WordPtr> index,
7860  uintptr_t offset) {
7861  int kAlign = 4; // Ensure that the LSB is 0, like a Smi.
7862  V<WordPtr> info = __ StackSlot(sizeof(MemoryTracingInfo), kAlign);
7863  V<WordPtr> effective_offset = __ WordPtrAdd(index, offset);
7864  __ Store(info, effective_offset, StoreOp::Kind::RawAligned(),
7865  MemoryRepresentation::UintPtr(), compiler::kNoWriteBarrier,
7866  offsetof(MemoryTracingInfo, offset));
7867  __ Store(info, __ Word32Constant(is_store ? 1 : 0),
7868  StoreOp::Kind::RawAligned(), MemoryRepresentation::Uint8(),
7869  compiler::kNoWriteBarrier, offsetof(MemoryTracingInfo, is_store));
7870  V<Word32> rep_as_int = __ Word32Constant(
7871  static_cast<int>(repr.ToMachineType().representation()));
7872  __ Store(info, rep_as_int, StoreOp::Kind::RawAligned(),
7873  MemoryRepresentation::Uint8(), compiler::kNoWriteBarrier,
7874  offsetof(MemoryTracingInfo, mem_rep));
7875  CallRuntime(decoder->zone(), Runtime::kWasmTraceMemory, {info},
7876  __ NoContextConstant());
7877  }
7878 
7879  void StackCheck(WasmStackCheckOp::Kind kind, FullDecoder* decoder) {
7880  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!v8_flags.wasm_stack_checks)) return;
7881  __ WasmStackCheck(kind);
7882  }
7883 
7884  private:
7885  std::pair<V<Word32>, V<HeapObject>> BuildImportedFunctionTargetAndImplicitArg(
7886  FullDecoder* decoder, uint32_t function_index) {
7887  ModuleTypeIndex sig_index =
7888  decoder->module_->functions[function_index].sig_index;
7889  bool shared = decoder->module_->type(sig_index).is_shared;
7890  return WasmGraphBuilderBase::BuildImportedFunctionTargetAndImplicitArg(
7891  function_index, trusted_instance_data(shared));
7892  }
7893 
7894  // Returns the call target and the implicit argument (WasmTrustedInstanceData
7895  // or WasmImportData) for an indirect call.
7896  std::pair<V<Word32>, V<ExposedTrustedObject>>
7897  BuildIndirectCallTargetAndImplicitArg(FullDecoder* decoder,
7898  V<WordPtr> index_wordptr,
7899  CallIndirectImmediate imm,
7900  bool needs_type_or_null_check = true) {
7901  static_assert(kV8MaxWasmTableSize < size_t{kMaxInt});
7902  const WasmTable* table = imm.table_imm.table;
7903 
7904  /* Step 1: Load the indirect function tables for this table. */
7905  V<WasmDispatchTable> dispatch_table;
7906  if (imm.table_imm.index == 0) {
7907  dispatch_table =
7908  LOAD_PROTECTED_INSTANCE_FIELD(trusted_instance_data(table->shared),
7909  DispatchTable0, WasmDispatchTable);
7910  } else {
7911  V<ProtectedFixedArray> dispatch_tables =
7912  LOAD_IMMUTABLE_PROTECTED_INSTANCE_FIELD(
7913  trusted_instance_data(table->shared), DispatchTables,
7914  ProtectedFixedArray);
7915  dispatch_table =
7916  V<WasmDispatchTable>::Cast(__ LoadProtectedFixedArrayElement(
7917  dispatch_tables, imm.table_imm.index));
7918  }
7919 
7920  /* Step 2: Bounds check against the table size. */
7921  V<Word32> table_length;
7922  bool needs_dynamic_size =
7923  !table->has_maximum_size || table->maximum_size != table->initial_size;
7924  if (needs_dynamic_size) {
7925  table_length = __ LoadField<Word32>(
7926  dispatch_table, AccessBuilder::ForWasmDispatchTableLength());
7927  } else {
7928  table_length = __ Word32Constant(table->initial_size);
7929  }
7930  V<Word32> in_bounds = __ UintPtrLessThan(
7931  index_wordptr, __ ChangeUint32ToUintPtr(table_length));
7932  __ TrapIfNot(in_bounds, TrapId::kTrapTableOutOfBounds);
7933 
7934  /* Step 3: Check the canonical real signature against the canonical declared
7935  * signature. */
7936  ModuleTypeIndex sig_index = imm.sig_imm.index;
7937  bool needs_type_check =
7938  needs_type_or_null_check &&
7939  !EquivalentTypes(table->type.AsNonNull(),
7940  ValueType::Ref(imm.sig_imm.heap_type()),
7941  decoder->module_);
7942  bool needs_null_check =
7943  needs_type_or_null_check && table->type.is_nullable();
7944 
7945  V<WordPtr> dispatch_table_entry_offset = __ WordPtrAdd(
7946  __ WordPtrMul(index_wordptr, WasmDispatchTable::kEntrySize),
7947  WasmDispatchTable::kEntriesOffset);
7948 
7949  if (needs_type_check) {
7950  CanonicalTypeIndex sig_id = env_->module->canonical_sig_id(sig_index);
7951  V<Word32> expected_canonical_sig =
7952  __ RelocatableWasmCanonicalSignatureId(sig_id.index);
7953 
7954  V<Word32> loaded_sig =
7955  __ Load(dispatch_table, dispatch_table_entry_offset,
7956  LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase(), MemoryRepresentation::Uint32(),
7957  WasmDispatchTable::kSigBias);
7958  V<Word32> sigs_match = __ Word32Equal(expected_canonical_sig, loaded_sig);
7959  if (!decoder->module_->type(sig_index).is_final) {
7960  // In this case, a full type check is needed.
7961  Label<> end(&asm_);
7962 
7963  // First, check if signatures happen to match exactly.
7964  GOTO_IF(sigs_match, end);
7965 
7966  if (needs_null_check) {
7967  // Trap on null element.
7968  __ TrapIf(__ Word32Equal(loaded_sig, -1),
7969  TrapId::kTrapFuncSigMismatch);
7970  }
7971  bool shared = decoder->module_->type(sig_index).is_shared;
7972  V<Map> formal_rtt = __ RttCanon(managed_object_maps(shared), sig_index);
7973  int rtt_depth = GetSubtypingDepth(decoder->module_, sig_index);
7974  DCHECK_GE(rtt_depth, 0);
7975 
7976  // Since we have the canonical index of the real rtt, we have to load it
7977  // from the isolate rtt-array (which is canonically indexed). Since this
7978  // reference is weak, we have to promote it to a strong reference.
7979  // Note: The reference cannot have been cleared: Since the loaded_sig
7980  // corresponds to a function of the same canonical type, that function
7981  // will have kept the type alive.
7982  V<WeakFixedArray> rtts = LOAD_ROOT(WasmCanonicalRtts);
7983  V<Object> weak_rtt = __ Load(
7984  rtts, __ ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(loaded_sig),
7985  LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase(), MemoryRepresentation::TaggedPointer(),
7986  OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(WeakFixedArray), kTaggedSizeLog2);
7987  V<Map> real_rtt =
7988  V<Map>::Cast(__ BitcastWordPtrToTagged(__ WordPtrBitwiseAnd(
7989  __ BitcastHeapObjectToWordPtr(V<HeapObject>::Cast(weak_rtt)),
7990  ~kWeakHeapObjectMask)));
7991  V<WasmTypeInfo> type_info =
7992  __ Load(real_rtt, LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase(),
7993  MemoryRepresentation::TaggedPointer(),
7994  Map::kConstructorOrBackPointerOrNativeContextOffset);
7995  // If the depth of the rtt is known to be less than the minimum
7996  // supertype array length, we can access the supertype without
7997  // bounds-checking the supertype array.
7998  if (static_cast<uint32_t>(rtt_depth) >=
7999  wasm::kMinimumSupertypeArraySize) {
8000  V<Word32> supertypes_length =
8001  __ UntagSmi(__ Load(type_info, LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase(),
8002  MemoryRepresentation::TaggedSigned(),
8003  WasmTypeInfo::kSupertypesLengthOffset));
8004  __ TrapIfNot(__ Uint32LessThan(rtt_depth, supertypes_length),
8005  OpIndex::Invalid(), TrapId::kTrapFuncSigMismatch);
8006  }
8007  V<Map> maybe_match =
8008  __ Load(type_info, LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase(),
8009  MemoryRepresentation::TaggedPointer(),
8010  WasmTypeInfo::kSupertypesOffset + kTaggedSize * rtt_depth);
8011  __ TrapIfNot(__ TaggedEqual(maybe_match, formal_rtt),
8012  OpIndex::Invalid(), TrapId::kTrapFuncSigMismatch);
8013  GOTO(end);
8014  BIND(end);
8015  } else {
8016  // In this case, signatures must match exactly.
8017  __ TrapIfNot(sigs_match, TrapId::kTrapFuncSigMismatch);
8018  }
8019  } else if (needs_null_check) {
8020  V<Word32> loaded_sig =
8021  __ Load(dispatch_table, dispatch_table_entry_offset,
8022  LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase(), MemoryRepresentation::Uint32(),
8023  WasmDispatchTable::kSigBias);
8024  __ TrapIf(__ Word32Equal(-1, loaded_sig), TrapId::kTrapFuncSigMismatch);
8025  }
8026 
8027  /* Step 4: Extract ref and target. */
8028  V<Word32> target = __ Load(
8029  dispatch_table, dispatch_table_entry_offset, LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase(),
8030  MemoryRepresentation::Uint32(), WasmDispatchTable::kTargetBias);
8031  V<ExposedTrustedObject> implicit_arg =
8032  V<ExposedTrustedObject>::Cast(__ LoadProtectedPointerField(
8033  dispatch_table, dispatch_table_entry_offset,
8034  LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase(), WasmDispatchTable::kImplicitArgBias,
8035  0));
8036 
8037  return {target, implicit_arg};
8038  }
8039 
8040  // Load the call target and implicit arg (WasmTrustedInstanceData or
8041  // WasmImportData) from a function reference.
8042  std::pair<V<Word32>, V<ExposedTrustedObject>>
8043  BuildFunctionReferenceTargetAndImplicitArg(V<WasmFuncRef> func_ref,
8044  ValueType type) {
8045  if (type.is_nullable() &&
8046  null_check_strategy_ == compiler::NullCheckStrategy::kExplicit) {
8047  func_ref = V<WasmFuncRef>::Cast(
8048  __ AssertNotNull(func_ref, type, TrapId::kTrapNullDereference));
8049  }
8050 
8051  LoadOp::Kind load_kind =
8052  type.is_nullable() && null_check_strategy_ ==
8053  compiler::NullCheckStrategy::kTrapHandler
8054  ? LoadOp::Kind::TrapOnNull().Immutable()
8055  : LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase().Immutable();
8056 
8057  V<WasmInternalFunction> internal_function =
8058  V<WasmInternalFunction>::Cast(__ LoadTrustedPointerField(
8059  func_ref, load_kind, kWasmInternalFunctionIndirectPointerTag,
8060  WasmFuncRef::kTrustedInternalOffset));
8061 
8062  return BuildFunctionTargetAndImplicitArg(internal_function);
8063  }
8064 
8065  OpIndex AnnotateResultIfReference(OpIndex result, wasm::ValueType type) {
8066  return type.is_object_reference()
8067  ? __ AnnotateWasmType(V<Object>::Cast(result), type)
8068  : result;
8069  }
8070 
8071  void BuildWasmCall(
8072  FullDecoder* decoder, const FunctionSig* sig, V<CallTarget> callee,
8073  V<HeapObject> ref, const Value args[], Value returns[],
8074  compiler::WasmCallKind call_kind = compiler::WasmCallKind::kWasmFunction,
8075  CheckForException check_for_exception =
8076  CheckForException::kCatchInThisFrame) {
8077  const TSCallDescriptor* descriptor = TSCallDescriptor::Create(
8078  compiler::GetWasmCallDescriptor(__ graph_zone(), sig, call_kind),
8079  compiler::CanThrow::kYes, compiler::LazyDeoptOnThrow::kNo,
8080  __ graph_zone());
8081 
8082  SmallZoneVector<OpIndex, 16> arg_indices(sig->parameter_count() + 1,
8083  decoder->zone());
8084  arg_indices[0] = ref;
8085  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < sig->parameter_count(); i++) {
8086  arg_indices[i + 1] = args[i].op;
8087  }
8088 
8089  OpIndex call = CallAndMaybeCatchException(
8090  decoder, callee, base::VectorOf(arg_indices), descriptor,
8091  check_for_exception, OpEffects().CanCallAnything());
8092 
8093  if (sig->return_count() == 1) {
8094  returns[0].op = AnnotateResultIfReference(call, sig->GetReturn(0));
8095  } else if (sig->return_count() > 1) {
8096  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < sig->return_count(); i++) {
8097  wasm::ValueType type = sig->GetReturn(i);
8098  returns[i].op = AnnotateResultIfReference(
8099  __ Projection(call, i, RepresentationFor(type)), type);
8100  }
8101  }
8102  // Calls might mutate cached instance fields.
8103  instance_cache_.ReloadCachedMemory();
8104  }
8105 
8106  private:
8107  void BuildWasmMaybeReturnCall(
8108  FullDecoder* decoder, const FunctionSig* sig, V<CallTarget> callee,
8109  V<HeapObject> ref, const Value args[],
8110  compiler::WasmCallKind call_kind = compiler::kWasmFunction) {
8111  if (mode_ == kRegular || mode_ == kInlinedTailCall) {
8112  const TSCallDescriptor* descriptor = TSCallDescriptor::Create(
8113  compiler::GetWasmCallDescriptor(__ graph_zone(), sig, call_kind),
8114  compiler::CanThrow::kYes, compiler::LazyDeoptOnThrow::kNo,
8115  __ graph_zone());
8116 
8117  SmallZoneVector<OpIndex, 16> arg_indices(sig->parameter_count() + 1,
8118  decoder->zone_);
8119  arg_indices[0] = ref;
8120  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < sig->parameter_count(); i++) {
8121  arg_indices[i + 1] = args[i].op;
8122  }
8123  __ TailCall(callee, base::VectorOf(arg_indices), descriptor);
8124  } else {
8125  if (__ generating_unreachable_operations()) return;
8126  // This is a tail call in the inlinee, which in turn was a regular call.
8127  // Transform the tail call into a regular call, and return the return
8128  // values to the caller.
8129  size_t return_count = sig->return_count();
8130  SmallZoneVector<Value, 16> returns(return_count, decoder->zone_);
8131  // Since an exception in a tail call cannot be caught in this frame, we
8132  // should only catch exceptions in the generated call if this is a
8133  // recursively inlined function, and the parent frame provides a handler.
8134  BuildWasmCall(decoder, sig, callee, ref, args, returns.data(), call_kind,
8135  CheckForException::kCatchInParentFrame);
8136  for (size_t i = 0; i < return_count; i++) {
8137  return_phis_->AddInputForPhi(i, returns[i].op);
8138  }
8139  __ Goto(return_block_);
8140  }
8141  }

8143  template <typename Descriptor>
8144  compiler::turboshaft::detail::index_type_for_t<typename Descriptor::results_t>
8145  CallBuiltinThroughJumptable(
8146  FullDecoder* decoder, const typename Descriptor::arguments_t& args,
8147  CheckForException check_for_exception = CheckForException::kNo)
8148  requires(!Descriptor::kNeedsContext)
8149  {
8150  DCHECK_NE(check_for_exception, CheckForException::kCatchInParentFrame);
8151 
8152  V<WordPtr> callee =
8153  __ RelocatableWasmBuiltinCallTarget(Descriptor::kFunction);
8154  auto arguments = std::apply(
8155  [](auto&&... as) {
8156  return base::SmallVector<
8157  OpIndex, std::tuple_size_v<typename Descriptor::arguments_t> + 1>{
8158  std::forward<decltype(as)>(as)...};
8159  },
8160  args);
8161 
8162  return CallAndMaybeCatchException(
8163  decoder, callee, base::VectorOf(arguments),
8164  Descriptor::Create(StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub,
8165  __ output_graph().graph_zone()),
8166  check_for_exception, Descriptor::kEffects);
8167  }
8168 
8169  template <typename Descriptor>
8170  compiler::turboshaft::detail::index_type_for_t<typename Descriptor::results_t>
8171  CallBuiltinThroughJumptable(
8172  FullDecoder* decoder, V<Context> context,
8173  const typename Descriptor::arguments_t& args,
8174  CheckForException check_for_exception = CheckForException::kNo)
8175  requires Descriptor::kNeedsContext
8176  {
8177  DCHECK_NE(check_for_exception, CheckForException::kCatchInParentFrame);
8178 
8179  V<WordPtr> callee =
8180  __ RelocatableWasmBuiltinCallTarget(Descriptor::kFunction);
8181  auto arguments = std::apply(
8182  [context](auto&&... as) {
8183  return base::SmallVector<
8184  OpIndex, std::tuple_size_v<typename Descriptor::arguments_t> + 1>{
8185  std::forward<decltype(as)>(as)..., context};
8186  },
8187  args);
8188 
8189  return CallAndMaybeCatchException(
8190  decoder, callee, base::VectorOf(arguments),
8191  Descriptor::Create(StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub,
8192  __ output_graph().graph_zone()),

8196  template <typename Descriptor>
8197  compiler::turboshaft::detail::index_type_for_t<typename Descriptor::results_t>
8198  CallBuiltinByPointer(

8200  CheckForException check_for_exception = CheckForException::kNo)

8210  std::forward<decltype(as)>(as)...};
8211  },

8220 
8221  private:
8222  void MaybeSetPositionToParent(OpIndex call,
8223  CheckForException check_for_exception) {
8224  // For tail calls that we transform to regular calls, we need to set the
8225  // call's position to that of the inlined call node to get correct stack
8226  // traces.
8227  if (check_for_exception == CheckForException::kCatchInParentFrame) {
8228  __ output_graph().operation_origins()[call] = WasmPositionToOpIndex(
8229  parent_position_.ScriptOffset(), parent_position_.InliningId() == -1
8230  ? kNoInliningId
8231  : parent_position_.InliningId());
8232  }
8233  }
8234 
8235  OpIndex CallAndMaybeCatchException(FullDecoder* decoder, V<CallTarget> callee,
8236  base::Vector<const OpIndex> args,
8237  const TSCallDescriptor* descriptor,
8238  CheckForException check_for_exception,
8239  OpEffects effects) {
8240  if (check_for_exception == CheckForException::kNo) {
8241  return __ Call(callee, OpIndex::Invalid(), args, descriptor, effects);
8242  }
8243  bool handled_in_this_frame =
8244  decoder && decoder->current_catch() != -1 &&
8245  check_for_exception == CheckForException::kCatchInThisFrame;
8246  if (!handled_in_this_frame && mode_ != kInlinedWithCatch) {
8247  OpIndex call =
8248  __ Call(callee, OpIndex::Invalid(), args, descriptor, effects);
8249  MaybeSetPositionToParent(call, check_for_exception);
8250  return call;
8251  }
8252 
8253  TSBlock* catch_block;
8254  if (handled_in_this_frame) {
8255  Control* current_catch =
8256  decoder->control_at(decoder->control_depth_of_current_catch());
8257  catch_block = current_catch->false_or_loop_or_catch_block;
8258  } else {
8259  DCHECK_EQ(mode_, kInlinedWithCatch);
8260  catch_block = return_catch_block_;
8261  }
8262  TSBlock* success_block = __ NewBlock();
8263  TSBlock* exception_block = __ NewBlock();
8264  OpIndex call;
8265  {
8266  Assembler::CatchScope scope(asm_, exception_block);
8267 
8268  call = __ Call(callee, OpIndex::Invalid(), args, descriptor, effects);
8269  __ Goto(success_block);
8270  }
8271 
8272  __ Bind(exception_block);
8273  OpIndex exception = __ CatchBlockBegin();
8274  if (handled_in_this_frame) {
8275  // The exceptional operation could have modified memory size; we need
8276  // to reload the memory context into the exceptional control path.
8277  instance_cache_.ReloadCachedMemory();
8278  SetupControlFlowEdge(decoder, catch_block, 0, exception);
8279  } else {
8280  DCHECK_EQ(mode_, kInlinedWithCatch);
8281  if (exception.valid()) return_phis_->AddIncomingException(exception);
8282  // Reloading the InstanceCache will happen when {return_exception_phis_}
8283  // are retrieved.
8284  }
8285  __ Goto(catch_block);
8286 
8287  __ Bind(success_block);
8288 
8289  MaybeSetPositionToParent(call, check_for_exception);
8290 
8291  return call;
8292  }
8293 
8294  OpIndex CallCStackSlotToInt32(OpIndex arg, ExternalReference ref,
8295  MemoryRepresentation arg_type) {
8296  OpIndex stack_slot_param =
8297  __ StackSlot(arg_type.SizeInBytes(), arg_type.SizeInBytes());
8298  __ Store(stack_slot_param, arg, StoreOp::Kind::RawAligned(), arg_type,
8299  compiler::WriteBarrierKind::kNoWriteBarrier);
8300  MachineType reps[]{MachineType::Int32(), MachineType::Pointer()};
8301  MachineSignature sig(1, 1, reps);
8302  return CallC(&sig, ref, stack_slot_param);
8303  }
8304 
8305  V<Word32> CallCStackSlotToInt32(
8306  ExternalReference ref,
8307  std::initializer_list<std::pair<OpIndex, MemoryRepresentation>> args) {
8308  int slot_size = 0;
8309  for (auto arg : args) slot_size += arg.second.SizeInBytes();
8310  // Since we are storing the arguments unaligned anyway, we do not need
8311  // alignment > 0.
8312  V<WordPtr> stack_slot_param = __ StackSlot(slot_size, 0);
8313  int offset = 0;
8314  for (auto arg : args) {
8315  __ Store(stack_slot_param, arg.first,
8316  StoreOp::Kind::MaybeUnaligned(arg.second), arg.second,
8317  compiler::WriteBarrierKind::kNoWriteBarrier, offset);
8318  offset += arg.second.SizeInBytes();
8319  }
8320  MachineType reps[]{MachineType::Int32(), MachineType::Pointer()};
8321  MachineSignature sig(1, 1, reps);
8322  return CallC(&sig, ref, stack_slot_param);
8323  }
8324 
8325  OpIndex CallCStackSlotToStackSlot(
8326  ExternalReference ref, MemoryRepresentation res_type,
8327  std::initializer_list<std::pair<OpIndex, MemoryRepresentation>> args) {
8328  int slot_size = 0;
8329  for (auto arg : args) slot_size += arg.second.SizeInBytes();
8330  // Since we are storing the arguments unaligned anyway, we do not need
8331  // alignment > 0.
8332  slot_size = std::max<int>(slot_size, res_type.SizeInBytes());
8333  V<WordPtr> stack_slot_param = __ StackSlot(slot_size, 0);
8334  int offset = 0;
8335  for (auto arg : args) {
8336  __ Store(stack_slot_param, arg.first,
8337  StoreOp::Kind::MaybeUnaligned(arg.second), arg.second,
8338  compiler::WriteBarrierKind::kNoWriteBarrier, offset);
8339  offset += arg.second.SizeInBytes();
8340  }
8341  MachineType reps[]{MachineType::Pointer()};
8342  MachineSignature sig(0, 1, reps);
8343  CallC(&sig, ref, stack_slot_param);
8344  return __ Load(stack_slot_param, LoadOp::Kind::RawAligned(), res_type);
8345  }
8346 
8347  OpIndex CallCStackSlotToStackSlot(OpIndex arg, ExternalReference ref,
8348  MemoryRepresentation arg_type) {
8349  return CallCStackSlotToStackSlot(arg, ref, arg_type, arg_type);
8350  }
8351 
8352  OpIndex CallCStackSlotToStackSlot(OpIndex arg, ExternalReference ref,
8353  MemoryRepresentation arg_type,
8354  MemoryRepresentation res_type) {
