8356  }
8357 
8358  OpIndex CallCStackSlotToStackSlot(OpIndex arg0, OpIndex arg1,
8359  ExternalReference ref,
8360  MemoryRepresentation arg_type) {
8361  return CallCStackSlotToStackSlot(ref, arg_type,
8362  {{arg0, arg_type}, {arg1, arg_type}});
8363  }
8364 
8365  V<WordPtr> MemOrTableAddressToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(AddressType address_type,
8366  V<Word> index,
8367  TrapId trap_reason) {
8368  // Note: this {ChangeUint32ToUintPtr} doesn't just satisfy the compiler's
8369  // consistency checks, it's also load-bearing to prevent escaping from a
8370  // compromised sandbox (where in-sandbox corruption can cause the high
8371  // word of what's supposed to be an i32 to be non-zero).
8372  if (address_type == AddressType::kI32) {
8373  return __ ChangeUint32ToUintPtr(V<Word32>::Cast(index));
8374  }
8375  if constexpr (Is64()) {
8376  return V<WordPtr>::Cast(index);
8377  }
8378  __ TrapIf(__ TruncateWord64ToWord32(
8379  __ Word64ShiftRightLogical(V<Word64>::Cast(index), 32)),
8380  OpIndex::Invalid(), trap_reason);
8381  return V<WordPtr>::Cast(__ TruncateWord64ToWord32(V<Word64>::Cast(index)));
8382  }
8383 
8384  V<WordPtr> MemoryAddressToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(AddressType address_type,
8385  V<Word> index) {
8386  return MemOrTableAddressToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(address_type, index,
8387  TrapId::kTrapMemOutOfBounds);
8388  }
8389 
8390  V<WordPtr> TableAddressToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(AddressType address_type,
8391  V<Word> index) {
8392  return MemOrTableAddressToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(address_type, index,
8393  TrapId::kTrapTableOutOfBounds);
8394  }
8395 
8396  V<Smi> ChangeUint31ToSmi(V<Word32> value) {
8397  if constexpr (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
8398  return V<Smi>::Cast(
8399  __ Word32ShiftLeft(value, kSmiShiftSize + kSmiTagSize));
8400  } else {
8401  return V<Smi>::Cast(__ WordPtrShiftLeft(__ ChangeUint32ToUintPtr(value),
8402  kSmiShiftSize + kSmiTagSize));
8403  }
8404  }
8405 
8406  V<Word32> ChangeSmiToUint32(V<Smi> value) {
8407  if constexpr (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
8408  return __ Word32ShiftRightLogical(V<Word32>::Cast(value),
8409  kSmiShiftSize + kSmiTagSize);
8410  } else {
8411  return __ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(__ WordPtrShiftRightLogical(
8412  V<WordPtr>::Cast(value), kSmiShiftSize + kSmiTagSize));
8413  }
8414  }
8415 
8416  void BuildEncodeException32BitValue(V<FixedArray> values_array,
8417  uint32_t index, V<Word32> value) {
8418  V<Smi> upper_half =
8419  ChangeUint31ToSmi(__ Word32ShiftRightLogical(value, 16));
8420  __ StoreFixedArrayElement(values_array, index, upper_half,
8421  compiler::kNoWriteBarrier);
8422  V<Smi> lower_half = ChangeUint31ToSmi(__ Word32BitwiseAnd(value, 0xffffu));
8423  __ StoreFixedArrayElement(values_array, index + 1, lower_half,
8424  compiler::kNoWriteBarrier);
8425  }
8426 
8427  V<Word32> BuildDecodeException32BitValue(V<FixedArray> exception_values_array,
8428  int index) {
8429  V<Word32> upper_half = __ Word32ShiftLeft(
8430  ChangeSmiToUint32(V<Smi>::Cast(
8431  __ LoadFixedArrayElement(exception_values_array, index))),
8432  16);
8433  V<Word32> lower_half = ChangeSmiToUint32(V<Smi>::Cast(
8434  __ LoadFixedArrayElement(exception_values_array, index + 1)));
8435  return __ Word32BitwiseOr(upper_half, lower_half);
8436  }
8437 
8438  V<Word64> BuildDecodeException64BitValue(V<FixedArray> exception_values_array,
8439  int index) {
8440  V<Word64> upper_half = __ Word64ShiftLeft(
8441  __ ChangeUint32ToUint64(
8442  BuildDecodeException32BitValue(exception_values_array, index)),
8443  32);
8444  V<Word64> lower_half = __ ChangeUint32ToUint64(
8445  BuildDecodeException32BitValue(exception_values_array, index + 2));
8446  return __ Word64BitwiseOr(upper_half, lower_half);
8447  }
8448 
8449  void UnpackWasmException(FullDecoder* decoder, V<Object> exception,
8450  base::Vector<Value> values) {
8451  V<FixedArray> exception_values_array = V<FixedArray>::Cast(
8452  CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmGetOwnProperty>(
8453  decoder, instance_cache_.native_context(),
8454  {exception, LOAD_ROOT(wasm_exception_values_symbol)}));
8455 
8456  int index = 0;
8457  for (Value& value : values) {
8458  switch (value.type.kind()) {
8459  case kI32:
8460  value.op =
8461  BuildDecodeException32BitValue(exception_values_array, index);
8462  index += 2;
8463  break;
8464  case kI64:
8465  value.op =
8466  BuildDecodeException64BitValue(exception_values_array, index);
8467  index += 4;
8468  break;
8469  case kF32:
8470  value.op = __ BitcastWord32ToFloat32(
8471  BuildDecodeException32BitValue(exception_values_array, index));
8472  index += 2;
8473  break;
8474  case kF64:
8475  value.op = __ BitcastWord64ToFloat64(
8476  BuildDecodeException64BitValue(exception_values_array, index));
8477  index += 4;
8478  break;
8479  case kS128: {
8480  V<compiler::turboshaft::Simd128> value_s128;
8481  value_s128 = __ Simd128Splat(
8482  BuildDecodeException32BitValue(exception_values_array, index),
8483  compiler::turboshaft::Simd128SplatOp::Kind::kI32x4);
8484  index += 2;
8485  using Kind = compiler::turboshaft::Simd128ReplaceLaneOp::Kind;
8486  value_s128 = __ Simd128ReplaceLane(
8487  value_s128,
8488  BuildDecodeException32BitValue(exception_values_array, index),
8489  Kind::kI32x4, 1);
8490  index += 2;
8491  value_s128 = __ Simd128ReplaceLane(
8492  value_s128,
8493  BuildDecodeException32BitValue(exception_values_array, index),
8494  Kind::kI32x4, 2);
8495  index += 2;
8496  value.op = __ Simd128ReplaceLane(
8497  value_s128,
8498  BuildDecodeException32BitValue(exception_values_array, index),
8499  Kind::kI32x4, 3);
8500  index += 2;
8501  break;
8502  }
8503  case kRef:
8504  case kRefNull:
8505  value.op = __ LoadFixedArrayElement(exception_values_array, index);
8506  index++;
8507  break;
8508  case kI8:
8509  case kI16:
8510  case kF16:
8511  case kVoid:
8512  case kTop:
8513  case kBottom:
8514  UNREACHABLE();
8515  }
8516  }
8517  }
8518 
8519  void ThrowRef(FullDecoder* decoder, OpIndex exn) {
8520  CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmThrowRef>(
8521  decoder, {exn}, CheckForException::kCatchInThisFrame);
8522  __ Unreachable();
8523  }
8524 
8525  void AsmjsStoreMem(V<Word32> index, OpIndex value,
8526  MemoryRepresentation repr) {
8527  // Since asmjs does not support unaligned accesses, we can bounds-check
8528  // ignoring the access size.
8529  // Technically, we should do a signed 32-to-ptr extension here. However,
8530  // that is an explicit instruction, whereas unsigned extension is implicit.
8531  // Since the difference is only observable for memories larger than 2 GiB,
8532  // and since we disallow such memories, we can use unsigned extension.
8533  V<WordPtr> index_ptr = __ ChangeUint32ToUintPtr(index);
8534  IF (LIKELY(__ UintPtrLessThan(index_ptr, MemSize(0)))) {
8535  __ Store(MemStart(0), index_ptr, value, StoreOp::Kind::RawAligned(), repr,
8536  compiler::kNoWriteBarrier, 0);
8537  }
8538  }
8539 
8540  OpIndex AsmjsLoadMem(V<Word32> index, MemoryRepresentation repr) {
8541  // Since asmjs does not support unaligned accesses, we can bounds-check
8542  // ignoring the access size.
8543  Variable result = __ NewVariable(repr.ToRegisterRepresentation());
8544 
8545  // Technically, we should do a signed 32-to-ptr extension here. However,
8546  // that is an explicit instruction, whereas unsigned extension is implicit.
8547  // Since the difference is only observable for memories larger than 2 GiB,
8548  // and since we disallow such memories, we can use unsigned extension.
8549  V<WordPtr> index_ptr = __ ChangeUint32ToUintPtr(index);
8550  IF (LIKELY(__ UintPtrLessThan(index_ptr, MemSize(0)))) {
8551  __ SetVariable(result, __ Load(MemStart(0), index_ptr,
8552  LoadOp::Kind::RawAligned(), repr));
8553  } ELSE {
8554  switch (repr) {
8555  case MemoryRepresentation::Int8():
8556  case MemoryRepresentation::Int16():
8557  case MemoryRepresentation::Int32():
8558  case MemoryRepresentation::Uint8():
8559  case MemoryRepresentation::Uint16():
8560  case MemoryRepresentation::Uint32():
8561  __ SetVariable(result, __ Word32Constant(0));
8562  break;
8563  case MemoryRepresentation::Float32():
8564  __ SetVariable(result, __ Float32Constant(
8565  std::numeric_limits<float>::quiet_NaN()));
8566  break;
8567  case MemoryRepresentation::Float64():
8568  __ SetVariable(result, __ Float64Constant(
8569  std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN()));
8570  break;
8571  default:
8572  UNREACHABLE();
8573  }
8574  }
8575 
8576  OpIndex result_op = __ GetVariable(result);
8577  __ SetVariable(result, OpIndex::Invalid());
8578  return result_op;
8579  }
8580 
8581  void BoundsCheckArray(V<WasmArrayNullable> array, V<Word32> index,
8582  ValueType array_type) {
8583  if (V8_UNLIKELY(v8_flags.experimental_wasm_skip_bounds_checks)) {
8584  if (array_type.is_nullable()) {
8585  __ AssertNotNull(array, array_type, TrapId::kTrapNullDereference);
8586  }
8587  } else {
8588  OpIndex length = __ ArrayLength(array, array_type.is_nullable()
8589  ? compiler::kWithNullCheck
8590  : compiler::kWithoutNullCheck);
8591  __ TrapIfNot(__ Uint32LessThan(index, length),
8592  TrapId::kTrapArrayOutOfBounds);
8593  }
8594  }
8595 
8596  V<WasmArray> BoundsCheckArrayWithLength(V<WasmArrayNullable> array,
8597  V<Word32> index, V<Word32> length,
8598  compiler::CheckForNull null_check) {
8599  if (V8_UNLIKELY(v8_flags.experimental_wasm_skip_bounds_checks)) {
8600  return V<WasmArray>::Cast(array);
8601  }
8602  V<Word32> array_length = __ ArrayLength(array, null_check);
8603  V<Word32> range_end = __ Word32Add(index, length);
8604  V<Word32> range_valid = __ Word32BitwiseAnd(
8605  // OOB if (index + length > array.len).
8606  __ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(range_end, array_length),
8607  // OOB if (index + length) overflows.
8608  __ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(index, range_end));
8609  __ TrapIfNot(range_valid, TrapId::kTrapArrayOutOfBounds);
8610  // The array is now guaranteed to be non-null.
8611  return V<WasmArray>::Cast(array);
8612  }
8613 
8614  void BrOnCastImpl(FullDecoder* decoder, V<Map> rtt,
8615  compiler::WasmTypeCheckConfig config, const Value& object,
8616  Value* value_on_branch, uint32_t br_depth,
8617  bool null_succeeds) {
8618  OpIndex cast_succeeds = __ WasmTypeCheck(object.op, rtt, config);
8619  IF (cast_succeeds) {
8620  // Narrow type for the successful cast target branch.
8621  Forward(decoder, object, value_on_branch);
8622  BrOrRet(decoder, br_depth);
8623  }
8624  // Note: Differently to below for br_on_cast_fail, we do not Forward
8625  // the value here to perform a TypeGuard. It can't be done here due to
8626  // asymmetric decoder code. A Forward here would be popped from the stack
8627  // and ignored by the decoder. Therefore the decoder has to call Forward
8628  // itself.
8629  }
8630 
8631  void BrOnCastFailImpl(FullDecoder* decoder, V<Map> rtt,
8632  compiler::WasmTypeCheckConfig config,
8633  const Value& object, Value* value_on_fallthrough,
8634  uint32_t br_depth, bool null_succeeds) {
8635  OpIndex cast_succeeds = __ WasmTypeCheck(object.op, rtt, config);
8636  IF (__ Word32Equal(cast_succeeds, 0)) {
8637  // It is necessary in case of {null_succeeds} to forward the value.
8638  // This will add a TypeGuard to the non-null type (as in this case the
8639  // object is non-nullable).
8640  Forward(decoder, object, decoder->stack_value(1));
8641  BrOrRet(decoder, br_depth);
8642  }
8643  // Narrow type for the successful cast fallthrough branch.
8644  value_on_fallthrough->op =
8645  __ AnnotateWasmType(V<Object>::Cast(object.op), config.to);
8646  }
8647 
8648  V<HeapObject> ArrayNewImpl(FullDecoder* decoder, ModuleTypeIndex index,
8649  const ArrayType* array_type, V<Word32> length,
8650  V<Any> initial_value) {
8651  // Initialize the array header.
8652  bool shared = decoder->module_->type(index).is_shared;
8653  V<Map> rtt = __ RttCanon(managed_object_maps(shared), index);
8654  V<WasmArray> array = __ WasmAllocateArray(rtt, length, array_type, shared);
8655  // Initialize the elements.
8656  ArrayFillImpl(array, __ Word32Constant(0), initial_value, length,
8657  array_type, false);
8658  return array;
8659  }
8660 
8661  V<Map> GetRttFromDescriptor(const Value& descriptor) {
8662  V<WasmStructNullable> descriptor_struct =
8663  V<WasmStructNullable>::Cast(descriptor.op);
8664  // TODO(jkummerow): Refactor this to share the logic with
8665  // wasm-lowering-reducer.h.
8666  bool force_explicit_null_check =
8667  !trap_handler::IsTrapHandlerEnabled() || !V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL;
8668  bool explicit_null_check =
8669  descriptor.type.is_nullable() && force_explicit_null_check;
8670  bool implicit_null_check =
8671  descriptor.type.is_nullable() && !force_explicit_null_check;
8672 
8673  if (explicit_null_check) {
8674  __ TrapIf(__ IsNull(descriptor_struct, wasm::kWasmAnyRef),
8675  TrapId::kTrapNullDereference);
8676  }
8677  LoadOp::Kind load_kind = implicit_null_check ? LoadOp::Kind::TrapOnNull()
8678  : LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase();
8679  load_kind = load_kind.Immutable();
8680  return __ Load(descriptor_struct, load_kind,
8681  MemoryRepresentation::TaggedPointer(),
8682  WasmStruct::kHeaderSize);
8683  }
8684 
8685  V<WasmStruct> StructNewImpl(FullDecoder* decoder,
8686  const StructIndexImmediate& imm,
8687  const Value& descriptor, OpIndex args[],
8688  bool has_nondefault_args) {
8689  const TypeDefinition& type = decoder->module_->type(imm.index);
8690  DCHECK_EQ(type.has_descriptor(), descriptor.op.valid());
8691  V<Map> rtt;
8692  if (type.has_descriptor()) {
8693  rtt = GetRttFromDescriptor(descriptor);
8694  } else {
8695  rtt = __ RttCanon(managed_object_maps(type.is_shared), imm.index);
8696  }
8697 
8698  V<WasmStruct> struct_value;
8699  if (type.is_descriptor()) {
8700  bool pass_potential_prototype =
8701  has_nondefault_args &&
8702  imm.struct_type->first_field_can_be_prototype();
8703  V<Object> first_field =
8704  pass_potential_prototype ? args[0] : __ SmiZeroConstant();
8705 
8706  struct_value = CallBuiltinThroughJumptable<
8707  BuiltinCallDescriptor::WasmAllocateDescriptorStruct>(
8708  decoder, {rtt, __ Word32Constant(imm.index.index), first_field});
8709  } else {
8710  const bool shared = type.is_shared;
8711  struct_value = __ WasmAllocateStruct(rtt, imm.struct_type, shared);
8712  }
8713 
8714  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < imm.struct_type->field_count(); ++i) {
8715  __ StructSet(struct_value, args[i], imm.struct_type, imm.index, i,
8716  compiler::kWithoutNullCheck, {});
8717  }
8718  // If this assert fails then initialization of padding field might be
8719  // necessary.
8720  static_assert(Heap::kMinObjectSizeInTaggedWords == 2 &&
8721  WasmStruct::kHeaderSize == 2 * kTaggedSize,
8722  "empty struct might require initialization of padding field");
8723  return struct_value;
8724  }
8725 
8726  bool IsSimd128ZeroConstant(OpIndex op) {
8727  DCHECK_IMPLIES(!op.valid(), __ generating_unreachable_operations());
8728  if (__ generating_unreachable_operations()) return false;
8729  const Simd128ConstantOp* s128_op =
8730  __ output_graph().Get(op).TryCast<Simd128ConstantOp>();
8731  return s128_op && s128_op->IsZero();
8732  }
8733 
8734  void ArrayFillImpl(V<WasmArray> array, V<Word32> index, V<Any> value,
8735  OpIndex length, const wasm::ArrayType* type,
8736  bool emit_write_barrier) {
8737  wasm::ValueType element_type = type->element_type();
8738 
8739  // Initialize the array. Use an external function for large arrays with
8740  // null/number initializer. Use a loop for small arrays and reference arrays
8741  // with a non-null initial value.
8742  Label<> done(&asm_);
8743 
8744  // The builtin cannot handle s128 values other than 0.
8745  if (!(element_type == wasm::kWasmS128 && !IsSimd128ZeroConstant(value))) {
8746  constexpr uint32_t kArrayNewMinimumSizeForMemSet = 16;
8747  IF_NOT (__ Uint32LessThan(
8748  length, __ Word32Constant(kArrayNewMinimumSizeForMemSet))) {
8749  OpIndex stack_slot = StoreInStackSlot(value, element_type);
8750  MachineType arg_types[]{
8751  MachineType::TaggedPointer(), MachineType::Uint32(),
8752  MachineType::Uint32(), MachineType::Uint32(),
8753  MachineType::Uint32(), MachineType::Pointer()};
8754  MachineSignature sig(0, 6, arg_types);
8755  CallC(&sig, ExternalReference::wasm_array_fill(),
8756  {array, index, length,
8757  __ Word32Constant(emit_write_barrier ? 1 : 0),
8758  __ Word32Constant(element_type.raw_bit_field()), stack_slot});
8759  GOTO(done);
8760  }
8761  }
8762 
8763  ScopedVar<Word32> current_index(this, index);
8764 
8765  WHILE(__ Uint32LessThan(current_index, __ Word32Add(index, length))) {
8766  __ ArraySet(array, current_index, value, type->element_type(), {});
8767  current_index = __ Word32Add(current_index, 1);
8768  }
8769 
8770  GOTO(done);
8771 
8772  BIND(done);
8773  }
8774 
8775  V<WordPtr> StoreInStackSlot(OpIndex value, wasm::ValueType type) {
8776  // The input is unpacked.
8777  ValueType input_type = type.Unpacked();
8778 
8779  switch (type.kind()) {
8780  case wasm::kI32:
8781  case wasm::kI8:
8782  case wasm::kI16:
8783  case wasm::kI64:
8784  case wasm::kF32:
8785  case wasm::kF64:
8786  case wasm::kRefNull:
8787  case wasm::kRef:
8788  break;
8789  case wasm::kS128:
8790  // We can only get here if {value} is the constant 0.
8791  DCHECK(__ output_graph().Get(value).Cast<Simd128ConstantOp>().IsZero());
8792  value = __ Word64Constant(uint64_t{0});
8793  input_type = kWasmI64;
8794  break;
8795  case wasm::kF16:
8796  UNIMPLEMENTED();
8797  case wasm::kVoid:
8798  case kTop:
8799  case wasm::kBottom:
8800  UNREACHABLE();
8801  }
8802 
8803  // Differently to values on the heap, stack slots are always uncompressed.
8804  MemoryRepresentation memory_rep =
8805  type.is_reference() ? MemoryRepresentation::UncompressedTaggedPointer()
8806  : MemoryRepresentation::FromMachineRepresentation(
8807  input_type.machine_representation());
8808  V<WordPtr> stack_slot =
8809  __ StackSlot(memory_rep.SizeInBytes(), memory_rep.SizeInBytes(),
8810  type.is_reference());
8811  __ Store(stack_slot, value, StoreOp::Kind::RawAligned(), memory_rep,
8812  compiler::WriteBarrierKind::kNoWriteBarrier);
8813  return stack_slot;
8814  }
8815 
8816  bool InlineTargetIsTypeCompatible(const WasmModule* module,
8817  const FunctionSig* sig,
8818  const FunctionSig* inlinee) {
8819  if (sig->parameter_count() != inlinee->parameter_count()) return false;
8820  if (sig->return_count() != inlinee->return_count()) return false;
8821  for (size_t i = 0; i < sig->return_count(); ++i) {
8822  if (!IsSubtypeOf(inlinee->GetReturn(i), sig->GetReturn(i), module))
8823  return false;
8824  }
8825  for (size_t i = 0; i < sig->parameter_count(); ++i) {
8826  if (!IsSubtypeOf(sig->GetParam(i), inlinee->GetParam(i), module))
8827  return false;
8828  }
8829  return true;
8830  }
8831 
8832  void InlineWasmCall(FullDecoder* decoder, uint32_t func_index,
8833  const FunctionSig* sig, uint32_t feedback_case,
8834  bool is_tail_call, const Value args[], Value returns[]) {
8835  DCHECK_IMPLIES(is_tail_call, returns == nullptr);
8836  const WasmFunction& inlinee = decoder->module_->functions[func_index];
8837  // In a corrupted sandbox, we can't trust the collected feedback.
8838  SBXCHECK(InlineTargetIsTypeCompatible(decoder->module_, sig, inlinee.sig));
8839 
8840  SmallZoneVector<OpIndex, 16> inlinee_args(
8841  inlinee.sig->parameter_count() + 1, decoder->zone_);
8842  bool inlinee_is_shared = decoder->module_->function_is_shared(func_index);
8843  inlinee_args[0] = trusted_instance_data(inlinee_is_shared);
8844  for (size_t i = 0; i < inlinee.sig->parameter_count(); i++) {
8845  inlinee_args[i + 1] = args[i].op;
8846  }
8847 
8848  base::Vector<const uint8_t> function_bytes =
8849  wire_bytes_->GetCode(inlinee.code);
8850 
8851  const wasm::FunctionBody inlinee_body{
8852  inlinee.sig, inlinee.code.offset(), function_bytes.begin(),
8853  function_bytes.end(), inlinee_is_shared};
8854 
8855  // If the inlinee was not validated before, do that now.
8856  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!decoder->module_->function_was_validated(func_index))) {
8857  if (ValidateFunctionBody(decoder->zone_, decoder->enabled_,
8858  decoder->module_, decoder->detected_,
8859  inlinee_body)
8860  .failed()) {
8861  // At this point we cannot easily raise a compilation error any more.
8862  // Since this situation is highly unlikely though, we just ignore this
8863  // inlinee, emit a regular call, and move on. The same validation error
8864  // will be triggered again when actually compiling the invalid function.
8865  V<WordPtr> callee =
8866  __ RelocatableConstant(func_index, RelocInfo::WASM_CALL);
8867  if (is_tail_call) {
8868  BuildWasmMaybeReturnCall(
8869  decoder, sig, callee,
8870  trusted_instance_data(
8871  decoder->module_->function_is_shared(func_index)),
8872  args);
8873  } else {
8874  BuildWasmCall(decoder, sig, callee,
8875  trusted_instance_data(
8876  decoder->module_->function_is_shared(func_index)),
8877  args, returns);
8878  }
8879  return;
8880  }
8881  decoder->module_->set_function_validated(func_index);
8882  }
8883 
8884  BlockPhis fresh_return_phis(decoder->zone_);
8885 
8886  Mode inlinee_mode;
8887  TSBlock* callee_catch_block = nullptr;
8888  TSBlock* callee_return_block;
8889  BlockPhis* inlinee_return_phis;
8890 
8891  if (is_tail_call) {
8892  if (mode_ == kInlinedTailCall || mode_ == kRegular) {
8893  inlinee_mode = kInlinedTailCall;
8894  callee_return_block = nullptr;
8895  inlinee_return_phis = nullptr;
8896  } else {
8897  // A tail call inlined inside a regular call inherits its settings,
8898  // as any `return` statement returns to the nearest non-tail caller.
8899  inlinee_mode = mode_;
8900  callee_return_block = return_block_;
8901  inlinee_return_phis = return_phis_;
8902  if (mode_ == kInlinedWithCatch) {
8903  callee_catch_block = return_catch_block_;
8904  }
8905  }
8906  } else {
8907  // Regular call (i.e. not a tail call).
8908  if (mode_ == kInlinedWithCatch || decoder->current_catch() != -1) {
8909  inlinee_mode = kInlinedWithCatch;
8910  // TODO(14108): If this is a nested inlining, can we forward the
8911  // caller's catch block instead?
8912  callee_catch_block = __ NewBlock();
8913  } else {
8914  inlinee_mode = kInlinedUnhandled;
8915  }
8916  callee_return_block = __ NewBlock();
8917  inlinee_return_phis = &fresh_return_phis;
8918  }
8919 
8920  OptionalV<FrameState> frame_state;
8921  if (deopts_enabled()) {
8922  frame_state = is_tail_call
8923  ? parent_frame_state_
8924  : CreateFrameState(decoder, sig, /*funcref*/ nullptr,
8925  /*args*/ nullptr);
8926  }
8927 
8928  WasmFullDecoder<TurboshaftGraphBuildingInterface::ValidationTag,
8929  TurboshaftGraphBuildingInterface>
8930  inlinee_decoder(decoder->zone_, decoder->module_, decoder->enabled_,
8931  decoder->detected_, inlinee_body, decoder->zone_, env_,
8932  asm_, inlinee_mode, instance_cache_, assumptions_,
8933  inlining_positions_, func_index, inlinee_is_shared,
8934  wire_bytes_, base::VectorOf(inlinee_args),
8935  callee_return_block, inlinee_return_phis,
8936  callee_catch_block, is_tail_call, frame_state);
8937  SourcePosition call_position =
8938  SourcePosition(decoder->position(), inlining_id_ == kNoInliningId
8939  ? SourcePosition::kNotInlined
8940  : inlining_id_);
8941  inlining_positions_->push_back(
8942  {static_cast<int>(func_index), is_tail_call, call_position});
8943  inlinee_decoder.interface().set_inlining_id(
8944  static_cast<uint8_t>(inlining_positions_->size() - 1));
8945  inlinee_decoder.interface().set_parent_position(call_position);
8946  // Explicitly disable deopts if it has already been disabled for this
8947  // function.
8948  if (!deopts_enabled()) {
8949  inlinee_decoder.interface().disable_deopts();
8950  }
8951  if (v8_flags.liftoff) {
8952  if (inlining_decisions_ && inlining_decisions_->feedback_found()) {
8953  inlinee_decoder.interface().set_inlining_decisions(
8954  inlining_decisions_
8955  ->function_calls()[feedback_slot_][feedback_case]);
8956  }
8957  } else {
8958  no_liftoff_inlining_budget_ -= inlinee.code.length();
8959  inlinee_decoder.interface().set_no_liftoff_inlining_budget(
8960  no_liftoff_inlining_budget_);
8961  }
8962  inlinee_decoder.Decode();
8963  // The function was already validated above.
8964  DCHECK(inlinee_decoder.ok());
8965 
8966  DCHECK_IMPLIES(!is_tail_call && inlinee_mode == kInlinedWithCatch,
8967  inlinee_return_phis != nullptr);
8968 
8969  if (!is_tail_call && inlinee_mode == kInlinedWithCatch &&
8970  !inlinee_return_phis->incoming_exceptions().empty()) {
8971  // We need to handle exceptions in the inlined call.
8972  __ Bind(callee_catch_block);
8973  OpIndex exception =
8974  MaybePhi(inlinee_return_phis->incoming_exceptions(), kWasmExternRef);
8975  bool handled_in_this_frame = decoder->current_catch() != -1;
8976  TSBlock* catch_block;
8977  if (handled_in_this_frame) {
8978  Control* current_catch =
8979  decoder->control_at(decoder->control_depth_of_current_catch());
8980  catch_block = current_catch->false_or_loop_or_catch_block;
8981  // The exceptional operation could have modified memory size; we need
8982  // to reload the memory context into the exceptional control path.
8983  instance_cache_.ReloadCachedMemory();
8984  SetupControlFlowEdge(decoder, catch_block, 0, exception);
8985  } else {
8986  DCHECK_EQ(mode_, kInlinedWithCatch);
8987  catch_block = return_catch_block_;
8988  if (exception.valid()) return_phis_->AddIncomingException(exception);
8989  // Reloading the InstanceCache will happen when {return_exception_phis_}
8990  // are retrieved.
8991  }
8992  __ Goto(catch_block);
8993  }
8994 
8995  if (!is_tail_call) {
8996  __ Bind(callee_return_block);
8997  BlockPhis* return_phis = inlinee_decoder.interface().return_phis();
8998  size_t return_count = inlinee.sig->return_count();
8999  for (size_t i = 0; i < return_count; i++) {
9000  returns[i].op =
9001  MaybePhi(return_phis->phi_inputs(i), return_phis->phi_type(i));
9002  }
9003  }
9004 
9005  if (!v8_flags.liftoff) {
9006  set_no_liftoff_inlining_budget(
9007  inlinee_decoder.interface().no_liftoff_inlining_budget());
9008  }
9009  }
9010 
9011  TrapId GetTrapIdForTrap(wasm::TrapReason reason) {
9012  switch (reason) {
9013 #define TRAPREASON_TO_TRAPID(name) \
9014  case wasm::k##name: \
9015  static_assert(static_cast<int>(TrapId::k##name) == \
9016  static_cast<int>(Builtin::kThrowWasm##name), \
9017  "trap id mismatch"); \
9018  return TrapId::k##name;
9019  FOREACH_WASM_TRAPREASON(TRAPREASON_TO_TRAPID)
9020 #undef TRAPREASON_TO_TRAPID
9021  default:
9022  UNREACHABLE();
9023  }
9024  }
9025 
9026  // We need this shift so that resulting OpIndex offsets are multiples of
9027  // `sizeof(OperationStorageSlot)`.
9028  static constexpr int kPositionFieldShift = 3;
9029  static_assert(sizeof(compiler::turboshaft::OperationStorageSlot) ==
9030  1 << kPositionFieldShift);
9031  static constexpr int kPositionFieldSize = 23;
9032  static_assert(kV8MaxWasmFunctionSize < (1 << kPositionFieldSize));
9033  static constexpr int kInliningIdFieldSize = 6;
9034  static constexpr uint8_t kNoInliningId = 63;
9035  static_assert((1 << kInliningIdFieldSize) - 1 == kNoInliningId);
9036  // We need to assign inlining_ids to inlined nodes.
9037  static_assert(kNoInliningId > InliningTree::kMaxInlinedCount);
9038 
9039  // We encode the wasm code position and the inlining index in an OpIndex
9040  // stored in the output graph's node origins.
9041  using PositionField =
9042  base::BitField<WasmCodePosition, kPositionFieldShift, kPositionFieldSize>;
9043  using InliningIdField = PositionField::Next<uint8_t, kInliningIdFieldSize>;
9044 
9045  OpIndex WasmPositionToOpIndex(WasmCodePosition position, int inlining_id) {
9046  return OpIndex::FromOffset(
9047  PositionField::encode(position) | InliningIdField::encode(inlining_id),
9048  graph_generation_bit_);
9049  }
9050 
9051  SourcePosition OpIndexToSourcePosition(OpIndex index) {
9052  DCHECK(index.valid());
9053  uint8_t inlining_id = InliningIdField::decode(index.offset());
9054  return SourcePosition(PositionField::decode(index.offset()),
9055  inlining_id == kNoInliningId
9056  ? SourcePosition::kNotInlined
9057  : inlining_id);
9058  }
9059 
9060  BranchHint GetBranchHint(FullDecoder* decoder) {
9061  // Minimize overhead when branch hints aren't being used.
9062  if (branch_hinting_mode_ == BranchHintingMode::kNone) {
9063  return BranchHint::kNone;
9064  }
9065  if (branch_hinting_mode_ == BranchHintingMode::kModuleProvided) {
9066  return branch_hints_->GetHintFor(decoder->pc_relative_offset());
9067  }
9068  if (branch_hinting_mode_ == BranchHintingMode::kStress) {
9069  return branch_hinting_stresser_.GetNextHint();
9070  }
9071  UNREACHABLE();
9072  }
9073 
9074  private:
9075  bool should_inline(FullDecoder* decoder, int feedback_slot, int size) {
9076  if (!v8_flags.wasm_inlining) return false;
9077  // TODO(42204563,41480394,335082212): Do not inline if the current function
9078  // is shared (which also implies the target cannot be shared either).
9079  if (shared_) return false;
9080 
9081  // Configuration without Liftoff and feedback, e.g., for testing.
9082  if (!v8_flags.liftoff) {
9083  return size < no_liftoff_inlining_budget_ &&
9084  // In a production configuration, `InliningTree` decides what to
9085  // (not) inline, e.g., asm.js functions or to not exceed
9086  // `kMaxInlinedCount`. But without Liftoff, we need to "manually"
9087  // comply with these constraints here.
9088  !is_asmjs_module(decoder->module_) &&
9089  inlining_positions_->size() < InliningTree::kMaxInlinedCount;
9090  }
9091 
9092  // Default, production configuration: Liftoff collects feedback, which
9093  // decides whether we inline:
9094  if (inlining_decisions_ && inlining_decisions_->feedback_found()) {
9095  DCHECK_GT(inlining_decisions_->function_calls().size(), feedback_slot);
9096  // We should inline if at least one case for this feedback slot needs
9097  // to be inlined.
9098  for (InliningTree* tree :
9099  inlining_decisions_->function_calls()[feedback_slot]) {
9100  if (tree && tree->is_inlined()) {
9101  DCHECK(!decoder->module_->function_is_shared(tree->function_index()));
9102  return true;
9103  }
9104  }
9105  return false;
9106  }
9107  return false;
9108  }
9109 
9110  void set_inlining_decisions(InliningTree* inlining_decisions) {
9111  inlining_decisions_ = inlining_decisions;
9112  }
9113 
9114  BlockPhis* return_phis() { return return_phis_; }
9115  void set_inlining_id(uint8_t inlining_id) {
9116  DCHECK_NE(inlining_id, kNoInliningId);
9117  inlining_id_ = inlining_id;
9118  }
9119  void set_parent_position(SourcePosition position) {
9120  parent_position_ = position;
9121  }
9122  int no_liftoff_inlining_budget() { return no_liftoff_inlining_budget_; }
9123  void set_no_liftoff_inlining_budget(int no_liftoff_inlining_budget) {
9124  no_liftoff_inlining_budget_ = no_liftoff_inlining_budget;
9125  }
9126 
9127  void disable_deopts() { deopts_enabled_ = false; }
9128  bool deopts_enabled() {
9129  if (!deopts_enabled_.has_value()) {
9130  deopts_enabled_ = v8_flags.wasm_deopt;
9131  if (v8_flags.wasm_deopt) {
9132  const wasm::TypeFeedbackStorage& feedback = env_->module->type_feedback;
9133  base::MutexGuard mutex_guard(&feedback.mutex);
9134  auto iter = feedback.deopt_count_for_function.find(func_index_);
9135  if (iter != feedback.deopt_count_for_function.end() &&
9136  iter->second >= v8_flags.wasm_deopts_per_function_limit) {
9137  deopts_enabled_ = false;
9138  if (v8_flags.trace_wasm_inlining) {
9139  PrintF(
9140  "[function %d%s: Disabling deoptimizations for speculative "
9141  "inlining as the deoptimization limit (%u) for this function "
9142  "is reached or exceeded (%zu)]\n",
9143  func_index_, mode_ == kRegular ? "" : " (inlined)",
9144  iter->second, v8_flags.wasm_deopts_per_function_limit.value());
9145  }
9146  }
9147  }
9148  }
9149  return deopts_enabled_.value();
9150  }
9151 
9152  V<WasmTrustedInstanceData> trusted_instance_data(bool element_is_shared) {
9153  DCHECK_IMPLIES(shared_, element_is_shared);
9154  return (element_is_shared && !shared_)
9155  ? LOAD_IMMUTABLE_PROTECTED_INSTANCE_FIELD(
9156  instance_cache_.trusted_instance_data(), SharedPart,
9157  WasmTrustedInstanceData)
9158  : instance_cache_.trusted_instance_data();
9159  }
9160 
9161  V<FixedArray> managed_object_maps(bool type_is_shared) {
9162  DCHECK_IMPLIES(shared_, type_is_shared);
9163  if (type_is_shared && !shared_) {
9164  V<WasmTrustedInstanceData> shared_instance = trusted_instance_data(true);
9165  return LOAD_IMMUTABLE_INSTANCE_FIELD(
9166  shared_instance, ManagedObjectMaps,
9167  MemoryRepresentation::TaggedPointer());
9168  } else {
9169  return instance_cache_.managed_object_maps();
9170  }
9171  }

9173  private:
9174  Mode mode_;
9175  ZoneAbslFlatHashMap<TSBlock*, BlockPhis> block_phis_;
9176  CompilationEnv* env_;
9177  // Only used for "top-level" instantiations, not for inlining.
9178  std::unique_ptr<InstanceCache> owned_instance_cache_;
9179 
9180  // The instance cache to use (may be owned or passed in).
9181  InstanceCache& instance_cache_;
9182 
9183  // Yes, a *pointer* to a `unique_ptr`. The `unique_ptr` is allocated lazily
9184  // when adding the first assumption.
9185  std::unique_ptr<AssumptionsJournal>* assumptions_;
9186  ZoneVector<WasmInliningPosition>* inlining_positions_;
9187  uint8_t inlining_id_ = kNoInliningId;
9188  ZoneVector<OpIndex> ssa_env_;
9189  compiler::NullCheckStrategy null_check_strategy_ =
9190  trap_handler::IsTrapHandlerEnabled() && V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
9191  ? compiler::NullCheckStrategy::kTrapHandler
9192  : compiler::NullCheckStrategy::kExplicit;
9193  int func_index_;
9194  bool shared_;
9195  const WireBytesStorage* wire_bytes_;
9196  BranchHintingMode branch_hinting_mode_;
9197  const BranchHintMap* branch_hints_ = nullptr;
9198  BranchHintingStresser branch_hinting_stresser_;
9199  InliningTree* inlining_decisions_ = nullptr;
9200  int feedback_slot_ = -1;
9201  // Inlining budget in case of --no-liftoff.
9202  int no_liftoff_inlining_budget_ = 0;
9203  uint32_t liftoff_frame_size_ =
9204  FunctionTypeFeedback::kUninitializedLiftoffFrameSize;
9205 
9206  /* Used for inlining modes */
9207  // Contains real parameters for this inlined function, including the instance.
9208  // Used only in StartFunction();
9209  base::Vector<OpIndex> real_parameters_;
9210  // The block where this function returns its values (passed by the caller).
9211  TSBlock* return_block_ = nullptr;
9212  // The return values and exception values for this function.
9213  // The caller will reconstruct each one with a Phi.
9214  BlockPhis* return_phis_ = nullptr;
9215  // The block where exceptions from this function are caught (passed by the
9216  // caller).
9217  TSBlock* return_catch_block_ = nullptr;
9218  // The position of the call that is being inlined.
9219  SourcePosition parent_position_;
9220  bool is_inlined_tail_call_ = false;
9221 
9222  std::optional<bool> deopts_enabled_;
9223  OptionalV<FrameState> parent_frame_state_;
9224 #ifdef DEBUG
9225  const int graph_generation_bit_ = __ output_graph().generation_mod2();
9226 #else
9227  const int graph_generation_bit_ = 0;
9228 #endif
9229 };
9230 
9231 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE void BuildTSGraph(
9232  compiler::turboshaft::PipelineData* data, AccountingAllocator* allocator,
9233  CompilationEnv* env, WasmDetectedFeatures* detected, Graph& graph,
9234  const FunctionBody& func_body, const WireBytesStorage* wire_bytes,
9235  std::unique_ptr<AssumptionsJournal>* assumptions,
9236  ZoneVector<WasmInliningPosition>* inlining_positions, int func_index) {
9237  DCHECK(env->module->function_was_validated(func_index));
9238  Zone zone(allocator, ZONE_NAME);
9239  WasmGraphBuilderBase::Assembler assembler(data, graph, graph, &zone);
9240  WasmFullDecoder<TurboshaftGraphBuildingInterface::ValidationTag,
9241  TurboshaftGraphBuildingInterface>
9242  decoder(&zone, env->module, env->enabled_features, detected, func_body,
9243  &zone, env, assembler, assumptions, inlining_positions,
9244  func_index, func_body.is_shared, wire_bytes);
9245  decoder.Decode();
9246  // The function was already validated, so graph building must always succeed.
9247  DCHECK(decoder.ok());
9248 }
